00078 void pyne::pyne_start() {
00079 #if defined __WIN_MSVC__
00080   char * tmpPYNE_DATA;
00081   size_t lenPYNE_DATA;
00082   errno_t errPYNE_DATA = _dupenv_s(&tmpPYNE_DATA, &lenPYNE_DATA, "PYNE_DATA");
00083   if (errPYNE_DATA)
00084     tmpPYNE_DATA = (char *) "<NOT_FOUND>";
00085   PYNE_DATA = (std::string) tmpPYNE_DATA;
00086 
00087   char * tmpNUC_DATA_PATH;
00088   size_t lenNUC_DATA_PATH;
00089   errno_t errNUC_DATA_PATH = _dupenv_s(&tmpNUC_DATA_PATH, &lenNUC_DATA_PATH, "NUC_DATA_PATH");
00090   if (errPYNE_DATA)
00091     tmpNUC_DATA_PATH = (char *) "<NOT_FOUND>";
00092   NUC_DATA_PATH = (std::string) tmpNUC_DATA_PATH;
00093 #else
00094   char * tmppath;
00095   tmppath = getenv("PYNE_DATA");
00096   if (tmppath == NULL)
00097       tmppath = (char *) "<NOT_FOUND>";
00098   PYNE_DATA = std::string(tmppath);
00099 
00100   tmppath = getenv("NUC_DATA_PATH");
00101   if (tmppath == NULL)
00102       tmppath = (char *) "<NOT_FOUND>";
00103   NUC_DATA_PATH = std::string(tmppath);
00104 #endif
00105   return;
00106 };

00144 double pyne::endftod_cpp(char * s) {
00145   // Converts string from ENDF only handles "E-less" format but is 5x faster
00146   int pos, mant, exp;
00147   double v, dbl_exp;
00148 
00149   mant = exp = 0;
00150   if (s[2] == '.') {
00151     // Convert an ENDF float
00152     if (s[9] == '+' or s[9] == '-') {
00153       // All these factors of ten are from place values.
00154       mant = s[8] + 10 * s[7] + 100 * s[6] + 1000 * s[5] + 10000 * s[4] + \
00155              100000 * s[3] + 1000000 * s[1] - 1111111 * '0';
00156       exp = s[10] - '0';
00157       // Make the right power of 10.
00158       dbl_exp = exp & 01? 10.: 1;
00159       dbl_exp *= (exp >>= 1) & 01? 100.: 1;
00160       dbl_exp *= (exp >>= 1) & 01? 1.0e4: 1;
00161       dbl_exp *= (exp >>= 1) & 01? 1.0e8: 1;
00162       // Adjust for powers of ten from treating mantissa as an integer.
00163       dbl_exp = (s[9] == '-'? 1/dbl_exp: dbl_exp) * 1.0e-6;
00164       // Get mantissa sign, apply exponent.
00165       v = mant * (s[0] == '-'? -1: 1) * dbl_exp;
00166     }
00167     else {
00168       mant = s[7] + 10 * s[6] + 100 * s[5] + 1000 * s[4] + 10000 * s[3] + \
00169              100000 * s[1] - 111111 * '0';
00170       exp = s[10] + 10 * s[9] - 11 * '0';
00171       dbl_exp = exp & 01? 10.: 1;
00172       dbl_exp *= (exp >>= 1) & 01? 100.: 1;
00173       dbl_exp *= (exp >>= 1) & 01? 1.0e4: 1;
00174       dbl_exp *= (exp >>= 1) & 01? 1.0e8: 1;
00175       dbl_exp *= (exp >>= 1) & 01? 1.0e16: 1;
00176       dbl_exp *= (exp >>= 1) & 01? 1.0e32: 1;
00177       dbl_exp *= (exp >>= 1) & 01? 1.0e64: 1;
00178       dbl_exp = (s[8] == '-'? 1/dbl_exp: dbl_exp) * 1.0e-5;
00179       v = mant * (s[0] == '-'? -1: 1) * dbl_exp;
00180     }
00181   }
00182 
00183   // Convert an ENDF int to float; we start from the last char in the field and
00184   // move forward until we hit a non-digit.
00185   else {
00186     v = 0;
00187     mant = 1; // Here we use mant for the place value about to be read in.
00188     pos = 10;
00189     while (s[pos] != '-' and s[pos] != '+' and s[pos] != ' ' and pos > 0) {
00190       v += mant * (s[pos] - '0');
00191       mant *= 10;
00192       pos--;
00193     }
00194     v *= (s[pos] == '-'? -1: 1);
00195   }
00196   return v;
00197 }

00199 double pyne::endftod_f(char * s) {
00200 #ifdef PYNE_IS_AMALGAMATED
00201   return endftod_cpp(s);
00202 #else
00203   return endftod_(s, 12);
00204 #endif
00205 }

00213 std::string pyne::to_upper(std::string s) {
00214   // change each element of the string to upper case.
00215   for(unsigned int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++)
00216     s[i] = toupper(s[i]);
00217   return s;
00218 }
00219 
00220 std::string pyne::to_lower(std::string s) {
00221   // change each element of the string to lower case
00222   for(unsigned int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++)
00223     s[i] = tolower(s[i]);
00224   return s;
00225 }
00226 
00227 
00228 std::string pyne::capitalize(std::string s) {
00229   unsigned int slen = s.length();
00230   if (slen == 0)
00231     return s;
00232   // uppercase the first character
00233   s[0] = toupper(s[0]);
00234   // change each subsequent element of the string to lower case
00235   for(unsigned int i = 1; i < slen; i++)
00236     s[i] = tolower(s[i]);
00237   return s;
00238 }

00241 std::string pyne::get_flag(char line[], int max_l) {
00242   char tempflag [10];
00243   for (int i = 0; i < max_l; i++)
00244   {
00245     if (line[i] == '\t' || line[i] == '\n' || line[i] == ' ' || line[i] == '\0')
00246     {
00247       tempflag[i] = '\0';
00248       break;
00249     }
00250     else
00251       tempflag[i] = line[i];
00252   }
00253   return std::string (tempflag);
00254 }

00258 std::string pyne::remove_substring(std::string s, std::string substr) {
00259   // Removes a substring from the string s
00260   int n_found = s.find(substr);
00261   while ( 0 <= n_found ) {
00262     s.erase( n_found , substr.length() );
00263     n_found = s.find(substr);
00264   }
00265   return s;
00266 }
00267 
00268 
00269 std::string pyne::remove_characters(std::string s, std::string chars) {
00270   // Removes all characters in the string chars from the string s
00271   for (int i = 0; i < chars.length(); i++ ) {
00272     s = remove_substring(s, chars.substr(i, 1) );
00273   }
00274   return s;
00275 }

00277 
00278 std::string pyne::replace_all_substrings(std::string s, std::string substr, std::string repstr) {
00279   // Replaces all instance of substr in s with the string repstr
00280   int n_found = s.find(substr);
00281   while ( 0 <= n_found ) {
00282     s.replace( n_found , substr.length(), repstr );
00283     n_found = s.find(substr);
00284   }
00285   return s;
00286 };

00308 bool pyne::contains_substring(std::string s, std::string substr) {
00309   // Returns a boolean based on if the sub is in s.
00310   int n = s.find(substr);
00311   return ( 0 <= n && n < s.length() );
00312 }

00314 
00315 std::string pyne::natural_naming(std::string name) {
00316   // Calculates a version on the string name that is a valid
00317   // variable name, ie it uses only word characters.
00318   std::string nat_name (name);
00319 
00320   // Replace Whitespace characters with underscores
00321   nat_name = pyne::replace_all_substrings(nat_name, " ",  "_");
00322   nat_name = pyne::replace_all_substrings(nat_name, "\t", "_");
00323   nat_name = pyne::replace_all_substrings(nat_name, "\n", "_");
00324 
00325   // Remove non-word characters
00326   int n = 0;
00327   while ( n < nat_name.length() ) {
00328     if ( pyne::words.find(nat_name[n]) == std::string::npos )
00329       nat_name.erase(n, 1);
00330     else
00331       n++;
00332   }
00333 
00334   // Make sure that the name in non-empty before continuing
00335   if (nat_name.length() == 0)
00336     return nat_name;
00337 
00338   // Make sure that the name doesn't begin with a number.
00339   if ( pyne::digits.find(nat_name[0]) != std::string::npos)
00340     nat_name.insert(0, "_");
00341 
00342   return nat_name;
00343 };

00350 double pyne::slope(double x2, double y2, double x1, double y1) {
00351   // Finds the slope of a line.
00352   return (y2 - y1) / (x2 - x1);
00353 };
00354 
00355 
00356 double pyne::solve_line(double x, double x2, double y2, double x1, double y1) {
00357   return (slope(x2,y2,x1,y1) * (x - x2)) + y2;
00358 };

00371 // File Helpers
00372 
00373 bool pyne::file_exists(std::string strfilename) {
00374   // Thank you intarwebz for this function!
00375   // Sepcifically: http://www.techbytes.ca/techbyte103.html
00376   struct stat stFileInfo;
00377   bool blnReturn;
00378   int intStat;
00379 
00380   // Attempt to get the file attributes
00381   intStat = stat(strfilename.c_str(), &stFileInfo);
00382 
00383   if(intStat == 0) {
00384     // We were able to get the file attributes
00385     // so the file obviously exists.
00386     blnReturn = true;
00387   }
00388   else {
00389     // We were not able to get the file attributes.
00390     // This may mean that we don't have permission to
00391     // access the folder which contains this file. If you
00392     // need to do that level of checking, lookup the
00393     // return values of stat which will give you
00394     // more details on why stat failed.
00395     blnReturn = false;
00396   }
00397 
00398   return(blnReturn);
00399 };

02240 // zzaaam is for numerals only (923350).

02374 /*** Constructs zz to LL dictionary **/
02375 pyne::nucname::zzname_t pyne::nucname::get_zz_name()
02376 {
02377   zzname_t zld;
02378   for (name_zz_iter i = name_zz.begin(); i != name_zz.end(); i++)
02379   {
02380     zld[i->second] = i->first;
02381   }
02382   return zld;
02383 };
02384 pyne::nucname::zzname_t pyne::nucname::zz_name = pyne::nucname::get_zz_name();

02554 /******************************************/
02555 /*** Define useful elemental group sets ***/
02556 /******************************************/
02557 
02558 pyne::nucname::zz_group pyne::nucname::name_to_zz_group(pyne::nucname::name_group eg)
02559 {
02560   zz_group zg;
02561   for (name_group_iter i = eg.begin(); i != eg.end(); i++)
02562     zg.insert(name_zz[*i]);
02563   return zg;
02564 };

02570                                               pyne::nucname::LAN_array+15);

02572   pyne::nucname::name_to_zz_group(pyne::nucname::LAN);

02616 bool pyne::nucname::isnuclide(std::string nuc) {
02617   int n;
02618   try {
02619     n = id(nuc);
02620   }
02621   catch(NotANuclide) {
02622     return false;
02623   }
02624   catch(IndeterminateNuclideForm) {
02625     return false;
02626   };
02627   return isnuclide(n);
02628 };
02629 
02630 bool pyne::nucname::isnuclide(char * nuc) {
02631   return isnuclide(std::string(nuc));
02632 };
02633 
02634 bool pyne::nucname::isnuclide(int nuc) {
02635   int n;
02636   try {
02637     n = id(nuc);
02638   }
02639   catch(NotANuclide) {
02640     return false;
02641   }
02642   catch(IndeterminateNuclideForm) {
02643     return false;
02644   };
02645   if (n <= 10000000)
02646     return false;
02647   int zzz = n / 10000000;
02648   int aaa = (n % 10000000) / 10000;
02649   if (aaa == 0)
02650     return false;  // is element
02651   else if (aaa < zzz)
02652     return false;
02653   return true;
02654 };

02657 
02658 /********************/
02659 /*** id functions ***/
02660 /********************/
02661 int pyne::nucname::id(int nuc) {
02662   if (nuc < 0)
02663     throw NotANuclide(nuc, "");
02664 
02665   int newnuc;
02666   int zzz = nuc / 10000000;     // ZZZ ?
02667   int aaassss = nuc % 10000000; // AAA-SSSS ?
02668   int aaa = aaassss / 10000;    // AAA ?
02669   // Nuclide must already be in id form
02670   if (0 < zzz && zzz <= aaa && aaa <= zzz * 7) {
02671     // Normal nuclide
02672     return nuc;
02673   } else if (aaassss == 0 && 0 < zz_name.count(zzz)) {
02674     // Natural elemental nuclide:  ie for Uranium = 920000000
02675     return nuc;
02676   } else if (nuc < 1000 && 0 < zz_name.count(nuc))
02677     //  Gave Z-number
02678     return nuc * 10000000;
02679 
02680   // Not in id form, try  ZZZAAAM form.
02681   zzz = nuc / 10000;     // ZZZ ?
02682   aaassss = nuc % 10000; // AAA-SSSS ?
02683   aaa = aaassss / 10;    // AAA ?
02684   if (zzz <= aaa && aaa <= zzz * 7) {
02685     // ZZZAAAM nuclide
02686     return (zzz*10000000) + (aaa*10000) + (nuc%10);
02687   } else if (aaa <= zzz && zzz <= aaa * 7 && 0 < zz_name.count(aaa)) {
02688     // Cinder-form (aaazzzm), ie 2350920
02689     return (aaa*10000000) + (zzz*10000) + (nuc%10);
02690   }
02691   //else if (aaassss == 0 && 0 == zz_name.count(nuc/1000) && 0 < zz_name.count(zzz))
02692   else if (aaassss == 0 && 0 < zz_name.count(zzz)) {
02693     // zzaaam form natural nuclide
02694     return zzz * 10000000;
02695   }
02696 
02697   if (nuc >= 1000000){
02698     // From now we assume no metastable info has been given.
02699     throw IndeterminateNuclideForm(nuc, "");
02700   };
02701 
02702   // Nuclide is not in zzaaam form, 
02703   // Try MCNP form, ie zzaaa
02704   // This is the same form as SZA for the 0th state.
02705   zzz = nuc / 1000;
02706   aaa = nuc % 1000; 
02707   if (zzz <= aaa) {
02708     if (aaa - 400 < 0) {
02709       if (nuc == 95242)
02710         return nuc * 10000 + 1;  // special case MCNP Am-242m
02711       else
02712         return nuc * 10000;  // Nuclide in normal MCNP form
02713     } else {
02714       // Nuclide in MCNP metastable form
02715       if (nuc == 95642)
02716         return (95642 - 400)*10000;  // special case MCNP Am-242
02717       nuc = ((nuc - 400) * 10000) + 1;
02718       while (3.0 < (float ((nuc/10000)%1000) / float (nuc/10000000)))
02719         nuc -= 999999;
02720       return nuc;
02721     }
02722   } else if (aaa == 0 && 0 < zz_name.count(zzz)) {
02723     // MCNP form natural nuclide
02724     return zzz * 10000000;
02725   } else if (zzz > 1000) {
02726     // SZA form with a metastable state (sss != 0)
02727     int sss = zzz / 1000;
02728     int newzzz = zzz % 1000;
02729     
02730     return newzzz * 10000000 + aaa * 10000 + sss;
02731   }
02732 
02733   // Not a normal nuclide, might be a 
02734   // Natural elemental nuclide.  
02735   // ie 92 for Uranium = 920000
02736   if (0 < zz_name.count(nuc))
02737     return nuc * 10000000;
02738   throw IndeterminateNuclideForm(nuc, "");
02739 };
02740 
02741 int pyne::nucname::id(char * nuc) {
02742   std::string newnuc (nuc);
02743   return id(newnuc);
02744 };
02745 
02746 int pyne::nucname::id(std::string nuc) {
02747   if (nuc.empty())
02748     throw NotANuclide(nuc, "<empty>");
02749   int newnuc;
02750   std::string elem_name;
02751   
02752   if(nuc.length()>=5) { //nuc must be at least 4 characters or greater if it is in ZZLLAAAM form.
02753     if((pyne::contains_substring(nuc.substr(1, 3), "-")) && (pyne::contains_substring(nuc.substr(4, 5), "-")) ){
02754        // Nuclide most likely in ZZLLAAAM Form, only form that contains two "-"'s.
02755        int dashIndex = nuc.find("-"); 
02756        std::string zz = nuc.substr(0, dashIndex);
02757        std::string ll_aaa_m = nuc.substr(dashIndex+1);
02758        int dash2Index = ll_aaa_m.find("-");
02759        std::string ll = ll_aaa_m.substr(0, dash2Index);
02760        int zz_int;
02761        std::stringstream s_str(zz);
02762        s_str >> zz_int;
02763        if(znum(ll)==zz_int ) {    // Verifying that the LL and ZZ point to the same element as secondary
02764                                   // verification that nuc is in ZZLLAAAM form.
02765          return zzllaaam_to_id(nuc);
02766        }
02767     }
02768   }
02769 
02770   // Get the string into a regular form
02771   std::string nucstr = pyne::to_upper(nuc);
02772   nucstr = pyne::remove_substring(nucstr, "-");
02773   int nuclen = nucstr.length();
02774 
02775   if (pyne::contains_substring(pyne::digits, nucstr.substr(0, 1))) {
02776     if (pyne::contains_substring(pyne::digits, nucstr.substr(nuclen-1, nuclen))) {
02777       // Nuclide must actually be an integer that 
02778       // just happens to be living in string form.
02779       newnuc = pyne::to_int(nucstr);
02780       newnuc = id(newnuc);
02781     } else {
02782       // probably in NIST-like form (242Am)
02783       // Here we know we have both digits and letters
02784       std::string anum_str = pyne::remove_characters(nucstr, pyne::alphabet);
02785       newnuc = pyne::to_int(anum_str) * 10000;
02786 
02787       // Add the Z-number
02788       elem_name = pyne::remove_characters(nucstr, pyne::digits);
02789       elem_name = pyne::capitalize(elem_name);
02790       if (0 < name_zz.count(elem_name))
02791         newnuc = (10000000 * name_zz[elem_name]) + newnuc;
02792       else
02793         throw NotANuclide(nucstr, newnuc);
02794     };
02795   } else if (pyne::contains_substring(pyne::alphabet, nucstr.substr(0, 1))) {
02796     // Nuclide is probably in name form, or some variation therein
02797     std::string anum_str = pyne::remove_characters(nucstr, pyne::alphabet);
02798 
02799     // natural element form, a la 'U' -> 920000000
02800     if (anum_str.empty()) {
02801       elem_name = pyne::capitalize(nucstr);    
02802       if (0 < name_zz.count(elem_name))
02803         return 10000000 * name_zz[elem_name]; 
02804     }
02805 
02806     int anum = pyne::to_int(anum_str);
02807 
02808     // bad form
02809     if (anum < 0)
02810       throw NotANuclide(nucstr, anum); 
02811 
02812     // Figure out if we are meta-stable or not
02813     std::string end_char = pyne::last_char(nucstr);
02814     if (end_char == "M")
02815       newnuc = (10000 * anum) + 1;
02816     else if (pyne::contains_substring(pyne::digits, end_char))
02817       newnuc = (10000 * anum);
02818     else
02819       throw NotANuclide(nucstr, newnuc);
02820 
02821     // Add the Z-number
02822     elem_name = pyne::remove_characters(nucstr.substr(0, nuclen-1), pyne::digits);
02823     elem_name = pyne::capitalize(elem_name);
02824     if (0 < name_zz.count(elem_name))
02825       newnuc = (10000000 * name_zz[elem_name]) + newnuc;
02826     else
02827       throw NotANuclide(nucstr, newnuc);
02828   } else {
02829     // Clearly not a nuclide
02830     throw NotANuclide(nuc, nucstr);
02831   }
02832   return newnuc;  
02833 };
02834

02837 /**********************/
02838 /*** name functions ***/
02839 /**********************/
02840 std::string pyne::nucname::name(int nuc) {
02841   int nucid = id(nuc);
02842   std::string newnuc = "";
02843 
02844   int zzz = nucid / 10000000;
02845   int ssss = nucid % 10000;
02846   int aaassss = nucid % 10000000;
02847   int aaa = aaassss / 10000;
02848 
02849   // Make sure the LL value is correct
02850   if (0 == zz_name.count(zzz))
02851     throw NotANuclide(nuc, nucid);
02852 
02853   // Add LL
02854   newnuc += zz_name[zzz];
02855 
02856   // Add A-number
02857   if (0 < aaa)
02858     newnuc += pyne::to_str(aaa);
02859 
02860   // Add meta-stable flag
02861   if (0 < ssss)
02862     newnuc += "M";
02863 
02864   return newnuc;
02865 };

02870   std::string newnuc (nuc);
02871   return name(newnuc);
02872 }

02999 /*************************/
03000 /*** zzllaaam functions ***/
03001 /*************************/
03002 std::string pyne::nucname::zzllaaam(int nuc) {
03003   int nucid = id(nuc);
03004   std::string newnuc = "";
03005 
03006   int ssss = nucid % 10000;
03007   int aaassss = nucid % 10000000;
03008   int zzz = nucid / 10000000;
03009   int aaa = aaassss / 10000;
03010 
03011   // Make sure the LL value is correct
03012   if (0 == zz_name.count(zzz))
03013     throw NotANuclide(nuc, nucid);
03014   //Adding ZZ
03015   newnuc += pyne::to_str(zzz);
03016   newnuc += "-";
03017   // Add LL
03018   newnuc += zz_name[zzz];
03019   // Add required dash
03020   newnuc += "-";
03021   // Add AAA
03022   if (0 < aaassss)
03023     newnuc += pyne::to_str(aaa);
03024   // Add meta-stable flag
03025   if (0 < ssss)
03026     newnuc += "m";
03027   return newnuc;
03028 };

03032   std::string newnuc (nuc);
03033   return zzllaaam(newnuc);
03034 };

03038   return zzllaaam(id(nuc));
03039 };

03042 int pyne::nucname::zzllaaam_to_id(char * nuc) {
03043   return zzllaaam_to_id(std::string(nuc));
03044 };
03045 
03046 
03047 int pyne::nucname::zzllaaam_to_id(std::string nuc) {
03048   if (nuc.empty())
03049     throw NotANuclide(nuc, "<empty>");
03050   int nucid;
03051   std::string elem_name;
03052 
03053   // Get the string into a regular form
03054   std::string nucstr = pyne::to_upper(nuc);
03055   // Removing first two characters (redundant), for 1 digit nuclides, such
03056   // as 2-He-4, the first slash will be removed, and the second attempt to
03057   // remove the second slash will do nothing.  
03058   nucstr.erase(0,2);
03059   nucstr = pyne::remove_substring(nucstr, "-");
03060   // Does nothing if nuclide is short, otherwise removes the second "-" instance
03061   nucstr = pyne::remove_substring(nucstr, "-");
03062   int nuclen = nucstr.length();
03063 
03064   // Nuclide is probably in name form, or some variation therein
03065   std::string anum_str = pyne::remove_characters(nucstr, pyne::alphabet);
03066 
03067   // natural element form, a la 'U' -> 920000000
03068   if (anum_str.empty() || pyne::contains_substring(nucstr, "NAT")) {
03069     elem_name = pyne::capitalize(pyne::remove_substring(nucstr, "NAT")); 
03070     if (0 < name_zz.count(elem_name))
03071       return 10000000 * name_zz[elem_name]; 
03072   }
03073   int anum = pyne::to_int(anum_str);
03074 
03075   // Figure out if we are meta-stable or not
03076   std::string end_char = pyne::last_char(nucstr);
03077   if (end_char == "M")
03078     nucid = (10000 * anum) + 1;
03079   else if (pyne::contains_substring(pyne::digits, end_char))
03080     nucid = (10000 * anum);
03081   else
03082     throw NotANuclide(nucstr, nucid);
03083 
03084   // Add the Z-number
03085   elem_name = pyne::remove_characters(nucstr.substr(0, nuclen-1), pyne::digits);
03086   elem_name = pyne::capitalize(elem_name);
03087   if (0 < name_zz.count(elem_name))
03088     nucid = (10000000 * name_zz[elem_name]) + nucid;
03089   else
03090     throw NotANuclide(nucstr, nucid);
03091   return nucid;
03092 };
03093 
03094 /**********************/
03095 /*** mcnp functions ***/
03096 /**********************/
03097 int pyne::nucname::mcnp(int nuc) {
03098   nuc = id(nuc);
03099   int ssss = nuc % 10000;
03100   int newnuc = nuc / 10000;
03101 
03102   // special case Am242(m)
03103   if (newnuc == 95242 && ssss < 2)
03104     ssss = (ssss + 1) % 2;
03105 
03106   // Handle the crazy MCNP meta-stable format
03107   if (0 != ssss && ssss < 10) 
03108     newnuc += 300 + (ssss * 100);
03109 
03110   return newnuc;
03111 };

03124 };
03125 
03126 //
03127 // MCNP -> id
03128 //
03129 int pyne::nucname::mcnp_to_id(int nuc) {
03130   int zzz = nuc / 1000;
03131   int aaa = nuc % 1000; 
03132   if (zzz <= aaa) {
03133     if (aaa - 400 < 0) {
03134       if (nuc == 95242)
03135         return nuc * 10000 + 1;  // special case MCNP Am-242m
03136       else
03137         return nuc * 10000;  // Nuclide in normal MCNP form
03138     } else {
03139       // Nuclide in MCNP metastable form
03140       if (nuc == 95642)
03141         return (95642 - 400)*10000;  // special case MCNP Am-242
03142       nuc = ((nuc - 400) * 10000) + 1;
03143       while (3.0 < (float ((nuc/10000)%1000) / float (nuc/10000000)))
03144         nuc -= 999999;
03145       return nuc;
03146     }
03147   } else if (aaa == 0)
03148     // MCNP form natural nuclide
03149     return zzz * 10000000;
03150   throw IndeterminateNuclideForm(nuc, "");
03151 };

03155   return mcnp_to_id(std::string(nuc));
03156 };

03159 int pyne::nucname::mcnp_to_id(std::string nuc) {
03160   return mcnp_to_id(pyne::to_int(nuc));
03161 };

03165 /*** fluka functions ***/
03166 /**********************/
03167 std::string pyne::nucname::fluka(int nuc) {
03168   int x = id(nuc);
03169   if (zz_fluka.count(x) == 0) {
03170     throw NotANuclide(nuc, "fluka name could not be found");
03171   }
03172   return zz_fluka[x];
03173 };

03175 
03176 //
03177 // FLUKA name -> id
03178 //
03179 int pyne::nucname::fluka_to_id(std::string name) {
03180   if (fluka_zz.count(name) == 0) {
03181     throw NotANuclide(-1, "No nuclide: fluka name could not be found");
03182   }
03183   return fluka_zz[name];
03184 }
03185 
03186 int pyne::nucname::fluka_to_id(char * name) {
03187   return fluka_to_id(std::string(name));
03188 }

03190 
03191 /*************************/
03192 /*** serpent functions ***/
03193 /*************************/
03194 std::string pyne::nucname::serpent(int nuc) {
03195   int nucid = id(nuc);
03196   std::string newnuc = "";
03197 
03198   int ssss = nucid % 10000;
03199   int aaassss = nucid % 10000000;
03200   int zzz = nucid / 10000000;
03201   int aaa = aaassss / 10000;
03202 
03203   // Make sure the LL value is correct
03204   if (0 == zz_name.count(zzz))
03205     throw NotANuclide(nuc, nucid);
03206 
03207   // Add LL
03208   std::string llupper = pyne::to_upper(zz_name[zzz]);
03209   std::string lllower = pyne::to_lower(zz_name[zzz]);
03210   newnuc += llupper[0];
03211   for (int l = 1; l < lllower.size(); l++)
03212     newnuc += lllower[l];  
03213 
03214   // Add required dash
03215   newnuc += "-";
03216 
03217   // Add A-number
03218   if (0 < aaassss)
03219     newnuc += pyne::to_str(aaa);
03220   else if (0 == aaassss)
03221     newnuc += "nat";
03222 
03223   // Add meta-stable flag
03224   if (0 < ssss)
03225     newnuc += "m";
03226 
03227   return newnuc;
03228 };
03229 
03230 
03231 std::string pyne::nucname::serpent(char * nuc) {
03232   std::string newnuc (nuc);
03233   return serpent(newnuc);
03234 };
03235 
03236 
03237 std::string pyne::nucname::serpent(std::string nuc) {
03238   return serpent(id(nuc));
03239 };
03240 
03241 //
03242 // Serpent -> id
03243 //
03244 //int pyne::nucname::serpent_to_id(int nuc)
03245 //{
03246 // Should be ZAID
03247 //};
03248 
03249 
03250 int pyne::nucname::serpent_to_id(char * nuc) {
03251   return serpent_to_id(std::string(nuc));
03252 };
03253 
03254 
03255 int pyne::nucname::serpent_to_id(std::string nuc) {
03256   if (nuc.empty())
03257     throw NotANuclide(nuc, "<empty>");
03258   int nucid;
03259   std::string elem_name;
03260 
03261   // Get the string into a regular form
03262   std::string nucstr = pyne::to_upper(nuc);
03263   nucstr = pyne::remove_substring(nucstr, "-");
03264   int nuclen = nucstr.length();
03265 
03266   // Nuclide is probably in name form, or some variation therein
03267   std::string anum_str = pyne::remove_characters(nucstr, pyne::alphabet);
03268 
03269   // natural element form, a la 'U' -> 920000000
03270   if (anum_str.empty() || pyne::contains_substring(nucstr, "NAT")) {
03271     elem_name = pyne::capitalize(pyne::remove_substring(nucstr, "NAT")); 
03272     if (0 < name_zz.count(elem_name))
03273       return 10000000 * name_zz[elem_name]; 
03274   }
03275   int anum = pyne::to_int(anum_str);
03276 
03277   // Figure out if we are meta-stable or not
03278   std::string end_char = pyne::last_char(nucstr);
03279   if (end_char == "M")
03280     nucid = (10000 * anum) + 1;
03281   else if (pyne::contains_substring(pyne::digits, end_char))
03282     nucid = (10000 * anum);
03283   else
03284     throw NotANuclide(nucstr, nucid);
03285 
03286   // Add the Z-number
03287   elem_name = pyne::remove_characters(nucstr.substr(0, nuclen-1), pyne::digits);
03288   elem_name = pyne::capitalize(elem_name);
03289   if (0 < name_zz.count(elem_name))
03290     nucid = (10000000 * name_zz[elem_name]) + nucid;
03291   else
03292     throw NotANuclide(nucstr, nucid);
03293   return nucid;
03294 };
03295

03297 /**********************/
03298 /*** nist functions ***/
03299 /**********************/
03300 std::string pyne::nucname::nist(int nuc) {
03301   int nucid = id(nuc);
03302   std::string newnuc = "";
03303 
03304   int zzz = nucid / 10000000;
03305   int ssss = nucid % 10000;
03306   int aaassss = nucid % 10000000;
03307   int aaa = aaassss / 10000;
03308 
03309   // Make sure the LL value is correct
03310   if (0 == zz_name.count(zzz))
03311     throw NotANuclide(nuc, nucid);
03312 
03313   // Add A-number
03314   if (0 < aaassss)
03315     newnuc += pyne::to_str(aaa);
03316 
03317   // Add name
03318   std::string name_upper = pyne::to_upper(zz_name[zzz]);
03319   std::string name_lower = pyne::to_lower(zz_name[zzz]);
03320   newnuc += name_upper[0];
03321   for (int l = 1; l < name_lower.size(); l++)
03322     newnuc += name_lower[l];  
03323 
03324   // Add meta-stable flag
03325   // No metastable flag for NIST, 
03326   // but could add star, by uncommenting below
03327   //if (0 < mod_10)
03328   //  newnuc += "*";
03329 
03330   return newnuc;
03331 };

03336   return nist(newnuc);

03356 
03357 int pyne::nucname::nist_to_id(std::string nuc) {
03358   if (nuc.empty())
03359     throw NotANuclide(nuc, "<empty>");
03360   int nucid;
03361   nuc = pyne::to_upper(nuc);
03362   std::string elem_name;
03363   int nuclen = nuc.length();
03364 
03365   // Nuclide is probably in name form, or some variation therein
03366   std::string anum_str = pyne::remove_characters(nuc, pyne::alphabet);
03367 
03368   // natural element form, a la 'U' -> 920000000
03369   if (anum_str.empty()) {
03370     elem_name = pyne::capitalize(nuc);
03371     if (0 < name_zz.count(elem_name))
03372       return 10000000 * name_zz[elem_name]; 
03373   }
03374   nucid = pyne::to_int(anum_str) * 10000;
03375 
03376   // Add the Z-number
03377   elem_name = pyne::remove_characters(nuc, pyne::digits);
03378   elem_name = pyne::capitalize(elem_name);
03379   if (0 < name_zz.count(elem_name))
03380     nucid = (10000000 * name_zz[elem_name]) + nucid;
03381   else
03382     throw NotANuclide(nuc, nucid);
03383   return nucid;
03384 };

03387 /************************/
03388 /*** cinder functions ***/
03389 /************************/
03390 int pyne::nucname::cinder(int nuc) {
03391   // cinder nuclides of form aaazzzm
03392   int nucid = id(nuc);
03393   int zzz = nucid / 10000000;
03394   int ssss = nucid % 10000;
03395   int aaassss = nucid % 10000000;
03396   int aaa = aaassss / 10000;
03397   if (10 <= ssss)
03398     ssss = 9;
03399   return (aaa*10000) + (zzz*10) + ssss;
03400 };

03415 //
03416 // Cinder -> Id
03417 //
03418 int pyne::nucname::cinder_to_id(int nuc) {
03419   int ssss = nuc % 10;
03420   int aaazzz = nuc / 10;
03421   int zzz = aaazzz % 1000;
03422   int aaa = aaazzz / 1000;
03423   return (zzz * 10000000) + (aaa * 10000) + ssss;
03424 };

03439 /**********************/
03440 /*** ALARA functions ***/
03441 /**********************/
03442 std::string pyne::nucname::alara(int nuc) {
03443   int nucid = id(nuc);
03444   std::string newnuc = "";
03445   std::string ll = "";
03446 
03447   int zzz = nucid / 10000000;
03448   int ssss = nucid % 10000;
03449   int aaassss = nucid % 10000000;
03450   int aaa = aaassss / 10000;
03451 
03452   // Make sure the LL value is correct
03453   if (0 == zz_name.count(zzz))
03454     throw NotANuclide(nuc, nucid);
03455 
03456   // Add LL, in lower case
03457   ll += zz_name[zzz];
03458 
03459   for(int i = 0; ll[i] != '\0'; i++)
03460     ll[i] = tolower(ll[i]);
03461   newnuc += ll;
03462 
03463   // Add A-number
03464   if (0 < aaassss){
03465     newnuc += ":";
03466     newnuc += pyne::to_str(aaa);
03467   }
03468 
03469   // Note, ALARA input format does not use metastable flag
03470   return newnuc;
03471 };

03570 
03571 void pyne::nucname::_load_state_map(){
03572     for (int i = 0; i < TOTAL_STATE_MAPS; ++i) {
03573        state_id_map[map_nuc_ids[i]] = map_metastable[i];
03574     }
03575 }
03576 
03577 int pyne::nucname::state_id_to_id(int state) {
03578     int zzzaaa = (state / 10000) * 10000;
03579     
03580     std::map<int, int>::iterator nuc_iter, nuc_end;
03581 
03582     nuc_iter = state_id_map.find(state);
03583     nuc_end = state_id_map.end();
03584     if (nuc_iter != nuc_end){ 
03585      int m = (*nuc_iter).second;
03586      return zzzaaa + m;
03587     }        
03588 
03589     if (state_id_map.empty())  {
03590       _load_state_map();
03591       return state_id_to_id(state);
03592     }
03593     throw IndeterminateNuclideForm(state, "no matching metastable state");
03594 }
03595 
03596 
03597 int pyne::nucname::id_to_state_id(int nuc_id) {
03598     int zzzaaa = (nuc_id / 10000) * 10000;
03599     int state = nuc_id % 10000;
03600     
03601     std::map<int, int>::iterator nuc_iter, nuc_end, it;
03602     
03603     nuc_iter = state_id_map.lower_bound(nuc_id);
03604     nuc_end = state_id_map.upper_bound(nuc_id + 10000);
03605     for (it = nuc_iter; it!= nuc_end; ++it){
03606         if (state == it->second) {
03607           return it->first;
03608         }
03609     }
03610     int m = (*nuc_iter).second;
03611     
03612     if (state_id_map.empty())  {
03613       _load_state_map();
03614       return id_to_state_id(nuc_id);
03615     }
03616     throw IndeterminateNuclideForm(state, "no matching state id");
03617 }

05982   altnames["3HE"] = name_id["He3"];
05983   altnames["3He"] = name_id["He3"];
05984   altnames["3he"] = name_id["He3"];
05985   altnames["he-3"] = name_id["He3"];
05986   altnames["HE-3"] = name_id["He3"];
05987   altnames["*"] = name_id["excited"];
05988   altnames["2n"] = name_id["z_2n"];
05989   altnames["2p"] = name_id["z_2p"];
05990   altnames["3h"] = name_id["t"];
05991   altnames["g"] = name_id["it"];
05992   altnames["b-"] = name_id["bminus"];
05993   altnames["b+"] = name_id["bplus"];
05994   altnames["b-n"] = name_id["bminus_n"];
05995   altnames["b-a"] = name_id["bminus_a"];
05996   altnames["b+a"] = name_id["bplus_a"];
05997   altnames["ec+b+"] = name_id["ec_bplus"];
05998   altnames["b+p"] = name_id["bplus_p"];
05999   altnames["b-2n"] = name_id["bminus_2n"];
06000   altnames["b-3n"] = name_id["bminus_3n"];
06001   altnames["b-4n"] = name_id["bminus_4n"];
06002   altnames["b+2p"] = name_id["bplus_2p"];
06003   altnames["ec2p"] = name_id["ec_2p"];
06004   altnames["2b-"] = name_id["decay_2bminus"];
06005   altnames["b-p"] = name_id["bminus_p"];
06006   altnames["14c"] = name_id["decay_14c"];
06007   altnames["b+3p"] = name_id["bplus_3p"];
06008   altnames["2b+"] = name_id["decay_2bplus"];
06009   altnames["2ec"] = name_id["decay_2ec"];
06010   
06011 
06012   // set the nuclide difference mappings, offset_id
06013   // offset_id[incident particle type "n", "p", ...][delta Z num][delta A num][rxid]
06014   // offset_id mapping may be ambiquious so they must come before the id_offsets!
06015   // the following should be sorted by (dz, da, ds)
06016   // neutrons:
06017   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-4, -8))] = name_id["n2a"];
06018   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-4, -7))] = name_id["z_2a"];
06019   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-2, -5))] = name_id["z_2na"];
06020   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-2, -4))] = name_id["na"];
06021   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-2, -4, 1))] = name_id["na_1"];
06022   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-2, -4, 2))] = name_id["na_2"];
06023   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-2, -3))] = name_id["a"];
06024   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-2, -3, 1))] = name_id["a_1"];
06025   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-2, -3, 2))] = name_id["a_2"];
06026   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-2, -2))] = name_id["He3"];
06027   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-2, -2, 1))] = name_id["He3_1"];
06028   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-2, -2, 2))] = name_id["He3_2"];
06029   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-2, -1))] = name_id["z_2p"];
06030   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-2, -1, 1))] = name_id["z_2p_1"];
06031   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-2, -1, 2))] = name_id["z_2p_2"];
06032   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-1, -3))] = name_id["nt"];
06033   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-1, -3, 1))] = name_id["nt_1"];
06034   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-1, -3, 2))] = name_id["nt_2"];
06035   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-1, -2))] = name_id["t"];
06036   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-1, -2, 1))] = name_id["t_1"];
06037   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-1, -2, 2))] = name_id["t_2"];
06038   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-1, -1))] = name_id["d"];
06039   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-1, -1, 1))] = name_id["d_1"];
06040   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-1, -1, 2))] = name_id["d_2"];
06041   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-1, 0))] = name_id["p"];
06042   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-1, 0, 1))] = name_id["p_1"];
06043   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(-1, 0, 2))] = name_id["p_2"];
06044   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, -3))] = name_id["z_4n"];
06045   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, -3, 1))] = name_id["z_4n_1"];
06046   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, -2))] = name_id["z_3n"];
06047   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, -2, 1))] = name_id["z_3n_1"];
06048   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, -2, 2))] = name_id["z_3n_2"];
06049   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, -1))] = name_id["z_2n"];
06050   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, -1, 1))] = name_id["z_2n_1"];
06051   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, -1, 2))] = name_id["z_2n_2"];
06052   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, 0))] = name_id["scattering"];
06053   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, 0, 1))] = name_id["n_1"];
06054   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, 0, 2))] = name_id["n_2"];
06055   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, 1))] = name_id["absorption"];
06056   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, 1, 1))] = name_id["gamma_1"];
06057   offset_id[make_pair("n", offset(0, 1, 2))] = name_id["gamma_2"];
06058   // proton:
06059   offset_id[make_pair("p", offset(0, 0))] = name_id["scattering"];
06060   offset_id[make_pair("p", offset(1, 1))] = name_id["absorption"];
06061   offset_id[make_pair("p", offset(1, 0))] = name_id["n"];
06062   offset_id[make_pair("p", offset(1, -1))] = name_id["z_2n"];
06063   offset_id[make_pair("p", offset(1, -2))] = name_id["z_3n"];
06064   offset_id[make_pair("p", offset(1, -3))] = name_id["z_4n"];
06065   offset_id[make_pair("p", offset(-1, -1))] = name_id["z_2p"];
06066   offset_id[make_pair("p", offset(0, -1))] = name_id["d"];
06067   offset_id[make_pair("p", offset(0, -2))] = name_id["t"];
06068   offset_id[make_pair("p", offset(-1, -2))] = name_id["He3"];
06069   offset_id[make_pair("p", offset(-1, -3))] = name_id["a"];
06070   // deuterium:
06071   offset_id[make_pair("d", offset(0, 0))] = name_id["scattering"];
06072   offset_id[make_pair("d", offset(1, 2))] = name_id["absorption"];
06073   offset_id[make_pair("d", offset(1, 1))] = name_id["n"];
06074   offset_id[make_pair("d", offset(1, 0))] = name_id["z_2n"];
06075   offset_id[make_pair("d", offset(1, -1))] = name_id["z_3n"];
06076   offset_id[make_pair("d", offset(1, -2))] = name_id["z_4n"];
06077   offset_id[make_pair("d", offset(0, 1))] = name_id["p"];
06078   offset_id[make_pair("d", offset(-1, 0))] = name_id["z_2p"];
06079   offset_id[make_pair("d", offset(0, -1))] = name_id["t"];
06080   offset_id[make_pair("d", offset(-1, -1))] = name_id["He3"];
06081   offset_id[make_pair("d", offset(-1, -2))] = name_id["a"];
06082   // tritium:
06083   offset_id[make_pair("t", offset(0, 0))] = name_id["scattering"];
06084   offset_id[make_pair("t", offset(1, 3))] = name_id["absorption"];
06085   offset_id[make_pair("t", offset(1, 2))] = name_id["n"];
06086   offset_id[make_pair("t", offset(1, 1))] = name_id["z_2n"];
06087   offset_id[make_pair("t", offset(1, 0))] = name_id["z_3n"];
06088   offset_id[make_pair("t", offset(1, -1))] = name_id["z_4n"];
06089   offset_id[make_pair("t", offset(0, 2))] = name_id["p"];
06090   offset_id[make_pair("t", offset(-1, 1))] = name_id["z_2p"];
06091   offset_id[make_pair("t", offset(0, 1))] = name_id["d"];
06092   offset_id[make_pair("t", offset(-1, 0))] = name_id["He3"];
06093   offset_id[make_pair("t", offset(-1, -1))] = name_id["a"];
06094   // He3:
06095   offset_id[make_pair("He3", offset(0, 0))] = name_id["scattering"];
06096   offset_id[make_pair("He3", offset(2, 3))] = name_id["absorption"];
06097   offset_id[make_pair("He3", offset(2, 2))] = name_id["n"];
06098   offset_id[make_pair("He3", offset(2, 1))] = name_id["z_2n"];
06099   offset_id[make_pair("He3", offset(2, 0))] = name_id["z_3n"];
06100   offset_id[make_pair("He3", offset(2, -1))] = name_id["z_4n"];
06101   offset_id[make_pair("He3", offset(1, 2))] = name_id["p"];
06102   offset_id[make_pair("He3", offset(0, 1))] = name_id["z_2p"];
06103   offset_id[make_pair("He3", offset(1, 1))] = name_id["d"];
06104   offset_id[make_pair("He3", offset(1, 0))] = name_id["t"];
06105   offset_id[make_pair("He3", offset(0, -1))] = name_id["a"];
06106   // alpha:
06107   offset_id[make_pair("a", offset(0, 0))] = name_id["scattering"];
06108   offset_id[make_pair("a", offset(2, 4))] = name_id["absorption"];
06109   offset_id[make_pair("a", offset(2, 3))] = name_id["n"];
06110   offset_id[make_pair("a", offset(2, 2))] = name_id["z_2n"];
06111   offset_id[make_pair("a", offset(2, 1))] = name_id["z_3n"];
06112   offset_id[make_pair("a", offset(2, 0))] = name_id["z_4n"];
06113   offset_id[make_pair("a", offset(1, 3))] = name_id["p"];
06114   offset_id[make_pair("a", offset(0, 2))] = name_id["z_2p"];
06115   offset_id[make_pair("a", offset(1, 2))] = name_id["d"];
06116   offset_id[make_pair("a", offset(1, 1))] = name_id["t"];
06117   offset_id[make_pair("a", offset(0, 1))] = name_id["He3"];
06118   // gamma:
06119   offset_id[make_pair("gamma", offset(0, -1))] = name_id["n"];
06120   offset_id[make_pair("gamma", offset(0, -2))] = name_id["z_2n"];
06121   offset_id[make_pair("gamma", offset(0, -3))] = name_id["z_3n"];
06122   offset_id[make_pair("gamma", offset(0, -4))] = name_id["z_4n"];
06123   offset_id[make_pair("gamma", offset(-1, -1))] = name_id["p"];
06124   offset_id[make_pair("gamma", offset(-2, -2))] = name_id["z_2p"];
06125   offset_id[make_pair("gamma", offset(-1, -2))] = name_id["d"];
06126   offset_id[make_pair("gamma", offset(-1, -3))] = name_id["t"];
06127   offset_id[make_pair("gamma", offset(-2, -3))] = name_id["He3"];
06128   offset_id[make_pair("gamma", offset(-2, -4))] = name_id["a"];
06129   // decay:
06130   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(0, -1))] = name_id["n"];
06131   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(0, -2))] = name_id["z_2n"];
06132   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(0, -3))] = name_id["z_3n"];
06133   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(0, -4))] = name_id["z_4n"];
06134   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-1, -1))] = name_id["p"];
06135   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-2, -2))] = name_id["z_2p"];
06136   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-1, -2))] = name_id["d"];
06137   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-1, -3))] = name_id["t"];
06138   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-2, -3))] = name_id["He3"];
06139   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-2, -4))] = name_id["a"];
06140   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(1, 0))] = name_id["bminus"];
06141   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-1, 0))] = name_id["bplus"];
06142   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(1, -1))] = name_id["bminus_n"];
06143   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-1, -4))] = name_id["bminus_a"];
06144   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(0, 0))] = name_id["it"];
06145   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-3, -4))] = name_id["bplus_a"];
06146   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-2, -1))] = name_id["bplus_p"];
06147   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(1, -2))] = name_id["bminus_2n"];
06148   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(1, -3))] = name_id["bminus_3n"];
06149   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(1, -4))] = name_id["bminus_4n"];
06150   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-3, -2))] = name_id["bplus_2p"];
06151   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-4, -3))] = name_id["bplus_3p"];
06152   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(2, 0))] = name_id["decay_2bminus"];
06153   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-2, 0))] = name_id["decay_2bplus"];
06154   offset_id[make_pair("decay", offset(-6, -14))] = name_id["decay_14c"];
06155   
06156   // pre-loaded child offsets
06157   std::map<std::pair<std::string, int>, unsigned int>::iterator ioffid;
06158   for (ioffid = offset_id.begin(); ioffid != offset_id.end(); ioffid++) {
06159     id_offset[make_pair(ioffid->first.first, ioffid->second)] = ioffid->first.second;
06160   };
06161   // neutrons:
06162   id_offset[make_pair("n", name_id["nHe3"])] = offset(-2, -3);
06163   id_offset[make_pair("n", name_id["nHe3_1"])] = offset(-2, -3, 2);
06164   id_offset[make_pair("n", name_id["nHe3_2"])] = offset(-2, -3, 2);
06165   id_offset[make_pair("n", name_id["z_3np"])] = offset(-1, -3);
06166   id_offset[make_pair("n", name_id["nd"])] = offset(-1, -2);
06167   id_offset[make_pair("n", name_id["nd_1"])] = offset(-1, -2, 1);
06168   id_offset[make_pair("n", name_id["nd_2"])] = offset(-1, -2, 2);
06169   id_offset[make_pair("n", name_id["np"])] = offset(-1, -1);
06170   id_offset[make_pair("n", name_id["np_1"])] = offset(-1, -1, 1);
06171   id_offset[make_pair("n", name_id["np_2"])] = offset(-1, -1, 2);
06172   id_offset[make_pair("n", name_id["n"])] = offset(0, 0);
06173   id_offset[make_pair("n", name_id["gamma"])] = offset(0, 1);
06174   // decay:
06175   id_offset[make_pair("decay", name_id["bminus_p"])] = offset(0, -1);
06176   id_offset[make_pair("decay", name_id["ec_2p"])] = offset(-3, -2);
06177   id_offset[make_pair("decay", name_id["ec"])] = offset(-1, 0);
06178   id_offset[make_pair("decay", name_id["ec_bplus"])] = offset(-1, 0);
06179   id_offset[make_pair("decay", name_id["ecp"])] = offset(-2, -1);
06180   id_offset[make_pair("decay", name_id["eca"])] = offset(-3, -4);
06181   id_offset[make_pair("decay", name_id["decay_2ec"])] = offset(-2, 0);
06182   return NULL;
06183 };
06184 void * pyne::rxname::_ = pyne::rxname::_fill_maps();

06186 
06187 unsigned int pyne::rxname::hash(std::string s) {
06188   return pyne::rxname::hash(s.c_str());
06189   };
06190 
06191 unsigned int pyne::rxname::hash(const char * s) {
06192   // Modified from http://cboard.cprogramming.com/tech-board/114650-string-hashing-algorithm.html#post853145
06193   // starting from h = 32*2^5 > 1000, rather than 0, to reserve space for MT numbers
06194   int c;
06195   unsigned int h = 32; 
06196   while((c = *s++)) {
06197     h = ((h << 5) + h) ^ c;
06198   }
06199   return h;
06200 };

06204 // *** name functions *****
06205 // ************************
06206 
06207 std::string pyne::rxname::name(char * s) {
06208   return pyne::rxname::name(std::string(s));
06209   };
06210 
06211 std::string pyne::rxname::name(std::string s) {
06212   if (0 < names.count(s))
06213     return s;
06214   if (0 < altnames.count(s))
06215     return id_name[altnames[s]];
06216   // see if id in string form
06217   int i = 0;
06218   int I = s.length();
06219   int found = 0;
06220   while(0 <= found && i < I) {
06221     found = pyne::digits.find(s[i]);
06222     i++;
06223   }
06224   if (0<=found)
06225     return pyne::rxname::name(atoi(s.c_str()));
06226   // dead...
06227   throw NotAReaction(s, "???");
06228 };
06229 
06230 
06231 std::string pyne::rxname::name(int n) {
06232   return pyne::rxname::name((unsigned int) n);
06233 };
06234 
06235 std::string pyne::rxname::name(unsigned int n) {
06236   if (0 < id_name.count(n))
06237     return id_name[n];
06238   if (0 < mt_id.count(n))
06239     return id_name[mt_id[n]];
06240   throw NotAReaction(n, "???");
06241 };
06242 
06243 
06244 std::string pyne::rxname::name(int from_nuc, int to_nuc, std::string z) {
06245   // This assumes nuclides are in id form
06246   std::pair<std::string, int> key = std::make_pair(z, to_nuc - from_nuc);
06247   if (0 == offset_id.count(key))
06248     throw IndeterminateReactionForm("z=" + z + ", " + pyne::to_str(from_nuc) + \
06249                                     ", " + pyne::to_str(to_nuc), "???");
06250   return id_name[offset_id[key]];
06251 };

06253 std::string pyne::rxname::name(std::string from_nuc, int to_nuc, std::string z) {
06254   return pyne::rxname::name(pyne::nucname::id(from_nuc), 
06255                             pyne::nucname::id(to_nuc), z);
06256 };
06257 
06258 std::string pyne::rxname::name(int from_nuc, std::string to_nuc, std::string z) {
06259   return pyne::rxname::name(pyne::nucname::id(from_nuc), 
06260                             pyne::nucname::id(to_nuc), z);
06261 };
06262 
06263 std::string pyne::rxname::name(std::string from_nuc, std::string to_nuc, std::string z) {
06264   return pyne::rxname::name(pyne::nucname::id(from_nuc), 
06265                             pyne::nucname::id(to_nuc), z);

06278   if (0 < id_name.count(x))
06279     return x;
06280   if (0 < mt_id.count(x))
06281     return mt_id[x];
06282   return name_id[pyne::rxname::name(x)];
06283 };

06285 unsigned int pyne::rxname::id(const char * x) {
06286   return name_id[pyne::rxname::name(x)];
06287 };
06288   
06289 unsigned int pyne::rxname::id(std::string x) {
06290   if (0 < names.count(x))
06291     return name_id[x];
06292   if (0 < altnames.count(x))
06293     return altnames[x];
06294   return name_id[pyne::rxname::name(x)];  
06295 };

06298   // This assumes nuclides are in id form

06300   if (0 == offset_id.count(key))
06301     throw IndeterminateReactionForm("z=" + z + ", " + pyne::to_str(from_nuc) + \
06302                                     ", " + pyne::to_str(to_nuc), "???");
06303   return offset_id[key];
06304 };

06314 };

06454 // ***********************
06455 // *** child functions ***
06456 // ***********************
06457 
06458 int pyne::rxname::child(int nuc, unsigned int rx, std::string z) {
06459   // This assumes nuclides are in id form
06460   std::pair<std::string, unsigned int> key = std::make_pair(z, rx);
06461   if (0 == id_offset.count(key))
06462     throw IndeterminateReactionForm("z=" + z + ", rx=" + pyne::to_str(rx), "???");
06463   int to_nuc = nuc + id_offset[key];
06464   if (!pyne::nucname::isnuclide(to_nuc))
06465     throw pyne::nucname::NotANuclide(nuc, to_nuc);
06466   return to_nuc;
06467 };
06468 
06469 int pyne::rxname::child(int nuc, std::string rx, std::string z) {
06470   return child(nuc, id(rx), z);
06471 };
06472 
06473 int pyne::rxname::child(std::string nuc, unsigned int rx, std::string z) {
06474   return child(pyne::nucname::id(nuc), rx, z);
06475 };
06476 
06477 int pyne::rxname::child(std::string nuc, std::string rx, std::string z) {
06478   return child(pyne::nucname::id(nuc), id(rx), z);
06479 };
06480 
06481 
06482 // ************************
06483 // *** parent functions ***
06484 // ************************
06485 
06486 int pyne::rxname::parent(int nuc, unsigned int rx, std::string z) {
06487   // This assumes nuclides are in id form
06488   std::pair<std::string, unsigned int> key = std::make_pair(z, rx);
06489   if (0 == id_offset.count(key))
06490     throw IndeterminateReactionForm("z=" + z + ", rx=" + pyne::to_str(rx), "???");
06491   int from_nuc = nuc - id_offset[key];
06492   if (!pyne::nucname::isnuclide(from_nuc))
06493     throw pyne::nucname::NotANuclide(from_nuc, nuc);
06494   return from_nuc;
06495 };
06496 
06497 int pyne::rxname::parent(int nuc, std::string rx, std::string z) {
06498   return parent(nuc, id(rx), z);
06499 };
06500 
06501 int pyne::rxname::parent(std::string nuc, unsigned int rx, std::string z) {
06502   return parent(pyne::nucname::id(nuc), rx, z);
06503 };
06504 
06505 int pyne::rxname::parent(std::string nuc, std::string rx, std::string z) {
06506   return parent(pyne::nucname::id(nuc), id(rx), z);
06507 };

06552 /*****************************/
06553 /*** atomic_mass Functions ***/
06554 /*****************************/
06555 std::map<int, double> pyne::atomic_mass_map = std::map<int, double>();
06556 
06557 void pyne::_load_atomic_mass_map() {
06558   // Loads the important parts of atomic_wight table into atomic_mass_map
06559 
06560   //Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
06561   if (!pyne::file_exists(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH))
06562     throw pyne::FileNotFound(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
06563 
06564   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str());
06565   if (!ish5)
06566     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
06567 
06568   // Get the HDF5 compound type (table) description
06569   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, sizeof(atomic_mass_data));
06570   H5Tinsert(desc, "nuc",   HOFFSET(atomic_mass_data, nuc),   H5T_NATIVE_INT);
06571   H5Tinsert(desc, "mass",  HOFFSET(atomic_mass_data, mass),  H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
06572   H5Tinsert(desc, "error", HOFFSET(atomic_mass_data, error), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
06573   H5Tinsert(desc, "abund", HOFFSET(atomic_mass_data, abund), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
06574 
06575   // Open the HDF5 file
06576   hid_t nuc_data_h5 = H5Fopen(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY, H5P_DEFAULT);
06577 
06578   // Open the data set
06579   hid_t atomic_mass_set = H5Dopen2(nuc_data_h5, "/atomic_mass", H5P_DEFAULT);
06580   hid_t atomic_mass_space = H5Dget_space(atomic_mass_set);
06581   int atomic_mass_length = H5Sget_simple_extent_npoints(atomic_mass_space);
06582 
06583   // Read in the data
06584   atomic_mass_data * atomic_mass_array = new atomic_mass_data[atomic_mass_length];
06585   H5Dread(atomic_mass_set, desc, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT, atomic_mass_array);
06586 
06587   // close the nuc_data library, before doing anything stupid
06588   H5Dclose(atomic_mass_set);
06589   H5Fclose(nuc_data_h5);
06590 
06591   // Ok now that we have the array of stucts, put it in the map
06592   for(int n = 0; n < atomic_mass_length; n++) {
06593     atomic_mass_map[atomic_mass_array[n].nuc] = atomic_mass_array[n].mass;
06594     natural_abund_map[atomic_mass_array[n].nuc] = atomic_mass_array[n].abund;
06595   }
06596 
06597   delete[] atomic_mass_array;
06598 };
06599 
06600 
06601 double pyne::atomic_mass(int nuc) {
06602   // Find the nuclide's mass in AMU
06603   std::map<int, double>::iterator nuc_iter, nuc_end;
06604 
06605   nuc_iter = atomic_mass_map.find(nuc);
06606   nuc_end = atomic_mass_map.end();
06607 
06608   // First check if we already have the nuc mass in the map
06609   if (nuc_iter != nuc_end)
06610     return (*nuc_iter).second;
06611 
06612   // Next, fill up the map with values from the
06613   // nuc_data.h5, if the map is empty.
06614   if (atomic_mass_map.empty()) {
06615     // Don't fail if we can't load the library
06616     _load_atomic_mass_map();
06617     return atomic_mass(nuc);
06618   }
06619 
06620   double aw;
06621   int nucid = nucname::id(nuc);
06622 
06623   // If in an excited state, return the ground
06624   // state mass...not strictly true, but good guess.
06625   if (0 < nucid%10000) {
06626     aw = atomic_mass((nucid/10000)*10000);
06627     atomic_mass_map[nuc] = aw;
06628     return aw;
06629   };
06630 
06631   // Finally, if none of these work,
06632   // take a best guess based on the
06633   // aaa number.
06634   aw = (double) ((nucid/10000)%1000);
06635   atomic_mass_map[nuc] = aw;
06636   return aw;
06637 };
06638 
06639 
06640 double pyne::atomic_mass(char * nuc) {
06641   int nuc_zz = nucname::id(nuc);
06642   return atomic_mass(nuc_zz);
06643 };
06644 
06645 
06646 double pyne::atomic_mass(std::string nuc) {
06647   int nuc_zz = nucname::id(nuc);
06648   return atomic_mass(nuc_zz);
06649 };

06652 /*******************************/
06653 /*** natural_abund functions ***/
06654 /*******************************/
06655 
06656 std::map<int, double> pyne::natural_abund_map = std::map<int, double>();
06657 
06658 double pyne::natural_abund(int nuc) {
06659   // Find the nuclide's natural abundance
06660   std::map<int, double>::iterator nuc_iter, nuc_end;
06661 
06662   nuc_iter = natural_abund_map.find(nuc);
06663   nuc_end = natural_abund_map.end();
06664 
06665   // First check if we already have the nuc mass in the map
06666   if (nuc_iter != nuc_end)
06667     return (*nuc_iter).second;
06668 
06669   // Next, fill up the map with values from the
06670   // nuc_data.h5, if the map is empty.
06671   if (natural_abund_map.empty()) {
06672     // Don't fail if we can't load the library
06673       _load_atomic_mass_map();
06674       return natural_abund(nuc);
06675   };
06676 
06677   double na;
06678   int nucid = nucname::id(nuc);
06679 
06680   // If in an excited state, return the ground
06681   // state abundance...not strictly true, but good guess.
06682   if (0 < nucid%10000) {
06683     na = natural_abund((nucid/10000)*10000);
06684     atomic_mass_map[nuc] = na;
06685     return na;
06686   };
06687 
06688   // Finally, if none of these work,
06689   // take a best guess based on the
06690   // aaa number.
06691   na = 0.0;
06692   natural_abund_map[nuc] = na;
06693   return na;
06694 };

06710 /*************************/
06711 /*** Q_value Functions ***/
06712 /*************************/
06713 
06714 void pyne::_load_q_val_map() {
06715   // Loads the important parts of q_value table into q_value_map
06716 
06717   //Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
06718   if (!pyne::file_exists(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH))
06719     throw pyne::FileNotFound(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
06720 
06721   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str());
06722   if (!ish5)
06723     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
06724 
06725   // Get the HDF5 compound type (table) description
06726   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, sizeof(q_val_data));
06727   H5Tinsert(desc, "nuc", HOFFSET(q_val_data, nuc),  H5T_NATIVE_INT);
06728   H5Tinsert(desc, "q_val", HOFFSET(q_val_data, q_val), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
06729   H5Tinsert(desc, "gamma_frac", HOFFSET(q_val_data, gamma_frac), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
06730 
06731   // Open the HDF5 file
06732   hid_t nuc_data_h5 = H5Fopen(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY, H5P_DEFAULT);
06733 
06734   // Open the data set
06735   hid_t q_val_set = H5Dopen2(nuc_data_h5, "/decay/q_values", H5P_DEFAULT);
06736   hid_t q_val_space = H5Dget_space(q_val_set);
06737   int q_val_length = H5Sget_simple_extent_npoints(q_val_space);
06738 
06739   // Read in the data
06740   q_val_data * q_val_array = new q_val_data[q_val_length];
06741   H5Dread(q_val_set, desc, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT, q_val_array);
06742 
06743   // close the nuc_data library, before doing anything stupid
06744   H5Dclose(q_val_set);
06745   H5Fclose(nuc_data_h5);
06746 
06747   // Ok now that we have the array of structs, put it in the map
06748   for(int n = 0; n < q_val_length; n++) {
06749     q_val_map[q_val_array[n].nuc] = q_val_array[n].q_val;
06750     gamma_frac_map[q_val_array[n].nuc] = q_val_array[n].gamma_frac;
06751   }
06752 
06753   delete[] q_val_array;
06754 };
06755 
06756 std::map<int, double> pyne::q_val_map = std::map<int, double>();
06757 
06758 double pyne::q_val(int nuc) {
06759   // Find the nuclide's q_val in MeV/fission
06760   std::map<int, double>::iterator nuc_iter, nuc_end;
06761 
06762   nuc_iter = q_val_map.find(nuc);
06763   nuc_end = q_val_map.end();
06764 
06765   // First check if we already have the nuc q_val in the map
06766   if (nuc_iter != nuc_end)
06767     return (*nuc_iter).second;
06768 
06769   // Next, fill up the map with values from the nuc_data.h5 if the map is empty.
06770   if (q_val_map.empty()) {
06771       _load_q_val_map();
06772       return q_val(nuc);
06773   };
06774 
06775   double qv;
06776   int nucid = nucname::id(nuc);
06777   if (nucid != nuc)
06778     return q_val(nucid);
06779 
06780   // If nuclide is not found, return 0
06781   qv = 0.0;
06782   q_val_map[nuc] = qv;
06783   return qv;
06784 };
06785

06787 double pyne::q_val(const char * nuc) {
06788   int nuc_zz = nucname::id(nuc);
06789   return q_val(nuc_zz);
06790 };

06846 /*****************************/
06847 /*** Dose Factor Functions ***/
06848 /*****************************/
06849 /***************************************************************************
06850 This data is from: [Exposure Scenarios and Unit Dose Factors for the Hanford
06851 Immobilized Low-Activity Tank Waste Performance Assessment, ref.
06852 HNF-SD-WM-TI-707 Rev. 1 December 1999] Appendix O of HNF-5636 [DATA PACKAGES
06853 FOR THE HANFORD IMMOBILIZED LOW-ACTIVITY TANK WASTE PERFORMANCE ASSESSMENT:
06854 2001 VERSION]
06855 
06856 Liability Disclaimer: The PyNE Development Team shall not be liable for any
06857 loss or injury resulting from decisions made with this data.
06858 **************************************************************************/
06859 
06860 void pyne::_load_dose_map(std::map<int, dose>& dm, std::string source_path) {
06861   herr_t status;
06862 
06863   //Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
06864   if (!pyne::file_exists(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH))
06865     throw pyne::FileNotFound(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
06866 
06867   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str());
06868   if (!ish5)
06869     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
06870 
06871   // Defining string type for lung model data
06872   hid_t string_type_;
06873   string_type_ = H5Tcopy(H5T_C_S1);
06874   H5Tset_size(string_type_, 1);
06875   H5Tset_strpad(string_type_, H5T_STR_NULLPAD);
06876 
06877   // Get the HDF5 compound type (table) description
06878   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, sizeof(dose));
06879   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "nuc", HOFFSET(dose, nuc), H5T_NATIVE_INT);
06880   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "ext_air_dose", HOFFSET(dose, ext_air_dose), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
06881   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "ratio", HOFFSET(dose, ratio), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
06882   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "ext_soil_dose", HOFFSET(dose, ext_soil_dose), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
06883   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "ingest_dose", HOFFSET(dose, ingest_dose), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
06884   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "fluid_frac", HOFFSET(dose, fluid_frac), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
06885   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "inhale_dose", HOFFSET(dose, inhale_dose), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
06886   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "lung_mod", HOFFSET(dose, lung_mod), string_type_);
06887 
06888   // Open the HDF5 file
06889   hid_t nuc_data_h5 = H5Fopen(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY, H5P_DEFAULT);
06890 
06891   // Convert source_path to proper format for HD5open
06892   const char * c = source_path.c_str();
06893 
06894   // Open the data set
06895   hid_t dose_set = H5Dopen2(nuc_data_h5, c, H5P_DEFAULT);
06896   hid_t dose_space = H5Dget_space(dose_set);
06897   int dose_length = H5Sget_simple_extent_npoints(dose_space);
06898 
06899   // Read in the data
06900   dose * dose_array = new dose[dose_length];
06901   H5Dread(dose_set, desc, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT, dose_array);
06902 
06903   // Put array of structs in the map
06904   for (int n = 0; n < dose_length; n++) {
06905     dm[dose_array[n].nuc] = dose_array[n];
06906   };
06907 
06908   // Close the nuc_data library
06909   H5Dclose(dose_set);
06910   H5Tclose(string_type_);
06911   H5Fclose(nuc_data_h5);
06912 
06913   delete[] dose_array;
06914 };
06915 
06916 ///
06917 /// Functions for Source Location in nuc_data.h5
06918 /// and related Map Pointers
06919 ///
06920 
06921 std::string source_string(int source) {
06922   std::string source_location;
06923   if (source == 1) {
06924     source_location = "/dose_factors/DOE";
06925   } else if (source == 2) {
06926     source_location = "/dose_factors/GENII";
06927   } else {
06928     source_location = "/dose_factors/EPA";
06929   }
06930   return source_location;
06931 };
06932 
06933 std::map<int, pyne::dose>& dose_source_map(int source) {
06934   std::map<int, pyne::dose>* dm;
06935   if (source == 1) {
06936     dm = &pyne::doe_dose_map;
06937   } else if (source == 2) {
06938     dm = &pyne::genii_dose_map;
06939   } else {
06940     dm = &pyne::epa_dose_map;
06941   }
06942   if (dm->empty()) {
06943       std::string source_path = source_string(source);
06944       _load_dose_map(*dm, source_path);
06945   }
06946   return *dm;
06947 };
06948 
06949 std::map<int, pyne::dose> pyne::epa_dose_map;
06950 std::map<int, pyne::dose> pyne::doe_dose_map;
06951 std::map<int, pyne::dose> pyne::genii_dose_map;
06952

07132 
07133 /***********************************/
07134 /*** scattering length functions ***/
07135 /***********************************/
07136 std::map<int, xd_complex_t> pyne::b_coherent_map = std::map<int, xd_complex_t>();
07137 std::map<int, xd_complex_t> pyne::b_incoherent_map = std::map<int, xd_complex_t>();
07138 std::map<int, double> pyne::b_map = std::map<int, double>();
07139 
07140 
07141 void pyne::_load_scattering_lengths() {
07142   // Loads the important parts of atomic_wight table into atomic_mass_map
07143   herr_t status;
07144 
07145   //Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
07146   if (!pyne::file_exists(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH))
07147     throw pyne::FileNotFound(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
07148 
07149   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str());
07150   if (!ish5)
07151     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
07152 
07153   // Get the HDF5 compound type (table) description
07154   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, sizeof(scattering_lengths));
07155   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "nuc", HOFFSET(scattering_lengths, nuc), H5T_NATIVE_INT);
07156   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "b_coherent", HOFFSET(scattering_lengths, b_coherent),
07157                       h5wrap::PYTABLES_COMPLEX128);
07158   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "b_incoherent", HOFFSET(scattering_lengths, b_incoherent),
07159                       h5wrap::PYTABLES_COMPLEX128);
07160   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "xs_coherent", HOFFSET(scattering_lengths, xs_coherent),
07161                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07162   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "xs_incoherent", HOFFSET(scattering_lengths, xs_incoherent),
07163                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07164   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "xs", HOFFSET(scattering_lengths, xs), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07165 
07166   // Open the HDF5 file
07167   hid_t nuc_data_h5 = H5Fopen(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY, H5P_DEFAULT);
07168 
07169   // Open the data set
07170   hid_t scat_len_set = H5Dopen2(nuc_data_h5, "/neutron/scattering_lengths", H5P_DEFAULT);
07171   hid_t scat_len_space = H5Dget_space(scat_len_set);
07172   int scat_len_length = H5Sget_simple_extent_npoints(scat_len_space);
07173 
07174   // Read in the data
07175   scattering_lengths * scat_len_array = new scattering_lengths[scat_len_length];
07176   status = H5Dread(scat_len_set, desc, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT, scat_len_array);
07177 
07178   // close the nuc_data library, before doing anything stupid
07179   status = H5Dclose(scat_len_set);
07180   status = H5Fclose(nuc_data_h5);
07181 
07182   // Ok now that we have the array of stucts, put it in the maps
07183   for(int n = 0; n < scat_len_length; n++) {
07184     b_coherent_map[scat_len_array[n].nuc] = scat_len_array[n].b_coherent;
07185     b_incoherent_map[scat_len_array[n].nuc] = scat_len_array[n].b_incoherent;
07186   };
07187 
07188   delete[] scat_len_array;
07189 };
07190 
07191 
07192 
07193 //
07194 // Coherent functions
07195 //
07196 
07197 
07198 xd_complex_t pyne::b_coherent(int nuc) {
07199   // Find the nuclide's bound scattering length in cm
07200   std::map<int, xd_complex_t>::iterator nuc_iter, nuc_end;
07201 
07202   nuc_iter = b_coherent_map.find(nuc);
07203   nuc_end = b_coherent_map.end();
07204 
07205   // First check if we already have the nuc in the map
07206   if (nuc_iter != nuc_end)
07207     return (*nuc_iter).second;
07208 
07209   // Next, fill up the map with values from the
07210   // nuc_data.h5, if the map is empty.
07211   if (b_coherent_map.empty()) {
07212     _load_scattering_lengths();
07213     return b_coherent(nuc);
07214   };
07215 
07216   xd_complex_t bc;
07217   int nucid = nucname::id(nuc);
07218   int znum = nucname::znum(nucid);
07219   int anum = nucname::anum(nucid);
07220 
07221   // Try to find a nuclide with matching A-number
07222   nuc_iter = b_coherent_map.begin();
07223   while (nuc_iter != nuc_end) {
07224     if (anum == nucname::anum((*nuc_iter).first)) {
07225       bc = (*nuc_iter).second;
07226       b_coherent_map[nuc] = bc;
07227       return bc;
07228     };
07229     nuc_iter++;
07230   };
07231 
07232   // Try to find a nuclide with matching Z-number
07233   nuc_iter = b_coherent_map.begin();
07234   while (nuc_iter != nuc_end) {
07235     if (znum == nucname::znum((*nuc_iter).first)) {
07236       bc = (*nuc_iter).second;
07237       b_coherent_map[nuc] = bc;
07238       return bc;
07239     };
07240     nuc_iter++;
07241   };
07242 
07243   // Finally, if none of these work,
07244   // just return zero...
07245   bc.re = 0.0;
07246   bc.im = 0.0;
07247   b_coherent_map[nuc] = bc;
07248   return bc;
07249 };
07250 
07251 
07252 xd_complex_t pyne::b_coherent(char * nuc) {
07253   int nuc_zz = nucname::id(nuc);
07254   return b_coherent(nuc_zz);
07255 };
07256 
07257 
07258 xd_complex_t pyne::b_coherent(std::string nuc) {
07259   int nuc_zz = nucname::id(nuc);
07260   return b_coherent(nuc_zz);
07261 };
07262 
07263 
07264 
07265 //
07266 // Incoherent functions
07267 //
07268 
07269 
07270 xd_complex_t pyne::b_incoherent(int nuc) {
07271   // Find the nuclide's bound inchoherent scattering length in cm
07272   std::map<int, xd_complex_t>::iterator nuc_iter, nuc_end;
07273 
07274   nuc_iter = b_incoherent_map.find(nuc);
07275   nuc_end = b_incoherent_map.end();
07276 
07277   // First check if we already have the nuc in the map
07278   if (nuc_iter != nuc_end)
07279     return (*nuc_iter).second;
07280 
07281   // Next, fill up the map with values from the
07282   // nuc_data.h5, if the map is empty.
07283   if (b_incoherent_map.empty()) {
07284     _load_scattering_lengths();
07285     return b_incoherent(nuc);
07286   };
07287 
07288   xd_complex_t bi;
07289   int nucid = nucname::id(nuc);
07290   int znum = nucname::znum(nucid);
07291   int anum = nucname::anum(nucid);
07292 
07293   // Try to find a nuclide with matching A-number
07294   nuc_iter = b_incoherent_map.begin();
07295   while (nuc_iter != nuc_end) {
07296     if (anum == nucname::anum((*nuc_iter).first)) {
07297       bi = (*nuc_iter).second;
07298       b_incoherent_map[nuc] = bi;
07299       return bi;
07300     };
07301     nuc_iter++;
07302   };
07303 
07304   // Try to find a nuclide with matching Z-number
07305   nuc_iter = b_incoherent_map.begin();
07306   while (nuc_iter != nuc_end) {
07307     if (znum == nucname::znum((*nuc_iter).first)) {
07308       bi = (*nuc_iter).second;
07309       b_incoherent_map[nuc] = bi;
07310       return bi;
07311     };
07312     nuc_iter++;
07313   };
07314 
07315   // Finally, if none of these work,
07316   // just return zero...
07317   bi.re = 0.0;
07318   bi.im = 0.0;
07319   b_incoherent_map[nuc] = bi;
07320   return bi;
07321 };
07322 
07323 
07324 xd_complex_t pyne::b_incoherent(char * nuc) {
07325   return b_incoherent(nucname::id(nuc));
07326 };

07330   return b_incoherent(nucname::id(nuc));
07331 };

07333 
07334 
07335 //
07336 // b functions
07337 //
07338 
07339 double pyne::b(int nuc) {
07340   // Find the nuclide's bound scattering length in cm
07341   std::map<int, double>::iterator nuc_iter, nuc_end;
07342 
07343   nuc_iter = b_map.find(nuc);
07344   nuc_end = b_map.end();
07345 
07346   // First check if we already have the nuc in the map
07347   if (nuc_iter != nuc_end)
07348     return (*nuc_iter).second;
07349 
07350   // Next, calculate the value from coherent and incoherent lengths
07351   xd_complex_t bc = b_coherent(nuc);
07352   xd_complex_t bi = b_incoherent(nuc);
07353 
07354   double b_val = sqrt(bc.re*bc.re + bc.im*bc.im + bi.re*bi.re + bi.im*bi.im);
07355 
07356   return b_val;
07357 };
07358 
07359 
07360 double pyne::b(char * nuc) {
07361   int nucid = nucname::id(nuc);
07362   return b(nucid);
07363 };
07364 
07365 
07366 double pyne::b(std::string nuc) {
07367   int nucid = nucname::id(nuc);
07368   return b(nucid);
07369 };

07373 //
07374 // Fission Product Yield Data
07375 //
07376 std::map<std::pair<int, int>, double> pyne::wimsdfpy_data = \
07377   std::map<std::pair<int, int>, double>();
07378 
07379 void pyne::_load_wimsdfpy() {
07380   herr_t status;
07381 
07382   //Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
07383   if (!pyne::file_exists(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH))
07384     throw pyne::FileNotFound(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
07385 
07386   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str());
07387   if (!ish5)
07388     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
07389 
07390   // Get the HDF5 compound type (table) description
07391   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, sizeof(wimsdfpy));
07392   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "from_nuc", HOFFSET(wimsdfpy, from_nuc),
07393                      H5T_NATIVE_INT);
07394   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "to_nuc", HOFFSET(wimsdfpy, to_nuc),
07395                      H5T_NATIVE_INT);
07396   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "yields", HOFFSET(wimsdfpy, yields),
07397                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07398 
07399   // Open the HDF5 file
07400   hid_t nuc_data_h5 = H5Fopen(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY,
07401                               H5P_DEFAULT);
07402 
07403   // Open the data set
07404   hid_t wimsdfpy_set = H5Dopen2(nuc_data_h5, "/neutron/wimsd_fission_products",
07405                                 H5P_DEFAULT);
07406   hid_t wimsdfpy_space = H5Dget_space(wimsdfpy_set);
07407   int wimsdfpy_length = H5Sget_simple_extent_npoints(wimsdfpy_space);
07408 
07409   // Read in the data
07410   wimsdfpy * wimsdfpy_array = new wimsdfpy[wimsdfpy_length];
07411   status = H5Dread(wimsdfpy_set, desc, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT, wimsdfpy_array);
07412 
07413   // close the nuc_data library, before doing anything stupid
07414   status = H5Dclose(wimsdfpy_set);
07415   status = H5Fclose(nuc_data_h5);
07416 
07417   // Ok now that we have the array of stucts, put it in the maps
07418   for(int n=0; n < wimsdfpy_length; n++) {
07419     wimsdfpy_data[std::make_pair(wimsdfpy_array[n].from_nuc,
07420       wimsdfpy_array[n].to_nuc)] = wimsdfpy_array[n].yields;
07421   };
07422 
07423   delete[] wimsdfpy_array;
07424 };

07426 
07427 std::map<std::pair<int, int>, pyne::ndsfpysub> pyne::ndsfpy_data = \
07428   std::map<std::pair<int, int>, pyne::ndsfpysub>();
07429 
07430 void pyne::_load_ndsfpy() {
07431   herr_t status;
07432 
07433   //Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
07434   if (!pyne::file_exists(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH))
07435     throw pyne::FileNotFound(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
07436 
07437   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str());
07438   if (!ish5)
07439     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
07440 
07441   // Get the HDF5 compound type (table) description
07442   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, sizeof(ndsfpy));
07443   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "from_nuc", HOFFSET(ndsfpy, from_nuc),
07444                      H5T_NATIVE_INT);
07445   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "to_nuc", HOFFSET(ndsfpy, to_nuc),
07446                      H5T_NATIVE_INT);
07447   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "yield_thermal", HOFFSET(ndsfpy, yield_thermal),
07448                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07449   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "yield_thermal_err", HOFFSET(ndsfpy, yield_thermal_err),
07450                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07451   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "yield_fast", HOFFSET(ndsfpy, yield_fast),
07452                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07453   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "yield_fast_err", HOFFSET(ndsfpy, yield_fast_err),
07454                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07455   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "yield_14MeV", HOFFSET(ndsfpy, yield_14MeV),
07456                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07457   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "yield_14MeV_err", HOFFSET(ndsfpy, yield_14MeV_err),
07458                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07459 
07460   // Open the HDF5 file
07461   hid_t nuc_data_h5 = H5Fopen(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY,
07462                               H5P_DEFAULT);
07463 
07464   // Open the data set
07465   hid_t ndsfpy_set = H5Dopen2(nuc_data_h5, "/neutron/nds_fission_products",
07466                                 H5P_DEFAULT);
07467   hid_t ndsfpy_space = H5Dget_space(ndsfpy_set);
07468   int ndsfpy_length = H5Sget_simple_extent_npoints(ndsfpy_space);
07469 
07470   // Read in the data
07471   ndsfpy * ndsfpy_array = new ndsfpy[ndsfpy_length];
07472   status = H5Dread(ndsfpy_set, desc, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT, ndsfpy_array);
07473 
07474   // close the nuc_data library, before doing anything stupid
07475   status = H5Dclose(ndsfpy_set);
07476   status = H5Fclose(nuc_data_h5);
07477 
07478   ndsfpysub ndsfpysub_temp;
07479 
07480   // Ok now that we have the array of structs, put it in the maps
07481   for(int n=0; n < ndsfpy_length; n++) {
07482     ndsfpysub_temp.yield_thermal = ndsfpy_array[n].yield_thermal;
07483     ndsfpysub_temp.yield_thermal_err = ndsfpy_array[n].yield_thermal_err;
07484     ndsfpysub_temp.yield_fast = ndsfpy_array[n].yield_fast;
07485     ndsfpysub_temp.yield_fast_err = ndsfpy_array[n].yield_fast_err;
07486     ndsfpysub_temp.yield_14MeV = ndsfpy_array[n].yield_14MeV;
07487     ndsfpysub_temp.yield_14MeV_err = ndsfpy_array[n].yield_14MeV_err;
07488     ndsfpy_data[std::make_pair(ndsfpy_array[n].from_nuc,
07489       ndsfpy_array[n].to_nuc)] = ndsfpysub_temp;
07490   };
07491 
07492 
07493 
07494   delete[] ndsfpy_array;
07495 };
07496 
07497 double pyne::fpyield(std::pair<int, int> from_to, int source, bool get_error) {
07498   // Note that this may be expanded eventually to include other
07499   // sources of fission product data.
07500 
07501   // Find the parent/child pair branch ratio as a fraction
07502   if (source == 0) {
07503     std::map<std::pair<int, int>, double>::iterator fpy_iter, fpy_end;
07504     fpy_iter = wimsdfpy_data.find(from_to);
07505     fpy_end = wimsdfpy_data.end();
07506     if (fpy_iter != fpy_end)
07507         //if (get_error == true) return 0;
07508         return (*fpy_iter).second;
07509   } else {
07510     std::map<std::pair<int, int>, ndsfpysub>::iterator fpy_iter, fpy_end;
07511     fpy_iter = ndsfpy_data.find(from_to);
07512     fpy_end = ndsfpy_data.end();
07513     if (fpy_iter != fpy_end) {
07514         switch (source) {
07515           case 1:
07516             if (get_error)
07517                 return (*fpy_iter).second.yield_thermal_err;
07518             return (*fpy_iter).second.yield_thermal;
07519             break;
07520           case 2:
07521             if (get_error)
07522                 return (*fpy_iter).second.yield_fast_err;
07523             return (*fpy_iter).second.yield_fast;
07524             break;
07525           case 3:
07526             if (get_error)
07527                 return (*fpy_iter).second.yield_14MeV_err;
07528             return (*fpy_iter).second.yield_14MeV;
07529             break;
07530         }
07531     }
07532   }
07533 
07534 
07535   // Next, fill up the map with values from the
07536   // nuc_data.h5, if the map is empty.
07537   if ((source == 0 ) && (wimsdfpy_data.empty())) {
07538     _load_wimsdfpy();
07539     return fpyield(from_to, 0, get_error);
07540   }else if (ndsfpy_data.empty()) {
07541     _load_ndsfpy();
07542     return fpyield(from_to, source, get_error);
07543   }
07544 
07545   // Finally, if none of these work,
07546   // assume the value is stable
07547   double fpy = 0.0;
07548   wimsdfpy_data[from_to] = fpy;
07549   return fpy;
07550 };
07551 
07552 double pyne::fpyield(int from_nuc, int to_nuc, int source, bool get_error) {
07553   return fpyield(std::pair<int, int>(nucname::id(from_nuc),
07554                                      nucname::id(to_nuc)), source, get_error);
07555 };
07556 
07557 double pyne::fpyield(char * from_nuc, char * to_nuc, int source, bool get_error) {
07558   return fpyield(std::pair<int, int>(nucname::id(from_nuc),
07559                                      nucname::id(to_nuc)), source, get_error);
07560 };
07561 
07562 double pyne::fpyield(std::string from_nuc, std::string to_nuc, int source,
07563                      bool get_error) {
07564   return fpyield(std::pair<int, int>(nucname::id(from_nuc),
07565                                      nucname::id(to_nuc)), source, get_error);
07566 };
