07573 //
07574 // Data access tools
07575 //
07576 
07577 bool pyne::swapmapcompare::operator()(const std::pair<int, double>& lhs,
07578 const std::pair<int, double>& rhs) const {
07579     return lhs.second<rhs.second || (!(rhs.second<lhs.second) &&
07580       lhs.first<rhs.first);
07581 };
07582 
07583 template<typename T, typename U> std::vector<T> pyne::data_access(
07584 double energy_min, double energy_max, size_t valoffset, std::map<std::pair<int,
07585 double>, U>  &data) {
07586   typename std::map<std::pair<int, double>, U, swapmapcompare>::iterator
07587     nuc_iter, nuc_end, it;
07588   std::map<std::pair<int, double>, U, swapmapcompare> dc(data.begin(),
07589     data.end());
07590   std::vector<T> result;
07591   if (energy_max < energy_min){
07592     double temp = energy_max;
07593     energy_max = energy_min;
07594     energy_min = temp;
07595   }
07596   nuc_iter = dc.lower_bound(std::make_pair(0, energy_min));
07597   nuc_end = dc.upper_bound(std::make_pair(9999999999, energy_max));
07598   T *ret;
07599   // First check if we already have the nuc in the map
07600   for (it = nuc_iter; it!= nuc_end; ++it){
07601     ret = (T *)((char *)&(it->second) + valoffset);
07602     result.push_back(*ret);
07603   }
07604   // Next, fill up the map with values from the
07605   // nuc_data.h5, if the map is empty.
07606   if (data.empty())
07607   {
07608     _load_data<U>();
07609     return data_access<T, U>(energy_min, energy_max, valoffset, data);
07610   };
07611   return result;
07612 };
07613 
07614 template<typename T, typename U> std::vector<T> pyne::data_access(int parent,
07615 double min, double max, size_t valoffset,
07616 std::map<std::pair<int, double>, U>  &data) {
07617   typename std::map<std::pair<int, double>, U>::iterator nuc_iter, nuc_end, it;
07618   std::vector<T> result;
07619   nuc_iter = data.lower_bound(std::make_pair(parent,min));
07620   nuc_end = data.upper_bound(std::make_pair(parent,max));
07621   T *ret;
07622   // First check if we already have the nuc in the map
07623   for (it = nuc_iter; it!= nuc_end; ++it){
07624     ret = (T *)((char *)&(it->second) + valoffset);
07625     result.push_back(*ret);
07626   }
07627   // Next, fill up the map with values from the
07628   // nuc_data.h5, if the map is empty.
07629   if (data.empty())
07630   {
07631     _load_data<U>();
07632     return data_access<T, U>(parent, min, max, valoffset, data);
07633   };
07634   return result;
07635 };
07636 
07637 template<typename T, typename U> T pyne::data_access(std::pair<int, int>
07638 from_to, size_t valoffset, std::map<std::pair<int, int>, U> &data) {
07639   typename std::map<std::pair<int, int>, U>::iterator nuc_iter, nuc_end;
07640 
07641   nuc_iter = data.find(from_to);
07642   nuc_end = data.end();
07643   T *ret;
07644   // First check if we already have the nuc in the map
07645   if (nuc_iter != nuc_end){
07646     ret = (T *)((char *)&(nuc_iter->second) + valoffset);
07647     return *ret;
07648   }
07649   // Next, fill up the map with values from the
07650   // nuc_data.h5, if the map is empty.
07651   if (data.empty())
07652   {
07653     _load_data<U>();
07654     return data_access<T, U>(from_to, valoffset, data);
07655   };
07656   // This is okay for now because we only return ints and doubles
07657   return 0;
07658 }
07659 
07660 template<typename T, typename U> std::vector<T> pyne::data_access(int parent,
07661 size_t valoffset, std::map<std::pair<int, int>, U> &data){
07662   typename std::map<std::pair<int, int>, U>::iterator nuc_iter, nuc_end, it;
07663   std::vector<T> result;
07664   nuc_iter = data.lower_bound(std::make_pair(parent,0));
07665   nuc_end = data.upper_bound(std::make_pair(parent,9999999999));
07666   T *ret;
07667   // First check if we already have the nuc in the map
07668   for (it = nuc_iter; it!= nuc_end; ++it){
07669     ret = (T *)((char *)&(it->second) + valoffset);
07670     result.push_back(*ret);
07671   }
07672   // Next, fill up the map with values from the
07673   // nuc_data.h5, if the map is empty.
07674   if (data.empty())
07675   {
07676     _load_data<U>();
07677     return data_access<T, U>(parent, valoffset, data);
07678   };
07679   return result;
07680 };
07681 
07682 template<typename T, typename U> std::vector<T> pyne::data_access(int parent,
07683 size_t valoffset, std::map<std::pair<int, unsigned int>, U> &data){
07684   typename std::map<std::pair<int, unsigned int>, U>::iterator nuc_iter,
07685    nuc_end, it;
07686   std::vector<T> result;
07687   nuc_iter = data.lower_bound(std::make_pair(parent,0));
07688   nuc_end = data.upper_bound(std::make_pair(parent,UINT_MAX));
07689   T *ret;
07690   // First check if we already have the nuc in the map
07691   for (it = nuc_iter; it!= nuc_end; ++it){
07692     ret = (T *)((char *)&(it->second) + valoffset);
07693     result.push_back(*ret);
07694   }
07695   // Next, fill up the map with values from the
07696   // nuc_data.h5, if the map is empty.
07697   if (data.empty())
07698   {
07699     _load_data<U>();
07700     return data_access<T, U>(parent, valoffset, data);
07701   };
07702   return result;
07703 };
07704 
07705 template<typename U> double pyne::data_access(int nuc,
07706 size_t valoffset, std::map<int, U> &data){
07707   typename std::map<int, U>::iterator nuc_iter,
07708    nuc_end;
07709   nuc_iter = data.find(nuc);
07710   nuc_end = data.end();
07711   // First check if we already have the nuc in the map
07712   if (nuc_iter != nuc_end){
07713     return *(double *)((char *)&(nuc_iter->second) + valoffset);
07714   }
07715   // Next, fill up the map with values from the
07716   // nuc_data.h5, if the map is empty.
07717   if (data.empty())
07718   {
07719     _load_data<U>();
07720     return data_access<U>(nuc, valoffset, data);
07721   };
07722   throw pyne::nucname::NotANuclide(nuc, "");
07723 };

07726 //
07727 // Load atomic data
07728 //
07729 
07730 std::map<int, pyne::atomic> pyne::atomic_data_map;
07731 
07732 template<> void pyne::_load_data<pyne::atomic>() {
07733   // Loads the atomic table into memory
07734   herr_t status;
07735 
07736   //Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
07737   if (!pyne::file_exists(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH))
07738     throw pyne::FileNotFound(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
07739 
07740   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str());
07741   if (!ish5)
07742     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
07743 
07744   // Get the HDF5 compound type (table) description
07745   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, sizeof(atomic));
07746   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "z", HOFFSET(atomic, z),
07747                       H5T_NATIVE_INT);
07748   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "k_shell_fluor", HOFFSET(atomic, k_shell_fluor),
07749                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07750   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "k_shell_fluor_error", HOFFSET(atomic, k_shell_fluor_error),
07751                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07752   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "l_shell_fluor", HOFFSET(atomic, l_shell_fluor),
07753                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07754   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "l_shell_fluor_error", HOFFSET(atomic, l_shell_fluor_error),
07755                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07756   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "prob", HOFFSET(atomic, prob),
07757                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07758   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "k_shell_be", HOFFSET(atomic, k_shell_be),
07759                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07760   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "k_shell_be_err", HOFFSET(atomic, k_shell_be_err),
07761                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07762   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "li_shell_be", HOFFSET(atomic, li_shell_be),
07763                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07764   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "li_shell_be_err", HOFFSET(atomic, li_shell_be_err),
07765                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07766   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "mi_shell_be", HOFFSET(atomic, mi_shell_be),
07767                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07768   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "mi_shell_be_err", HOFFSET(atomic, mi_shell_be_err),
07769                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07770   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "ni_shell_be", HOFFSET(atomic, ni_shell_be),
07771                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07772   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "ni_shell_be_err", HOFFSET(atomic, ni_shell_be_err),
07773                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07774   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "kb_to_ka", HOFFSET(atomic, kb_to_ka),
07775                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07776   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "kb_to_ka_err", HOFFSET(atomic, kb_to_ka_err),
07777                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07778   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "ka2_to_ka1", HOFFSET(atomic, ka2_to_ka1),
07779                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07780   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "ka2_to_ka1_err", HOFFSET(atomic, ka2_to_ka1_err),
07781                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07782   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "l_auger", HOFFSET(atomic, l_auger),
07783                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07784   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "k_auger", HOFFSET(atomic, k_auger),
07785                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07786   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "ka1_x_ray_en", HOFFSET(atomic, ka1_x_ray_en),
07787                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07788   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "ka1_x_ray_en_err", HOFFSET(atomic, ka1_x_ray_en_err),
07789                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07790   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "ka2_x_ray_en", HOFFSET(atomic, ka2_x_ray_en),
07791                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07792   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "ka2_x_ray_en_err", HOFFSET(atomic, ka2_x_ray_en_err),
07793                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07794   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "kb_x_ray_en", HOFFSET(atomic, kb_x_ray_en),
07795                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07796   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "l_x_ray_en", HOFFSET(atomic, l_x_ray_en),
07797                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07798 
07799   // Open the HDF5 file
07800   hid_t nuc_data_h5 = H5Fopen(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY,
07801                               H5P_DEFAULT);
07802   // Open the data set
07803   hid_t atomic_set = H5Dopen2(nuc_data_h5, "/decay/atomic", H5P_DEFAULT);
07804   hid_t atomic_space = H5Dget_space(atomic_set);
07805   int atomic_length = H5Sget_simple_extent_npoints(atomic_space);
07806 
07807   // Read in the data
07808   atomic * atomic_array = new atomic[atomic_length];
07809   status = H5Dread(atomic_set, desc, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT,
07810                    atomic_array);
07811 
07812   // close the nuc_data library, before doing anything stupid
07813   status = H5Dclose(atomic_set);
07814   status = H5Fclose(nuc_data_h5);
07815 
07816   for (int i = 0; i < atomic_length; ++i) {
07817       atomic_data_map[atomic_array[i].z] = atomic_array[i];
07818   }
07819 
07820   delete[] atomic_array;
07821 
07822 }
07823 
07824 std::vector<std::pair<double, double> >
07825   pyne::calculate_xray_data(int z, double k_conv, double l_conv) {
07826   double xk = 0;
07827   double xka = 0;
07828   double xka1 = 0;
07829   double xka2 = 0;
07830   double xkb = 0;
07831   double xl = 0;
07832   if (!isnan(k_conv)) {
07833     xk = data_access<atomic> (z, offsetof(atomic, k_shell_fluor),
07834      atomic_data_map)*k_conv;
07835     xka = xk / (1.0 + data_access<atomic> (z, offsetof(atomic,
07836      kb_to_ka), atomic_data_map));
07837     xka1 = xka / (1.0 + data_access<atomic> (z, offsetof(atomic,
07838      ka2_to_ka1), atomic_data_map));
07839     xka2 = xka - xka1;
07840     xkb = xk - xka;
07841     if (!isnan(l_conv)) {
07842         xl = (l_conv + k_conv*data_access<atomic> (z, offsetof(atomic,
07843      prob), atomic_data_map))*data_access<atomic> (z, offsetof(atomic,
07844      l_shell_fluor), atomic_data_map);
07845     }
07846   } else if (!isnan(l_conv)) {
07847     xl = l_conv*data_access<atomic> (z, offsetof(atomic,
07848      l_shell_fluor), atomic_data_map);
07849   }
07850   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > result;
07851   result.push_back(std::make_pair(data_access<atomic> (z, offsetof(atomic,
07852      ka1_x_ray_en), atomic_data_map),xka1));
07853   result.push_back(std::make_pair(data_access<atomic> (z, offsetof(atomic,
07854      ka2_x_ray_en), atomic_data_map),xka2));
07855   result.push_back(std::make_pair(data_access<atomic> (z, offsetof(atomic,
07856      kb_x_ray_en), atomic_data_map),xkb));
07857   result.push_back(std::make_pair(data_access<atomic> (z, offsetof(atomic,
07858      l_x_ray_en), atomic_data_map),xl));
07859 
07860   return result;
07861 }

07863 
07864 //
07865 // Load level data
07866 //
07867 
07868 std::map<std::pair<int,double>, pyne::level_data> pyne::level_data_lvl_map;
07869 std::map<std::pair<int,unsigned int>,
07870   pyne::level_data> pyne::level_data_rx_map;
07871 
07872 
07873 template<> void pyne::_load_data<pyne::level_data>()
07874 {
07875 
07876   // Loads the level table into memory
07877   herr_t status;
07878 
07879   //Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
07880   if (!pyne::file_exists(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH))
07881     throw pyne::FileNotFound(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
07882 
07883   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str());
07884   if (!ish5)
07885     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
07886 
07887   // Get the HDF5 compound type (table) description
07888   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, sizeof(level_data));
07889   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "nuc_id", HOFFSET(level_data, nuc_id),
07890                       H5T_NATIVE_INT);
07891   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "rx_id", HOFFSET(level_data, rx_id),
07892                      H5T_NATIVE_UINT);
07893   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "half_life", HOFFSET(level_data, half_life),
07894                       H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07895   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "level", HOFFSET(level_data, level),
07896                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07897   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "branch_ratio", HOFFSET(level_data, branch_ratio),
07898                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
07899   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "metastable", HOFFSET(level_data, metastable),
07900                       H5T_NATIVE_INT);
07901   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "special", HOFFSET(level_data, special),
07902                       H5T_C_S1);
07903   // Open the HDF5 file
07904   hid_t nuc_data_h5 = H5Fopen(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY,
07905                               H5P_DEFAULT);
07906   // Open the data set
07907   hid_t level_set = H5Dopen2(nuc_data_h5, "/decay/level_list", H5P_DEFAULT);
07908   hid_t level_space = H5Dget_space(level_set);
07909   int level_length = H5Sget_simple_extent_npoints(level_space);
07910 
07911   // Read in the data
07912   level_data * level_array = new level_data[level_length];
07913   status = H5Dread(level_set, desc, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT,
07914                    level_array);
07915 
07916   // close the nuc_data library, before doing anything stupid
07917   status = H5Dclose(level_set);
07918   status = H5Fclose(nuc_data_h5);
07919 
07920   for (int i = 0; i < level_length; ++i) {
07921     if (level_array[i].rx_id == 0)
07922       level_data_lvl_map[std::make_pair(level_array[i].nuc_id,
07923                                         level_array[i].level)] = level_array[i];
07924     else
07925       level_data_rx_map[std::make_pair(level_array[i].nuc_id,
07926                                        level_array[i].rx_id)] = level_array[i];
07927   }
07928 
07929   delete[] level_array;
07930 }
07931 
07932 //
07933 // level id
07934 //
07935 int pyne::id_from_level(int nuc, double level, std::string special) {
07936   int nostate = (nuc / 10000) * 10000;
07937   if (level_data_lvl_map.empty()) {
07938     _load_data<level_data>();
07939   }
07940 
07941   std::map<std::pair<int, double>, level_data>::iterator nuc_lower, nuc_upper;
07942 
07943   nuc_lower = level_data_lvl_map.lower_bound(std::make_pair(nostate, 0.0));
07944   nuc_upper = level_data_lvl_map.upper_bound(std::make_pair(nostate+9999,
07945                                              DBL_MAX));
07946   double min = DBL_MAX;
07947   //by default return input nuc_id with level stripped
07948   int ret_id = nuc;
07949   for (std::map<std::pair<int, double>, level_data>::iterator it=nuc_lower;
07950   it!=nuc_upper;
07951        ++it) {
07952     if ((abs(level - it->second.level) < min) &&
07953     ((char)it->second.special == special.c_str()[0]) &&
07954     !isnan(it->second.level)) {
07955       min = abs(level - it->second.level);
07956       ret_id = it->second.nuc_id;
07957     }
07958   }
07959   if (min > 1.0)
07960     ret_id = nuc;
07961   return ret_id;
07962 }
07963 
07964 int pyne::id_from_level(int nuc, double level){
07965     return id_from_level(nuc, level, " ");
07966 }
07967 //
07968 // Metastable id data
07969 //
07970 
07971 int pyne::metastable_id(int nuc, int m) {
07972   int nostate = (nuc / 10000) * 10000;
07973   if (m==0) return nostate;
07974   if (level_data_lvl_map.empty()) {
07975     _load_data<level_data>();
07976   }
07977 
07978   std::map<std::pair<int, double>, level_data>::iterator nuc_lower, nuc_upper;
07979 
07980   nuc_lower = level_data_lvl_map.lower_bound(std::make_pair(nostate, 0.0));
07981   nuc_upper = level_data_lvl_map.upper_bound(std::make_pair(nostate+9999,
07982   DBL_MAX));
07983   for (std::map<std::pair<int, double>, level_data>::iterator it=nuc_lower;
07984   it!=nuc_upper; ++it) {
07985     if (it->second.metastable == m)
07986         return it->second.nuc_id;
07987   }
07988 
07989   return nuc;
07990 }
07991 
07992 int pyne::metastable_id(int nuc) {
07993   return metastable_id(nuc, 1);
07994 }
07995 
07996 //
07997 // Decay children data
07998 //
07999 
08000 
08001 std::set<int> pyne::decay_children(int nuc) {
08002   // make sure spontaneous fission data is loaded
08003   if (wimsdfpy_data.empty())
08004     _load_wimsdfpy();
08005 
08006   std::vector<unsigned int> part = data_access<unsigned int, level_data>(nuc,
08007     offsetof(level_data, rx_id), level_data_rx_map);
08008   std::vector<unsigned int>::iterator it = part.begin();
08009   std::set<int> result;
08010   for (; it != part.end(); ++it) {
08011     switch (*it) {
08012       case 36125: {
08013         // internal conversion, rx == 'it'
08014         result.insert((nuc /10000) * 10000);
08015         break;
08016       }
08017       case 36565: {
08018         // spontaneous fission, rx == 'sf'
08019         std::map<std::pair<int, int>, double>::iterator sf = wimsdfpy_data.begin();
08020         for (; sf != wimsdfpy_data.end(); ++sf)
08021           if (sf->first.first == nuc)
08022             result.insert(sf->first.second);
08023         break;
08024       }
08025       default: {
08026         result.insert((rxname::child(nuc, *it, "decay") /10000) * 10000);
08027       }
08028     }
08029   }
08030   return result;
08031 }
08032 
08033 std::set<int> pyne::decay_children(char * nuc)
08034 {
08035   return decay_children(nucname::id(nuc));
08036 };
08037 
08038 std::set<int> pyne::decay_children(std::string nuc)
08039 {
08040   return decay_children(nucname::id(nuc));
08041 };

08048 {

08050   DBL_MAX, offsetof(level_data, level), level_data_lvl_map);
08051   if (result.size() == 1)
08052     return result[0]/1000.0;
08053   return 0.0;
08054 }

08068 //
08069 // Decay constant data
08070 //
08071 
08072 double pyne::decay_const(int nuc)
08073 {
08074     std::vector<double> result = data_access<double, level_data>(nuc, 0.0,
08075       DBL_MAX, offsetof(level_data, half_life), level_data_lvl_map);
08076     if (result.size() == 1) {
08077         return log(2.0)/result[0];
08078     }
08079     return 0.0;
08080 }

08118 
08119 //
08120 // Branch ratio data
08121 //
08122 double pyne::branch_ratio(std::pair<int, int> from_to) {
08123   using std::vector;
08124   using pyne::nucname::groundstate;
08125   // make sure spontaneous fission data is loaded
08126   if (wimsdfpy_data.empty())
08127     _load_wimsdfpy();
08128 
08129   vector<unsigned int> part1 = \
08130     data_access<unsigned int, level_data>(from_to.first, offsetof(level_data, rx_id),
08131                                           level_data_rx_map);
08132   vector<double> part2 = \
08133     data_access<double, level_data>(from_to.first, offsetof(level_data, branch_ratio),
08134                                     level_data_rx_map);
08135   double result = 0.0;
08136   if ((from_to.first == from_to.second) && (decay_const(from_to.first) == 0.0))
08137     return 1.0;
08138   for (vector<unsigned int>::size_type i = 0; i < part1.size(); ++i) {
08139     if ((part1[i] == 36125) &&
08140         (groundstate(from_to.first) == groundstate(from_to.second)) &&
08141         (from_to.second % 10000 == 0)) {
08142       // internal conversion, rx == 'it'
08143       result = 1.0;
08144       break;
08145     } else if (part1[i] == 36565) {
08146       // spontaneous fission, rx == 'sf'
08147       result += part2[i] * 0.01 * wimsdfpy_data[from_to];
08148     } else if ((part1[i] != 0) && (groundstate(rxname::child(from_to.first, 
08149                                    part1[i], "decay")) == from_to.second)) {
08150       result += part2[i] * 0.01;
08151     }
08152   }
08153   return result;
08154 }
08155 
08156 double pyne::branch_ratio(int from_nuc, int to_nuc) {
08157   return branch_ratio(std::pair<int, int>(nucname::id(from_nuc),
08158                                           nucname::id(to_nuc)));
08159 };
08160 
08161 double pyne::branch_ratio(char * from_nuc, char * to_nuc) {
08162   return branch_ratio(std::pair<int, int>(nucname::id(from_nuc),
08163                                           nucname::id(to_nuc)));
08164 };
08165 
08166 double pyne::branch_ratio(std::string from_nuc, std::string to_nuc) {
08167   return branch_ratio(std::pair<int, int>(nucname::id(from_nuc),
08168                                           nucname::id(to_nuc)));
08169 };
08170 
08171 std::map<std::pair<int, int>, pyne::decay> pyne::decay_data = \
08172   std::map<std::pair<int, int>, pyne::decay>();
08173 
08174 template<> void pyne::_load_data<pyne::decay>() {
08175 
08176   // Loads the decay table into memory
08177   herr_t status;
08178 
08179   //Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
08180   if (!pyne::file_exists(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH))
08181     throw pyne::FileNotFound(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
08182 
08183   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str());
08184   if (!ish5)
08185     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
08186 
08187   // Get the HDF5 compound type (table) description
08188   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, sizeof(decay));
08189   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "parent", HOFFSET(decay, parent),
08190                      H5T_NATIVE_INT);
08191   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "child", HOFFSET(decay, child),
08192                      H5T_NATIVE_INT);
08193   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "decay", HOFFSET(decay, decay),
08194                      H5T_NATIVE_UINT);
08195   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "half_life", HOFFSET(decay, half_life),
08196                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08197   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "half_life_error", HOFFSET(decay,
08198                      half_life_error), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08199   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "branch_ratio", HOFFSET(decay, branch_ratio),
08200                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08201   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "photon_branch_ratio", HOFFSET(decay,
08202                      photon_branch_ratio), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08203   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "photon_branch_ratio_err", HOFFSET(decay,
08204                      photon_branch_ratio_error), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08205   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "beta_branch_ratio", HOFFSET(decay,
08206                      beta_branch_ratio), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08207   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "beta_branch_ratio_err", HOFFSET(decay,
08208                      beta_branch_ratio_error), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08209 
08210   // Open the HDF5 file
08211   hid_t nuc_data_h5 = H5Fopen(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY,
08212                               H5P_DEFAULT);
08213 
08214   // Open the data set
08215   hid_t decay_set = H5Dopen2(nuc_data_h5, "/decay/decays", H5P_DEFAULT);
08216   hid_t decay_space = H5Dget_space(decay_set);
08217   int decay_length = H5Sget_simple_extent_npoints(decay_space);
08218 
08219   // Read in the data
08220   decay * decay_array = new decay[decay_length];
08221   status = H5Dread(decay_set, desc, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT,
08222                    decay_array);
08223 
08224   // close the nuc_data library, before doing anything stupid
08225   status = H5Dclose(decay_set);
08226   status = H5Fclose(nuc_data_h5);
08227 
08228   for (int i = 0; i < decay_length; ++i) {
08229     decay_data[std::make_pair(decay_array[i].parent, decay_array[i].child)] = \
08230       decay_array[i];
08231   }
08232   delete[] decay_array;
08233 }

08239   return result;
08240 }

08312 std::map<std::pair<int, double>, pyne::gamma> pyne::gamma_data;
08313 
08314 template<> void pyne::_load_data<pyne::gamma>() {
08315 
08316   // Loads the gamma table into memory
08317   herr_t status;
08318 
08319   //Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
08320   if (!pyne::file_exists(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH))
08321     throw pyne::FileNotFound(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
08322 
08323   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str());
08324   if (!ish5)
08325     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
08326 
08327   // Get the HDF5 compound type (table) description
08328   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, sizeof(gamma));
08329   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "from_nuc", HOFFSET(gamma, from_nuc),
08330                      H5T_NATIVE_INT);
08331   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "to_nuc", HOFFSET(gamma, to_nuc),
08332                      H5T_NATIVE_INT);
08333   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "parent_nuc", HOFFSET(gamma, parent_nuc),
08334                      H5T_NATIVE_INT);
08335   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "energy", HOFFSET(gamma, energy),
08336                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08337   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "energy_err", HOFFSET(gamma, energy_err),
08338                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08339   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "photon_intensity", HOFFSET(gamma,
08340                      photon_intensity), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08341   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "photon_intensity_err", HOFFSET(gamma,
08342                      photon_intensity_err), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08343   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "conv_intensity", HOFFSET(gamma,
08344                      conv_intensity), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08345   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "conv_intensity_err", HOFFSET(gamma,
08346                      conv_intensity_err), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08347   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "total_intensity", HOFFSET(gamma,
08348                      total_intensity), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08349   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "total_intensity_err", HOFFSET(gamma,
08350                      total_intensity_err), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08351   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "k_conv_e", HOFFSET(gamma, k_conv_e),
08352                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08353   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "l_conv_e", HOFFSET(gamma, l_conv_e),
08354                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08355   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "m_conv_e", HOFFSET(gamma, m_conv_e),
08356                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08357 
08358 
08359   // Open the HDF5 file
08360   hid_t nuc_data_h5 = H5Fopen(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY,
08361                               H5P_DEFAULT);
08362 
08363   // Open the data set
08364   hid_t gamma_set = H5Dopen2(nuc_data_h5, "/decay/gammas", H5P_DEFAULT);
08365   hid_t gamma_space = H5Dget_space(gamma_set);
08366   int gamma_length = H5Sget_simple_extent_npoints(gamma_space);
08367 
08368   // Read in the data
08369   gamma * gamma_array = new gamma[gamma_length];
08370   status = H5Dread(gamma_set, desc, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT,
08371                    gamma_array);
08372 
08373   // close the nuc_data library, before doing anything stupid
08374   status = H5Dclose(gamma_set);
08375   status = H5Fclose(nuc_data_h5);
08376 
08377   for (int i = 0; i < gamma_length; ++i) {
08378     gamma_data[std::make_pair(gamma_array[i].parent_nuc,
08379       gamma_array[i].energy)] = gamma_array[i];
08380   }
08381   delete[] gamma_array;
08382 }

08474   return data_access<int, gamma>(energy+error, energy-error,
08475     offsetof(gamma, parent_nuc), gamma_data);
08476 };
08477 
08478 
08479 std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > pyne::gamma_xrays(int parent) {
08480   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > result;
08481   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > temp;
08482   std::vector<double> k_list = data_access<double, gamma>(parent, 0.0, DBL_MAX,
08483     offsetof(gamma, k_conv_e), gamma_data);
08484   std::vector<double> l_list = data_access<double, gamma>(parent, 0.0, DBL_MAX,
08485     offsetof(gamma, l_conv_e), gamma_data);
08486   std::vector<int> children = data_access<int, gamma>(parent, 0.0,
08487     DBL_MAX, offsetof(gamma, from_nuc), gamma_data);
08488   std::vector<int> decay_children = decay_data_children(parent);
08489   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > decay_br =
08490     decay_photon_branch_ratios(parent);
08491   for(int i = 0; i < k_list.size(); ++i){
08492     for (int j = 0; j < decay_children.size(); ++j) {
08493       if (nucname::zzzaaa(children[i]) == nucname::zzzaaa(decay_children[j])) {
08494         temp = calculate_xray_data(nucname::znum(children[i]),
08495           k_list[i]*decay_br[j].first, l_list[i]*decay_br[j].first);
08496         for (int k = 0; k < temp.size(); ++k) {
08497           if (!isnan(temp[k].second) && !isnan(temp[k].first)) {
08498             int found = 0;
08499             for (int l = 0; l < result.size(); ++l) {
08500               if (temp[k].first == result[l].first) {
08501                 result[l].second = result[l].second + temp[k].second;
08502                 found = 1;
08503                 break;
08504               }
08505             }
08506             if (found == 0) {
08507               result.push_back(temp[k]);
08508             }
08509           }
08510         }
08511         break;
08512       }
08513     }
08514   }
08515   return result;
08516 };
08517 
08518 std::map<std::pair<int, double>, pyne::alpha> pyne::alpha_data;
08519 
08520 template<> void pyne::_load_data<pyne::alpha>() {
08521 
08522   // Loads the alpha table into memory
08523   herr_t status;
08524 
08525   //Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
08526   if (!pyne::file_exists(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH))
08527     throw pyne::FileNotFound(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
08528 
08529   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str());
08530   if (!ish5)
08531     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
08532 
08533   // Get the HDF5 compound type (table) description
08534   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, sizeof(alpha));
08535   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "from_nuc", HOFFSET(alpha, from_nuc),
08536                      H5T_NATIVE_INT);
08537   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "to_nuc", HOFFSET(alpha, to_nuc),
08538                      H5T_NATIVE_INT);
08539   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "energy", HOFFSET(alpha, energy),
08540                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08541   status = H5Tinsert(desc, "intensity", HOFFSET(alpha, intensity),
08542                      H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
08543 
08544 
08545   // Open the HDF5 file
08546   hid_t nuc_data_h5 = H5Fopen(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY,
08547                               H5P_DEFAULT);
08548 
08549   // Open the data set
08550   hid_t alpha_set = H5Dopen2(nuc_data_h5, "/decay/alphas", H5P_DEFAULT);
08551   hid_t alpha_space = H5Dget_space(alpha_set);
08552   int alpha_length = H5Sget_simple_extent_npoints(alpha_space);
08553 
08554   // Read in the data
08555   alpha * alpha_array = new alpha[alpha_length];
08556   status = H5Dread(alpha_set, desc, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT,
08557                    alpha_array);
08558 
08559   // close the nuc_data library, before doing anything stupid
08560   status = H5Dclose(alpha_set);
08561   status = H5Fclose(nuc_data_h5);
08562 
08563   for (int i = 0; i < alpha_length; ++i) {
08564     alpha_data[std::make_pair(alpha_array[i].from_nuc, alpha_array[i].energy)]
08565     = alpha_array[i];
08566   }
08567   delete[] alpha_array;
08568 }

08772 
08773 std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > pyne::ecbp_xrays(int parent) {
08774   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > result;
08775   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > temp;
08776   std::vector<double> k_list = data_access<double, ecbp>(parent, 0.0, DBL_MAX,
08777     offsetof(ecbp, k_conv_e), ecbp_data);
08778   std::vector<double> l_list = data_access<double, ecbp>(parent, 0.0, DBL_MAX,
08779     offsetof(ecbp, l_conv_e), ecbp_data);
08780   std::vector<int> children = data_access<int, ecbp>(parent, 0.0, DBL_MAX,
08781     offsetof(ecbp, to_nuc), ecbp_data);
08782   std::vector<int> decay_children = decay_data_children(parent);
08783   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > decay_br =
08784     decay_beta_branch_ratios(parent);
08785   for(int i = 0; i < k_list.size(); ++i){
08786     for (int j = 0; j < decay_children.size(); ++j) {
08787       if (nucname::zzzaaa(children[i]) == nucname::zzzaaa(decay_children[j])) {
08788         temp = calculate_xray_data(nucname::znum(children[i]),
08789           k_list[i]*decay_br[j].first, l_list[i]*decay_br[j].first);
08790         for (int k = 0; k < temp.size(); ++k) {
08791           if (!isnan(temp[k].second) && !isnan(temp[k].first)) {
08792             int found = 0;
08793             for (int l = 0; l < result.size(); ++l) {
08794               if (temp[k].first == result[l].first) {
08795                 result[l].second = result[l].second + temp[k].second;
08796                 found = 1;
08797                 break;
08798               }
08799             }
08800             if (found == 0) {
08801               result.push_back(temp[k]);
08802             }
08803           }
08804         }
08805         break;
08806       }
08807     }
08808   }
08809   return result;
08810 };

08812 ///////////////////////////
08813 /// Combined decay data ///
08814 ///////////////////////////
08815 
08816 std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > pyne::gammas(int parent_state_id) {
08817   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > result;
08818   double decay_c = decay_const(parent_state_id);
08819   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > energies = gamma_energy(parent_state_id);
08820   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > intensities =
08821     gamma_photon_intensity(parent_state_id);
08822   std::vector<std::pair<int, int> > children = gamma_from_to(parent_state_id);
08823   std::vector<int> decay_children = decay_data_children(parent_state_id);
08824   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > decay_br =
08825     decay_photon_branch_ratios(parent_state_id);
08826   for (int i = 0; i < children.size(); ++i) {
08827     for (int j = 0; j < decay_children.size(); ++j) {
08828       if (nucname::zzzaaa(children[i].first) == nucname::zzzaaa(decay_children[j])) {
08829         result.push_back(std::make_pair(energies[i].first,
08830           decay_c*intensities[i].first*decay_br[j].first));
08831       }
08832     }
08833   }
08834   return result;
08835 }
08836 
08837 std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > pyne::alphas(int parent_state_id) {
08838   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > result;
08839   double decay_c = decay_const(parent_state_id);
08840   std::vector<double> energies = alpha_energy(parent_state_id);
08841   std::vector<double> intensities = alpha_intensity(parent_state_id);
08842   std::vector<int> children = alpha_child(parent_state_id);
08843   std::vector<int> decay_children = decay_data_children(parent_state_id);
08844   std::vector<double> decay_br = decay_branch_ratios(parent_state_id);
08845   for (int i = 0; i < children.size(); ++i) {
08846     for (int j = 0; j < decay_children.size(); ++j) {
08847       if (nucname::zzzaaa(children[i]) == nucname::zzzaaa(decay_children[j])) {
08848         result.push_back(std::make_pair(energies[i],
08849           decay_c*decay_br[j]*intensities[i]));
08850       }
08851     }
08852   }
08853   return result;
08854 }
08855 
08856 std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > pyne::betas(int parent_state_id) {
08857   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > result;
08858   double decay_c = decay_const(parent_state_id);
08859   std::vector<double> energies = beta_average_energy(parent_state_id);
08860   std::vector<double> intensities = beta_intensity(parent_state_id);
08861   std::vector<int> children = beta_child(parent_state_id);
08862   std::vector<int> decay_children = decay_data_children(parent_state_id);
08863   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > decay_br =
08864     decay_beta_branch_ratios(parent_state_id);
08865   for (int i = 0; i < children.size(); ++i) {
08866     for (int j = 0; j < decay_children.size(); ++j) {
08867       if (nucname::zzzaaa(children[i]) == nucname::zzzaaa(decay_children[j])) {
08868         result.push_back(std::make_pair(energies[i],
08869           decay_c*decay_br[j].first*intensities[i]));
08870         break;
08871       }
08872     }
08873   }
08874   return result;
08875 }
08876 
08877 std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > pyne::xrays(int parent) {
08878   double decay_c = decay_const(parent);
08879   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > result;
08880   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > temp;
08881   std::vector<double> k_list = data_access<double, ecbp>(parent, 0.0, DBL_MAX,
08882     offsetof(ecbp, k_conv_e), ecbp_data);
08883   std::vector<double> l_list = data_access<double, ecbp>(parent, 0.0, DBL_MAX,
08884     offsetof(ecbp, l_conv_e), ecbp_data);
08885   std::vector<int> children = data_access<int, ecbp>(parent, 0.0, DBL_MAX,
08886                      offsetof(ecbp, to_nuc), ecbp_data);
08887   std::vector<int> decay_children = decay_data_children(parent);
08888   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > decay_br =
08889     decay_beta_branch_ratios(parent);
08890   for(int i = 0; i < k_list.size(); ++i){
08891     for (int j = 0; j < decay_children.size(); ++j) {
08892       if (nucname::zzzaaa(children[i]) == nucname::zzzaaa(decay_children[j])) {
08893         temp = calculate_xray_data(nucname::znum(children[i]),
08894           k_list[i]*decay_br[j].first, l_list[i]*decay_br[j].first);
08895         for (int k = 0; k < temp.size(); ++k) {
08896           if (!isnan(temp[k].second) && !isnan(temp[k].first)) {
08897             int found = 0;
08898             for (int l = 0; l < result.size(); ++l) {
08899               if (temp[k].first == result[l].first) {
08900                 result[l].second = result[l].second + temp[k].second;
08901                 found = 1;
08902                 break;
08903               }
08904             }
08905             if (found == 0) {
08906               result.push_back(temp[k]);
08907             }
08908           }
08909         }
08910         break;
08911       }
08912     }
08913   }
08914   std::vector<double> gk_list = data_access<double, gamma>(parent, 0.0, DBL_MAX,
08915     offsetof(gamma, k_conv_e), gamma_data);
08916   std::vector<double> gl_list = data_access<double, gamma>(parent, 0.0, DBL_MAX,
08917     offsetof(gamma, l_conv_e), gamma_data);
08918   std::vector<int> gchildren = data_access<int, gamma>(parent, 0.0,
08919     DBL_MAX, offsetof(gamma, from_nuc), gamma_data);
08920   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > decay_nrbr =
08921     decay_photon_branch_ratios(parent);
08922   for(int i = 0; i < gk_list.size(); ++i){
08923     for (int j = 0; j < decay_children.size(); ++j) {
08924       if (nucname::zzzaaa(gchildren[i]) == nucname::zzzaaa(decay_children[j])) {
08925         temp = calculate_xray_data(nucname::znum(gchildren[i]),
08926           gk_list[i]*decay_nrbr[j].first, gl_list[i]*decay_nrbr[j].first);
08927         for (int k = 0; k < temp.size(); ++k) {
08928           if (!isnan(temp[k].second) && !isnan(temp[k].first)) {
08929             int found = 0;
08930             for (int l = 0; l < result.size(); ++l) {
08931               if (temp[k].first == result[l].first) {
08932                 result[l].second = result[l].second + temp[k].second;
08933                 found = 1;
08934                 break;
08935               }
08936             }
08937             if (found == 0) {
08938               result.push_back(temp[k]);
08939             }
08940           }
08941         }
08942         break;
08943       }
08944     }
08945   }
08946 
08947   for(int i = 0; i < result.size(); ++i)
08948     result[i].second = result[i].second * decay_c;
08949   return result;
08950 };
08951 
08952 //////////////////////////////////////////
08953 //////////// simple xs data //////////////
08954 //////////////////////////////////////////
08955 
08956 typedef struct simple_xs {
08957   int nuc;
08958   double sigma_t;
08959   double sigma_s;
08960   double sigma_e;
08961   double sigma_i;
08962   double sigma_a;
08963   double sigma_gamma;
08964   double sigma_f;
08965   double sigma_alpha;
08966   double sigma_proton;
08967   double sigma_deut;
08968   double sigma_trit;
08969   double sigma_2n;
08970   double sigma_3n;
08971   double sigma_4n;
08972 } simple_xs;
08973 
08974 std::map<std::string, std::map<int, std::map<int, double> > > pyne::simple_xs_map;
08975 
08976 // loads the simple cross section data for the specified energy band from
08977 // the nuc_data.h5 file into memory.
08978 static void _load_simple_xs_map(std::string energy) {
08979   //Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
08980   if (!pyne::file_exists(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH))
08981     throw pyne::FileNotFound(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
08982 
08983   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str());
08984   if (!ish5)
08985     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH);
08986 
08987   using pyne::rxname::id;
08988   std::map<unsigned int, size_t> rxns;
08989   rxns[id("tot")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_t);
08990   rxns[id("scat")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_s);
08991   rxns[id("elas")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_e);
08992   rxns[id("inel")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_i);
08993   rxns[id("abs")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_a);
08994   rxns[id("gamma")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_gamma);
08995   rxns[id("fiss")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_f);
08996   rxns[id("alpha")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_alpha);
08997   rxns[id("proton")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_proton);
08998   rxns[id("deut")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_deut);
08999   rxns[id("trit")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_trit);
09000   rxns[id("z_2n")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_2n);
09001   rxns[id("z_3n")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_3n);
09002   rxns[id("z_4n")] = offsetof(simple_xs, sigma_4n);
09003 
09004   // Get the HDF5 compound type (table) description
09005   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, sizeof(simple_xs));
09006   H5Tinsert(desc, "nuc",   HOFFSET(simple_xs, nuc),   H5T_NATIVE_INT);
09007   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_t",  HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_t),  H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09008   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_s", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_s), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09009   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_e", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_e), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09010   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_i", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_i), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09011   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_a", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_a), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09012   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_gamma", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_gamma), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09013   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_f", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_f), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09014   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_alpha", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_alpha), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09015   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_proton", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_proton), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09016   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_deut", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_deut), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09017   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_trit", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_trit), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09018   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_2n", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_2n), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09019   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_3n", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_3n), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09020   H5Tinsert(desc, "sigma_4n", HOFFSET(simple_xs, sigma_4n), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
09021 
09022   // Open the HDF5 file
09023   hid_t nuc_data_h5 = H5Fopen(pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY, H5P_DEFAULT);
09024 
09025   // build path to prober simple xs table
09026   std::string path = "/neutron/simple_xs/" + energy;
09027 
09028   // Open the data set
09029   hid_t simple_xs_set = H5Dopen2(nuc_data_h5, path.c_str(), H5P_DEFAULT);
09030   hid_t simple_xs_space = H5Dget_space(simple_xs_set);
09031   int n = H5Sget_simple_extent_npoints(simple_xs_space);
09032 
09033   // Read in the data
09034   simple_xs* array = new simple_xs[n];
09035   H5Dread(simple_xs_set, desc, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT, array);
09036 
09037   // close the nuc_data library, before doing anything stupid
09038   H5Dclose(simple_xs_set);
09039   H5Fclose(nuc_data_h5);
09040 
09041   // Ok now that we have the array of stucts, put it in the map
09042   for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
09043     std::map<unsigned int, size_t>::iterator it;
09044     for (it = rxns.begin(); it != rxns.end(); ++it) {
09045       double xs = *(double*)((char*)&array[i] + it->second);
09046       pyne::simple_xs_map[energy][array[i].nuc][it->first] = xs;
09047     }
09048   }
09049   delete[] array;
09050 }
09051 
09052 double pyne::simple_xs(int nuc, int rx_id, std::string energy) {
09053   std::set<std::string> energies;
09054   energies.insert("thermal");
09055   energies.insert("thermal_maxwell_ave");
09056   energies.insert("resonance_integral");
09057   energies.insert("fourteen_MeV");
09058   energies.insert("fission_spectrum_ave");
09059 
09060   if (energies.count(energy) == 0) {
09061     throw InvalidSimpleXS("Energy '" + energy +
09062         "' is not a valid simple_xs group");
09063   } else if (simple_xs_map.count(energy) == 0) {
09064     _load_simple_xs_map(energy);
09065   }
09066 
09067   if (simple_xs_map[energy].count(nuc) == 0) {
09068     throw InvalidSimpleXS(rxname::name(rx_id) +
09069         " is not a valid simple_xs nuclide");
09070   } else if (simple_xs_map[energy][nuc].count(rx_id) == 0) {
09071     throw InvalidSimpleXS(rxname::name(rx_id) +
09072         " is not a valid simple_xs reaction");
09073   }
09074 
09075   return simple_xs_map[energy][nuc][rx_id];
09076 }
09077 
09078 double pyne::simple_xs(int nuc, std::string rx, std::string energy) {
09079   return pyne::simple_xs(nucname::id(nuc), rxname::id(rx), energy);
09080 }
09081 double pyne::simple_xs(std::string nuc, int rx, std::string energy) {
09082   return pyne::simple_xs(nucname::id(nuc), rxname::id(rx), energy);
09083 }
09084 double pyne::simple_xs(std::string nuc, std::string rx, std::string energy) {
09085   return pyne::simple_xs(nucname::id(nuc), rxname::id(rx), energy);
09086 }

09190 /* This header provides common string manipulation support, such as UTF-8,
09191  * portable conversion from/to string...
09192  *
09193  * It is an internal header that must not be exposed.

09195 
09196 namespace Json {
09197 
09198 /// Converts a unicode code-point to UTF-8.
09199 static inline std::string 
09200 codePointToUTF8(unsigned int cp) {
09201    std::string result;
09202    
09203    // based on description from http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UTF-8
09204 
09205    if (cp <= 0x7f) {
09206       result.resize(1);
09207       result[0] = static_cast<char>(cp);
09208    } else if (cp <= 0x7FF) {
09209       result.resize(2);
09210       result[1] = static_cast<char>(0x80 | (0x3f & cp));
09211       result[0] = static_cast<char>(0xC0 | (0x1f & (cp >> 6)));
09212    } else if (cp <= 0xFFFF) {
09213       result.resize(3);
09214       result[2] = static_cast<char>(0x80 | (0x3f & cp));
09215       result[1] = 0x80 | static_cast<char>((0x3f & (cp >> 6)));
09216       result[0] = 0xE0 | static_cast<char>((0xf & (cp >> 12)));
09217    } else if (cp <= 0x10FFFF) {
09218       result.resize(4);
09219       result[3] = static_cast<char>(0x80 | (0x3f & cp));
09220       result[2] = static_cast<char>(0x80 | (0x3f & (cp >> 6)));
09221       result[1] = static_cast<char>(0x80 | (0x3f & (cp >> 12)));
09222       result[0] = static_cast<char>(0xF0 | (0x7 & (cp >> 18)));
09223    }
09224 
09225    return result;
09226 }
09227 
09228 
09229 /// Returns true if ch is a control character (in range [0,32[).
09230 static inline bool 
09231 isControlCharacter(char ch) {
09232    return ch > 0 && ch <= 0x1F;
09233 }
09234 
09235 
09236 enum { 
09237    /// Constant that specify the size of the buffer that must be passed to uintToString.
09238    uintToStringBufferSize = 3*sizeof(LargestUInt)+1 
09239 };
09240 
09241 // Defines a char buffer for use with uintToString().
09242 typedef char UIntToStringBuffer[uintToStringBufferSize];
09243 
09244 
09245 /** Converts an unsigned integer to string.
09246  * @param value Unsigned interger to convert to string
09247  * @param current Input/Output string buffer. 
09248  *        Must have at least uintToStringBufferSize chars free.
09249  */
09250 static inline void 
09251 uintToString( LargestUInt value, 
09252               char *&current ) {
09253    *--current = 0;
09254    do {
09255       *--current = char(value % 10) + '0';
09256       value /= 10;
09257    }
09258    while ( value != 0 );
09259 }

09339 static bool 
09340 containsNewLine( Reader::Location begin, 
09341                  Reader::Location end ) {
09342    for ( ;begin < end; ++begin )
09343       if ( *begin == '\n'  ||  *begin == '\r' )
09344          return true;
09345    return false;

09364                Value &root,
09365                bool collectComments ) {

09367    const char *begin = document_.c_str();
09368    const char *end = begin + document_.length();

09372 
09373 bool
09374 Reader::parse( std::istream& sin,
09375                Value &root,
09376                bool collectComments ) {
09377    //std::istream_iterator<char> begin(sin);
09378    //std::istream_iterator<char> end;
09379    // Those would allow streamed input from a file, if parse() were a
09380    // template function.
09381 
09382    // Since std::string is reference-counted, this at least does not
09383    // create an extra copy.
09384    std::string doc;
09385    std::getline(sin, doc, (char)EOF);
09386    return parse( doc, root, collectComments );
09387 }
09388 
09389 bool 
09390 Reader::parse( const char *beginDoc, const char *endDoc, 
09391                Value &root,
09392                bool collectComments ) {
09393    if ( !features_.allowComments_ ) {
09394       collectComments = false;
09395    }
09396 
09397    begin_ = beginDoc;
09398    end_ = endDoc;
09399    collectComments_ = collectComments;
09400    current_ = begin_;
09401    lastValueEnd_ = 0;
09402    lastValue_ = 0;
09403    commentsBefore_ = "";
09404    errors_.clear();
09405    while ( !nodes_.empty() )
09406       nodes_.pop();
09407    nodes_.push( &root );
09408    
09409    bool successful = readValue();
09410    Token token;
09411    skipCommentTokens( token );
09412    if ( collectComments_  &&  !commentsBefore_.empty() )
09413       root.setComment( commentsBefore_, commentAfter );
09414    if ( features_.strictRoot_ ) {
09415       if ( !root.isArray()  &&  !root.isObject() ) {
09416          // Set error location to start of doc, ideally should be first token found in doc
09417          token.type_ = tokenError;
09418          token.start_ = beginDoc;
09419          token.end_ = endDoc;
09420          addError( "A valid JSON document must be either an array or an object value.",
09421                    token );
09422          return false;
09423       }
09424    }
09425    return successful;
09426 }
09427 
09428 
09429 bool
09430 Reader::readValue() {
09431    Token token;
09432    skipCommentTokens( token );
09433    bool successful = true;
09434 
09435    if ( collectComments_  &&  !commentsBefore_.empty() ) {
09436       currentValue().setComment( commentsBefore_, commentBefore );
09437       commentsBefore_ = "";
09438    }
09439 
09440 
09441    switch ( token.type_ ) {
09442    case tokenObjectBegin:
09443       successful = readObject( token );
09444       break;
09445    case tokenArrayBegin:
09446       successful = readArray( token );
09447       break;
09448    case tokenNumber:
09449       successful = decodeNumber( token );
09450       break;
09451    case tokenString:
09452       successful = decodeString( token );
09453       break;
09454    case tokenTrue:
09455       currentValue() = true;
09456       break;
09457    case tokenFalse:
09458       currentValue() = false;
09459       break;
09460    case tokenNull:
09461       currentValue() = Value();
09462       break;
09463    default:
09464       return addError( "Syntax error: value, object or array expected.", token );
09465    }
09466 
09467    if ( collectComments_ ) {
09468       lastValueEnd_ = current_;
09469       lastValue_ = &currentValue();
09470    }
09471 
09472    return successful;
09473 }
09474 
09475 
09476 void 
09477 Reader::skipCommentTokens( Token &token ) {
09478    if ( features_.allowComments_ ) {
09479       do {
09480          readToken( token );
09481       }
09482       while ( token.type_ == tokenComment );
09483    } else {
09484       readToken( token );
09485    }
09486 }
09487 
09488 
09489 bool 
09490 Reader::expectToken( TokenType type, Token &token, const char *message ) {
09491    readToken( token );
09492    if ( token.type_ != type )
09493       return addError( message, token );
09494    return true;
09495 }
09496 
09497 
09498 bool 
09499 Reader::readToken( Token &token ) {
09500    skipSpaces();
09501    token.start_ = current_;
09502    Char c = getNextChar();
09503    bool ok = true;
09504    switch ( c ) {
09505    case '{':
09506       token.type_ = tokenObjectBegin;
09507       break;
09508    case '}':
09509       token.type_ = tokenObjectEnd;
09510       break;
09511    case '[':
09512       token.type_ = tokenArrayBegin;
09513       break;
09514    case ']':
09515       token.type_ = tokenArrayEnd;
09516       break;
09517    case '"':
09518       token.type_ = tokenString;
09519       ok = readString();
09520       break;
09521    case '/':
09522       token.type_ = tokenComment;
09523       ok = readComment();
09524       break;
09525    case '0':
09526    case '1':
09527    case '2':
09528    case '3':
09529    case '4':
09530    case '5':
09531    case '6':
09532    case '7':
09533    case '8':
09534    case '9':
09535    case '-':
09536       token.type_ = tokenNumber;
09537       readNumber();
09538       break;
09539    case 't':
09540       token.type_ = tokenTrue;
09541       ok = match( "rue", 3 );
09542       break;
09543    case 'f':
09544       token.type_ = tokenFalse;
09545       ok = match( "alse", 4 );
09546       break;
09547    case 'n':
09548       token.type_ = tokenNull;
09549       ok = match( "ull", 3 );
09550       break;
09551    case ',':
09552       token.type_ = tokenArraySeparator;
09553       break;
09554    case ':':
09555       token.type_ = tokenMemberSeparator;
09556       break;
09557    case 0:
09558       token.type_ = tokenEndOfStream;
09559       break;
09560    default:
09561       ok = false;
09562       break;
09563    }
09564    if ( !ok )
09565       token.type_ = tokenError;
09566    token.end_ = current_;
09567    return true;
09568 }
09569 
09570 
09571 void 
09572 Reader::skipSpaces() {
09573    while ( current_ != end_ ) {
09574       Char c = *current_;
09575       if ( c == ' '  ||  c == '\t'  ||  c == '\r'  ||  c == '\n' )
09576          ++current_;
09577       else
09578          break;
09579    }
09580 }
09581 
09582 
09583 bool 
09584 Reader::match( Location pattern, 
09585                int patternLength ) {
09586    if ( end_ - current_ < patternLength )
09587       return false;
09588    int index = patternLength;
09589    while ( index-- )
09590       if ( current_[index] != pattern[index] )
09591          return false;
09592    current_ += patternLength;
09593    return true;
09594 }
09595 
09596 
09597 bool
09598 Reader::readComment() {
09599    Location commentBegin = current_ - 1;
09600    Char c = getNextChar();
09601    bool successful = false;
09602    if ( c == '*' )
09603       successful = readCStyleComment();
09604    else if ( c == '/' )
09605       successful = readCppStyleComment();
09606    if ( !successful )
09607       return false;
09608 
09609    if ( collectComments_ ) {
09610       CommentPlacement placement = commentBefore;
09611       if ( lastValueEnd_  &&  !containsNewLine( lastValueEnd_, commentBegin ) )
09612       {
09613          if ( c != '*'  ||  !containsNewLine( commentBegin, current_ ) )
09614             placement = commentAfterOnSameLine;
09615       }
09616 
09617       addComment( commentBegin, current_, placement );
09618    }
09619    return true;
09620 }
09621 
09622 
09623 void 
09624 Reader::addComment( Location begin, 
09625                     Location end, 
09626                     CommentPlacement placement ) {
09627    assert( collectComments_ );
09628    if ( placement == commentAfterOnSameLine )
09629    {
09630       assert( lastValue_ != 0 );
09631       lastValue_->setComment( std::string( begin, end ), placement );
09632    } else {
09633       if ( !commentsBefore_.empty() )
09634          commentsBefore_ += "\n";
09635       commentsBefore_ += std::string( begin, end );
09636    }
09637 }

09639 
09640 bool 
09641 Reader::readCStyleComment() {
09642    while ( current_ != end_ ) {
09643       Char c = getNextChar();
09644       if ( c == '*'  &&  *current_ == '/' )
09645          break;
09646    }
09647    return getNextChar() == '/';
09648 }
09649 
09650 
09651 bool 
09652 Reader::readCppStyleComment() {
09653    while ( current_ != end_ ) {
09654       Char c = getNextChar();
09655       if (  c == '\r'  ||  c == '\n' )
09656          break;
09657    }
09658    return true;
09659 }
09660 
09661 
09662 void 
09663 Reader::readNumber() {
09664    while ( current_ != end_ ) {
09665       if ( !(*current_ >= '0'  &&  *current_ <= '9')  &&
09666            !in( *current_, '.', 'e', 'E', '+', '-' ) )
09667          break;
09668       ++current_;
09669    }
09670 }
09671 
09672 bool
09673 Reader::readString() {
09674    Char c = 0;
09675    while ( current_ != end_ ) {
09676       c = getNextChar();
09677       if ( c == '\\' )
09678          getNextChar();
09679       else if ( c == '"' )
09680          break;
09681    }
09682    return c == '"';
09683 }
09684 
09685 
09686 bool 
09687 Reader::readObject( Token &/*tokenStart*/ ) {
09688    Token tokenName;
09689    std::string name;
09690    currentValue() = Value( objectValue );
09691    while ( readToken( tokenName ) ) {
09692       bool initialTokenOk = true;
09693       while ( tokenName.type_ == tokenComment  &&  initialTokenOk )
09694          initialTokenOk = readToken( tokenName );
09695       if  ( !initialTokenOk )
09696          break;
09697       if ( tokenName.type_ == tokenObjectEnd  &&  name.empty() )  // empty object
09698          return true;
09699       if ( tokenName.type_ != tokenString )
09700          break;
09701       
09702       name = "";
09703       if ( !decodeString( tokenName, name ) )
09704          return recoverFromError( tokenObjectEnd );
09705 
09706       Token colon;
09707       if ( !readToken( colon ) ||  colon.type_ != tokenMemberSeparator ) {
09708          return addErrorAndRecover( "Missing ':' after object member name", 
09709                                     colon, 
09710                                     tokenObjectEnd );
09711       }
09712       Value &value = currentValue()[ name ];
09713       nodes_.push( &value );
09714       bool ok = readValue();
09715       nodes_.pop();
09716       if ( !ok ) // error already set
09717          return recoverFromError( tokenObjectEnd );
09718 
09719       Token comma;
09720       if ( !readToken( comma )
09721             ||  ( comma.type_ != tokenObjectEnd  &&  
09722                   comma.type_ != tokenArraySeparator &&
09723                   comma.type_ != tokenComment ) ) {
09724          return addErrorAndRecover( "Missing ',' or '}' in object declaration", 
09725                                     comma, 
09726                                     tokenObjectEnd );
09727       }
09728       bool finalizeTokenOk = true;
09729       while ( comma.type_ == tokenComment &&
09730               finalizeTokenOk )
09731          finalizeTokenOk = readToken( comma );
09732       if ( comma.type_ == tokenObjectEnd )
09733          return true;
09734    }
09735    return addErrorAndRecover( "Missing '}' or object member name", 
09736                               tokenName, 
09737                               tokenObjectEnd );
09738 }
09739 
09740 
09741 bool 
09742 Reader::readArray( Token &/*tokenStart*/ ) {
09743    currentValue() = Value( arrayValue );
09744    skipSpaces();
09745    if ( *current_ == ']' ) { // empty array
09746       Token endArray;
09747       readToken( endArray );
09748       return true;
09749    }
09750    int index = 0;
09751    for (;;) {
09752       Value &value = currentValue()[ index++ ];
09753       nodes_.push( &value );
09754       bool ok = readValue();
09755       nodes_.pop();
09756       if ( !ok ) // error already set
09757          return recoverFromError( tokenArrayEnd );
09758 
09759       Token token;
09760       // Accept Comment after last item in the array.
09761       ok = readToken( token );
09762       while ( token.type_ == tokenComment  &&  ok ) {
09763          ok = readToken( token );
09764       }
09765       bool badTokenType = ( token.type_ != tokenArraySeparator  &&
09766                             token.type_ != tokenArrayEnd );
09767       if ( !ok  ||  badTokenType ) {
09768          return addErrorAndRecover( "Missing ',' or ']' in array declaration", 
09769                                     token, 
09770                                     tokenArrayEnd );
09771       }
09772       if ( token.type_ == tokenArrayEnd )
09773          break;
09774    }
09775    return true;
09776 }
09777 
09778 
09779 bool 
09780 Reader::decodeNumber( Token &token ) {
09781    bool isDouble = false;
09782    for ( Location inspect = token.start_; inspect != token.end_; ++inspect )
09783    {
09784       isDouble = isDouble  
09785                  ||  in( *inspect, '.', 'e', 'E', '+' )  
09786                  ||  ( *inspect == '-'  &&  inspect != token.start_ );
09787    }
09788    if ( isDouble )
09789       return decodeDouble( token );
09790    // Attempts to parse the number as an integer. If the number is
09791    // larger than the maximum supported value of an integer then
09792    // we decode the number as a double.
09793    Location current = token.start_;
09794    bool isNegative = *current == '-';
09795    if ( isNegative )
09796       ++current;
09797    Value::LargestUInt maxIntegerValue = isNegative ? Value::LargestUInt(-Value::minLargestInt) 
09798                                                    : Value::maxLargestUInt;
09799    Value::LargestUInt threshold = maxIntegerValue / 10;
09800    Value::UInt lastDigitThreshold = Value::UInt( maxIntegerValue % 10 );
09801    assert( lastDigitThreshold >=0  &&  lastDigitThreshold <= 9 );
09802    Value::LargestUInt value = 0;
09803    while ( current < token.end_ ) {
09804       Char c = *current++;
09805       if ( c < '0'  ||  c > '9' )
09806          return addError( "'" + std::string( token.start_, token.end_ ) + "' is not a number.", token );
09807       Value::UInt digit(c - '0');
09808       if ( value >= threshold ) {
09809          // If the current digit is not the last one, or if it is
09810          // greater than the last digit of the maximum integer value,
09811          // the parse the number as a double.
09812          if ( current != token.end_  ||  digit > lastDigitThreshold ) {
09813             return decodeDouble( token );
09814          }
09815       }
09816       value = value * 10 + digit;
09817    }
09818    if ( isNegative )
09819       currentValue() = -Value::LargestInt( value );
09820    else if ( value <= Value::LargestUInt(Value::maxInt) )
09821       currentValue() = Value::LargestInt( value );
09822    else
09823       currentValue() = value;
09824    return true;
09825 }
09826 
09827 
09828 bool 
09829 Reader::decodeDouble( Token &token ) {
09830    double value = 0;
09831    const int bufferSize = 32;
09832    int count;
09833    int length = int(token.end_ - token.start_);
09834    if ( length <= bufferSize ) {
09835       Char buffer[bufferSize+1];
09836       memcpy( buffer, token.start_, length );
09837       buffer[length] = 0;
09838       count = sscanf( buffer, "%lf", &value );
09839    } else {
09840       std::string buffer( token.start_, token.end_ );
09841       count = sscanf( buffer.c_str(), "%lf", &value );
09842    }
09843 
09844    if ( count != 1 )
09845       return addError( "'" + std::string( token.start_, token.end_ ) + "' is not a number.", token );
09846    currentValue() = value;
09847    return true;
09848 }
09849 
09850 
09851 bool 
09852 Reader::decodeString( Token &token ) {
09853    std::string decoded;
09854    if ( !decodeString( token, decoded ) )
09855       return false;
09856    currentValue() = decoded;
09857    return true;
09858 }
09859 
09860 
09861 bool 
09862 Reader::decodeString( Token &token, std::string &decoded ) {
09863    decoded.reserve( token.end_ - token.start_ - 2 );
09864    Location current = token.start_ + 1; // skip '"'
09865    Location end = token.end_ - 1;      // do not include '"'
09866    while ( current != end ) {
09867       Char c = *current++;
09868       if ( c == '"' )
09869          break;
09870       else if ( c == '\\' ) {
09871          if ( current == end )
09872             return addError( "Empty escape sequence in string", token, current );
09873          Char escape = *current++;
09874          switch ( escape ) {
09875          case '"': decoded += '"'; break;
09876          case '/': decoded += '/'; break;
09877          case '\\': decoded += '\\'; break;
09878          case 'b': decoded += '\b'; break;
09879          case 'f': decoded += '\f'; break;
09880          case 'n': decoded += '\n'; break;
09881          case 'r': decoded += '\r'; break;
09882          case 't': decoded += '\t'; break;
09883          case 'u': {
09884                unsigned int unicode;
09885                if ( !decodeUnicodeCodePoint( token, current, end, unicode ) )
09886                   return false;
09887                decoded += codePointToUTF8(unicode);
09888             }
09889             break;
09890          default:
09891             return addError( "Bad escape sequence in string", token, current );
09892          }
09893       }
09894       else {
09895          decoded += c;
09896       }
09897    }
09898    return true;
09899 }
09900 
09901 bool
09902 Reader::decodeUnicodeCodePoint( Token &token, 
09903                                      Location &current, 
09904                                      Location end, 
09905                                      unsigned int &unicode ) {
09906 
09907    if ( !decodeUnicodeEscapeSequence( token, current, end, unicode ) )
09908       return false;
09909    if (unicode >= 0xD800 && unicode <= 0xDBFF) {
09910       // surrogate pairs
09911       if (end - current < 6)
09912          return addError( "additional six characters expected to parse unicode surrogate pair.", token, current );
09913       unsigned int surrogatePair;
09914       if (*(current++) == '\\' && *(current++)== 'u') {
09915          if (decodeUnicodeEscapeSequence( token, current, end, surrogatePair )) {
09916             unicode = 0x10000 + ((unicode & 0x3FF) << 10) + (surrogatePair & 0x3FF);
09917          } else
09918             return false;
09919       } else
09920          return addError( "expecting another \\u token to begin the second half of a unicode surrogate pair", token, current );
09921    }
09922    return true;
09923 }
09924 
09925 bool 
09926 Reader::decodeUnicodeEscapeSequence( Token &token, 
09927                                      Location &current, 
09928                                      Location end, 
09929                                      unsigned int &unicode ) {
09930    if ( end - current < 4 )
09931       return addError( "Bad unicode escape sequence in string: four digits expected.", token, current );
09932    unicode = 0;
09933    for ( int index =0; index < 4; ++index ) {
09934       Char c = *current++;
09935       unicode *= 16;
09936       if ( c >= '0'  &&  c <= '9' )
09937          unicode += c - '0';
09938       else if ( c >= 'a'  &&  c <= 'f' )
09939          unicode += c - 'a' + 10;
09940       else if ( c >= 'A'  &&  c <= 'F' )
09941          unicode += c - 'A' + 10;
09942       else
09943          return addError( "Bad unicode escape sequence in string: hexadecimal digit expected.", token, current );
09944    }
09945    return true;
09946 }
09947

09949 bool 
09950 Reader::addError( const std::string &message, 
09951                   Token &token,
09952                   Location extra ) {
09953    ErrorInfo info;
09954    info.token_ = token;
09955    info.message_ = message;
09956    info.extra_ = extra;
09957    errors_.push_back( info );
09958    return false;
09959 }

09961 
09962 bool 
09963 Reader::recoverFromError( TokenType skipUntilToken ) {
09964    int errorCount = int(errors_.size());
09965    Token skip;
09966    for (;;) {
09967       if ( !readToken(skip) )
09968          errors_.resize( errorCount ); // discard errors caused by recovery
09969       if ( skip.type_ == skipUntilToken  ||  skip.type_ == tokenEndOfStream )
09970          break;
09971    }
09972    errors_.resize( errorCount );
09973    return false;
09974 }
09975 
09976 
09977 bool 
09978 Reader::addErrorAndRecover( const std::string &message, 
09979                             Token &token,
09980                             TokenType skipUntilToken ) {
09981    addError( message, token );
09982    return recoverFromError( skipUntilToken );
09983 }

09994    if ( current_ == end_ )
09995       return 0;
09996    return *current_++;

09999 
10000 void 
10001 Reader::getLocationLineAndColumn( Location location,
10002                                   int &line,
10003                                   int &column ) const {
10004    Location current = begin_;
10005    Location lastLineStart = current;
10006    line = 0;
10007    while ( current < location  &&  current != end_ ) {
10008       Char c = *current++;
10009       if ( c == '\r' ) {
10010          if ( *current == '\n' )
10011             ++current;
10012          lastLineStart = current;
10013          ++line;
10014       } else if ( c == '\n' ) {
10015          lastLineStart = current;
10016          ++line;
10017       }
10018    }
10019    // column & line start at 1
10020    column = int(location - lastLineStart) + 1;
10021    ++line;
10022 }
10023 
10024 
10025 std::string
10026 Reader::getLocationLineAndColumn( Location location ) const {
10027    int line, column;
10028    getLocationLineAndColumn( location, line, column );
10029    char buffer[18+16+16+1];
10030    sprintf( buffer, "Line %d, Column %d", line, column );
10031    return buffer;
10032 }

10038     return getFormattedErrorMessages();
10039 }
10040 
10041 
10042 std::string 
10043 Reader::getFormattedErrorMessages() const {
10044    std::string formattedMessage;
10045    for ( Errors::const_iterator itError = errors_.begin();
10046          itError != errors_.end();
10047          ++itError ) {
10048       const ErrorInfo &error = *itError;
10049       formattedMessage += "* " + getLocationLineAndColumn( error.token_.start_ ) + "\n";
10050       formattedMessage += "  " + error.message_ + "\n";
10051       if ( error.extra_ )
10052          formattedMessage += "See " + getLocationLineAndColumn( error.extra_ ) + " for detail.\n";
10053    }
10054    return formattedMessage;
10055 }

10059     Json::Reader reader;
10060     bool ok = reader.parse(sin, root, true);
10061     //JSON_ASSERT( ok );
10062     if (!ok) throw std::runtime_error(reader.getFormattedErrorMessages());
10063     return sin;
10064 }

10087 #ifndef JSONCPP_BATCHALLOCATOR_H_INCLUDED
10088 # define JSONCPP_BATCHALLOCATOR_H_INCLUDED
10089 
10090 # include <stdlib.h>
10091 # include <assert.h>
10092 
10093 # ifndef JSONCPP_DOC_EXCLUDE_IMPLEMENTATION
10094 
10095 namespace Json {
10096 
10097 /* Fast memory allocator.
10098  *
10099  * This memory allocator allocates memory for a batch of object (specified by
10100  * the page size, the number of object in each page).
10101  *
10102  * It does not allow the destruction of a single object. All the allocated objects
10103  * can be destroyed at once. The memory can be either released or reused for future
10104  * allocation.
10105  * 
10106  * The in-place new operator must be used to construct the object using the pointer
10107  * returned by allocate.
10108  */
10109 template<typename AllocatedType
10110         ,const unsigned int objectPerAllocation>
10111 class BatchAllocator {
10112 public:
10113    typedef AllocatedType Type;
10114 
10115    BatchAllocator( unsigned int objectsPerPage = 255 )
10116       : freeHead_( 0 )
10117       , objectsPerPage_( objectsPerPage ) {
10118 //      printf( "Size: %d => %s\n", sizeof(AllocatedType), typeid(AllocatedType).name() );
10119       assert( sizeof(AllocatedType) * objectPerAllocation >= sizeof(AllocatedType *) ); // We must be able to store a slist in the object free space.
10120       assert( objectsPerPage >= 16 );
10121       batches_ = allocateBatch( 0 );   // allocated a dummy page
10122       currentBatch_ = batches_;
10123    }
10124 
10125    ~BatchAllocator() {
10126       for ( BatchInfo *batch = batches_; batch;  ) {
10127          BatchInfo *nextBatch = batch->next_;
10128          free( batch );
10129          batch = nextBatch;
10130       }
10131    }
10132 
10133    /// allocate space for an array of objectPerAllocation object.
10134    /// @warning it is the responsability of the caller to call objects constructors.
10135    AllocatedType *allocate() {
10136       if ( freeHead_ ) { // returns node from free list.
10137          AllocatedType *object = freeHead_;
10138          freeHead_ = *(AllocatedType **)object;
10139          return object;
10140       }
10141       if ( currentBatch_->used_ == currentBatch_->end_ ) {
10142          currentBatch_ = currentBatch_->next_;
10143          while ( currentBatch_  &&  currentBatch_->used_ == currentBatch_->end_ )
10144             currentBatch_ = currentBatch_->next_;
10145 
10146          if ( !currentBatch_  ) { // no free batch found, allocate a new one
10147             currentBatch_ = allocateBatch( objectsPerPage_ );
10148             currentBatch_->next_ = batches_; // insert at the head of the list
10149             batches_ = currentBatch_;
10150          }
10151       }
10152       AllocatedType *allocated = currentBatch_->used_;
10153       currentBatch_->used_ += objectPerAllocation;
10154       return allocated;
10155    }
10156 
10157    /// Release the object.
10158    /// @warning it is the responsability of the caller to actually destruct the object.
10159    void release( AllocatedType *object ) {
10160       assert( object != 0 );
10161       *(AllocatedType **)object = freeHead_;
10162       freeHead_ = object;
10163    }
10164 
10165 private:
10166    struct BatchInfo {
10167       BatchInfo *next_;
10168       AllocatedType *used_;
10169       AllocatedType *end_;
10170       AllocatedType buffer_[objectPerAllocation];
10171    };
10172 
10173    // disabled copy constructor and assignement operator.
10174    BatchAllocator( const BatchAllocator & );
10175    void operator =( const BatchAllocator &);
10176 
10177    static BatchInfo *allocateBatch( unsigned int objectsPerPage ) {
10178       const unsigned int mallocSize = sizeof(BatchInfo) - sizeof(AllocatedType)* objectPerAllocation
10179                                 + sizeof(AllocatedType) * objectPerAllocation * objectsPerPage;
10180       BatchInfo *batch = static_cast<BatchInfo*>( malloc( mallocSize ) );
10181       batch->next_ = 0;
10182       batch->used_ = batch->buffer_;
10183       batch->end_ = batch->buffer_ + objectsPerPage;
10184       return batch;
10185    }
10186 
10187    BatchInfo *batches_;
10188    BatchInfo *currentBatch_;
10189    /// Head of a single linked list within the allocated space of freeed object
10190    AllocatedType *freeHead_;
10191    unsigned int objectsPerPage_;
10192 };
10193

10197 # endif // ifndef JSONCPP_DOC_INCLUDE_IMPLEMENTATION
10198 
10199 #endif // JSONCPP_BATCHALLOCATOR_H_INCLUDED
