10297 
10298 
10299 ValueIteratorBase::difference_type 
10300 ValueIteratorBase::computeDistance( const SelfType &other ) const {
10301 #ifndef JSON_VALUE_USE_INTERNAL_MAP
10302 # ifdef JSON_USE_CPPTL_SMALLMAP
10303    return current_ - other.current_;
10304 # else
10305    // Iterator for null value are initialized using the default
10306    // constructor, which initialize current_ to the default
10307    // std::map::iterator. As begin() and end() are two instance 
10308    // of the default std::map::iterator, they can not be compared.
10309    // To allow this, we handle this comparison specifically.
10310    if ( isNull_  &&  other.isNull_ ) {
10311       return 0;
10312    }
10313 
10314 
10315    // Usage of std::distance is not portable (does not compile with Sun Studio 12 RogueWave STL,
10316    // which is the one used by default).
10317    // Using a portable hand-made version for non random iterator instead:
10318    //   return difference_type( std::distance( current_, other.current_ ) );
10319    difference_type myDistance = 0;
10320    for ( Value::ObjectValues::iterator it = current_; it != other.current_; ++it ) {
10321       ++myDistance;
10322    }
10323    return myDistance;
10324 # endif
10325 #else
10326    if ( isArray_ )
10327       return ValueInternalArray::distance( iterator_.array_, other.iterator_.array_ );
10328    return ValueInternalMap::distance( iterator_.map_, other.iterator_.map_ );
10329 #endif
10330 }
10331 
10332 
10333 bool 
10334 ValueIteratorBase::isEqual( const SelfType &other ) const {
10335 #ifndef JSON_VALUE_USE_INTERNAL_MAP
10336    if ( isNull_ ) {
10337       return other.isNull_;
10338    }
10339    return current_ == other.current_;
10340 #else
10341    if ( isArray_ )
10342       return ValueInternalArray::equals( iterator_.array_, other.iterator_.array_ );
10343    return ValueInternalMap::equals( iterator_.map_, other.iterator_.map_ );
10344 #endif
10345 }
10346 
10347 
10348 void 
10349 ValueIteratorBase::copy( const SelfType &other ) {
10350 #ifndef JSON_VALUE_USE_INTERNAL_MAP
10351    current_ = other.current_;
10352 #else
10353    if ( isArray_ )
10354       iterator_.array_ = other.iterator_.array_;
10355    iterator_.map_ = other.iterator_.map_;
10356 #endif
10357 }
10358 
10359 
10360 Value 
10361 ValueIteratorBase::key() const {
10362 #ifndef JSON_VALUE_USE_INTERNAL_MAP
10363    const Value::CZString czstring = (*current_).first;
10364    if ( czstring.c_str() ) {
10365       if ( czstring.isStaticString() )
10366          return Value( StaticString( czstring.c_str() ) );
10367       return Value( czstring.c_str() );
10368    }
10369    return Value( czstring.index() );
10370 #else
10371    if ( isArray_ )
10372       return Value( ValueInternalArray::indexOf( iterator_.array_ ) );
10373    bool isStatic;
10374    const char *memberName = ValueInternalMap::key( iterator_.map_, isStatic );
10375    if ( isStatic )
10376       return Value( StaticString( memberName ) );
10377    return Value( memberName );
10378 #endif
10379 }
10380 
10381 
10382 UInt 
10383 ValueIteratorBase::index() const {
10384 #ifndef JSON_VALUE_USE_INTERNAL_MAP
10385    const Value::CZString czstring = (*current_).first;
10386    if ( !czstring.c_str() )
10387       return czstring.index();
10388    return Value::UInt( -1 );
10389 #else
10390    if ( isArray_ )
10391       return Value::UInt( ValueInternalArray::indexOf( iterator_.array_ ) );
10392    return Value::UInt( -1 );
10393 #endif
10394 }
10395 
10396 
10397 const char *
10398 ValueIteratorBase::memberName() const {
10399 #ifndef JSON_VALUE_USE_INTERNAL_MAP
10400    const char *name = (*current_).first.c_str();
10401    return name ? name : "";
10402 #else
10403    if ( !isArray_ )
10404       return ValueInternalMap::key( iterator_.map_ );
10405    return "";
10406 #endif
10407 }

10538 
10539 /// Unknown size marker
10540 static const unsigned int unknown = (unsigned)-1;
10541 
10542 
10543 /** Duplicates the specified string value.
10544  * @param value Pointer to the string to duplicate. Must be zero-terminated if
10545  *              length is "unknown".
10546  * @param length Length of the value. if equals to unknown, then it will be
10547  *               computed using strlen(value).
10548  * @return Pointer on the duplicate instance of string.
10549  */
10550 static inline char *
10551 duplicateStringValue( const char *value, 
10552                       unsigned int length = unknown ) {
10553    if ( length == unknown )
10554       length = (unsigned int)strlen(value);
10555    char *newString = static_cast<char *>( malloc( length + 1 ) );
10556    JSON_ASSERT_MESSAGE( newString != 0, "Failed to allocate string value buffer" );
10557    memcpy( newString, value, length );
10558    newString[length] = 0;
10559    return newString;
10560 }
10561 
10562 
10563 /** Free the string duplicated by duplicateStringValue().
10564  */
10565 static inline void 
10566 releaseStringValue( char *value ) {
10567    if ( value )
10568       free( value );
10569 }

10601 Value::CommentInfo::CommentInfo()
10602    : comment_( 0 ) {
10603 }

10606    if ( comment_ )
10607       releaseStringValue( comment_ );
10608 }

10610 
10611 void 
10612 Value::CommentInfo::setComment( const char *text ) {
10613    if ( comment_ )
10614       releaseStringValue( comment_ );
10615    JSON_ASSERT( text != 0 );
10616    JSON_ASSERT_MESSAGE( text[0]=='\0' || text[0]=='/', "Comments must start with /");
10617    // It seems that /**/ style comments are acceptable as well.
10618    comment_ = duplicateStringValue( text );
10619 }

10641                                   : cstr )
10642    , index_( allocate ) {
10643 }
10644 
10645 Value::CZString::CZString( const CZString &other )
10646 : cstr_( other.index_ != noDuplication &&  other.cstr_ != 0
10647                 ?  duplicateStringValue( other.cstr_ )
10648                 : other.cstr_ )
10649    , index_( other.cstr_ ? (other.index_ == noDuplication ? noDuplication : duplicate)
10650                          : other.index_ ) {
10651 }

10654    if ( cstr_  &&  index_ == duplicate )
10655       releaseStringValue( const_cast<char *>( cstr_ ) );

10713 /*! \internal Default constructor initialization must be equivalent to:
10714  * memset( this, 0, sizeof(Value) )
10715  * This optimization is used in ValueInternalMap fast allocator.
10716  */
10717 Value::Value( ValueType type )
10718    : type_( type )
10719    , allocated_( 0 )
10720    , comments_( 0 )
10721 # ifdef JSON_VALUE_USE_INTERNAL_MAP
10722    , itemIsUsed_( 0 )
10723 #endif
10724 {
10725    switch ( type ) {
10726    case nullValue:
10727       break;
10728    case intValue:
10729    case uintValue:
10730       value_.int_ = 0;
10731       break;
10732    case realValue:
10733       value_.real_ = 0.0;
10734       break;
10735    case stringValue:
10736       value_.string_ = 0;
10737       break;
10738 #ifndef JSON_VALUE_USE_INTERNAL_MAP
10739    case arrayValue:
10740    case objectValue:
10741       value_.map_ = new ObjectValues();
10742       break;
10743 #else
10744    case arrayValue:
10745       value_.array_ = arrayAllocator()->newArray();
10746       break;
10747    case objectValue:
10748       value_.map_ = mapAllocator()->newMap();
10749       break;
10750 #endif
10751    case booleanValue:
10752       value_.bool_ = false;
10753       break;
10754    default:
10755       JSON_ASSERT_UNREACHABLE;
10756    }
10757 }

10888 
10889 
10890 Value::Value( const Value &other )
10891    : type_( other.type_ )
10892    , comments_( 0 )
10893 # ifdef JSON_VALUE_USE_INTERNAL_MAP
10894    , itemIsUsed_( 0 )
10895 #endif
10896 {
10897    switch ( type_ ) {
10898    case nullValue:
10899    case intValue:
10900    case uintValue:
10901    case realValue:
10902    case booleanValue:
10903       value_ = other.value_;
10904       break;
10905    case stringValue:
10906       if ( other.value_.string_ ) {
10907          value_.string_ = duplicateStringValue( other.value_.string_ );
10908          allocated_ = true;
10909       }
10910       else
10911          value_.string_ = 0;
10912       break;
10913 #ifndef JSON_VALUE_USE_INTERNAL_MAP
10914    case arrayValue:
10915    case objectValue:
10916       value_.map_ = new ObjectValues( *other.value_.map_ );
10917       break;
10918 #else
10919    case arrayValue:
10920       value_.array_ = arrayAllocator()->newArrayCopy( *other.value_.array_ );
10921       break;
10922    case objectValue:
10923       value_.map_ = mapAllocator()->newMapCopy( *other.value_.map_ );
10924       break;
10925 #endif
10926    default:
10927       JSON_ASSERT_UNREACHABLE;
10928    }
10929    if ( other.comments_ ) {
10930       comments_ = new CommentInfo[numberOfCommentPlacement];
10931       for ( int comment =0; comment < numberOfCommentPlacement; ++comment ) {
10932          const CommentInfo &otherComment = other.comments_[comment];
10933          if ( otherComment.comment_ )
10934             comments_[comment].setComment( otherComment.comment_ );
10935       }
10936    }
10937 }
10938 
10939 
10940 Value::~Value() {
10941    switch ( type_ ) {
10942    case nullValue:
10943    case intValue:
10944    case uintValue:
10945    case realValue:
10946    case booleanValue:
10947       break;
10948    case stringValue:
10949       if ( allocated_ )
10950          releaseStringValue( value_.string_ );
10951       break;
10952 #ifndef JSON_VALUE_USE_INTERNAL_MAP
10953    case arrayValue:
10954    case objectValue:
10955       delete value_.map_;
10956       break;
10957 #else
10958    case arrayValue:
10959       arrayAllocator()->destructArray( value_.array_ );
10960       break;
10961    case objectValue:
10962       mapAllocator()->destructMap( value_.map_ );
10963       break;
10964 #endif
10965    default:
10966       JSON_ASSERT_UNREACHABLE;
10967    }
10968 
10969    if ( comments_ )
10970       delete[] comments_;
10971 }
10972 
10973 Value &
10974 Value::operator=( const Value &other ) {
10975    Value temp( other );
10976    swap( temp );
10977    return *this;
10978 }
10979 
10980 void 
10981 Value::swap( Value &other ) {
10982    ValueType temp = type_;
10983    type_ = other.type_;
10984    other.type_ = temp;
10985    std::swap( value_, other.value_ );
10986    int temp2 = allocated_;
10987    allocated_ = other.allocated_;
10988    other.allocated_ = temp2;
10989 }
10990 
10991 ValueType 
10992 Value::type() const {
10993    return type_;
10994 }
10995 
10996 
10997 int 
10998 Value::compare( const Value &other ) const {
10999    if ( *this < other )
11000       return -1;
11001    if ( *this > other )
11002       return 1;
11003    return 0;
11004 }
11005 
11006 
11007 bool 
11008 Value::operator <( const Value &other ) const {
11009    int typeDelta = type_ - other.type_;
11010    if ( typeDelta )
11011       return typeDelta < 0 ? true : false;
11012    switch ( type_ ) {
11013    case nullValue:
11014       return false;
11015    case intValue:
11016       return value_.int_ < other.value_.int_;
11017    case uintValue:
11018       return value_.uint_ < other.value_.uint_;
11019    case realValue:
11020       return value_.real_ < other.value_.real_;
11021    case booleanValue:
11022       return value_.bool_ < other.value_.bool_;
11023    case stringValue:
11024       return ( value_.string_ == 0  &&  other.value_.string_ )
11025              || ( other.value_.string_  
11026                   &&  value_.string_  
11027                   && strcmp( value_.string_, other.value_.string_ ) < 0 );
11028 #ifndef JSON_VALUE_USE_INTERNAL_MAP
11029    case arrayValue:
11030    case objectValue: {
11031          int delta = int( value_.map_->size() - other.value_.map_->size() );
11032          if ( delta )
11033             return delta < 0;
11034          return (*value_.map_) < (*other.value_.map_);
11035       }
11036 #else
11037    case arrayValue:
11038       return value_.array_->compare( *(other.value_.array_) ) < 0;
11039    case objectValue:
11040       return value_.map_->compare( *(other.value_.map_) ) < 0;
11041 #endif
11042    default:
11043       JSON_ASSERT_UNREACHABLE;
11044    }
11045    return false;  // unreachable
11046 }
11047 
11048 bool 
11049 Value::operator <=( const Value &other ) const {
11050    return !(other < *this);
11051 }
11052 
11053 bool 
11054 Value::operator >=( const Value &other ) const {
11055    return !(*this < other);
11056 }
11057 
11058 bool 
11059 Value::operator >( const Value &other ) const {
11060    return other < *this;
11061 }
11062 
11063 bool 
11064 Value::operator ==( const Value &other ) const {
11065    //if ( type_ != other.type_ )
11066    // GCC 2.95.3 says:
11067    // attempt to take address of bit-field structure member `Json::Value::type_'
11068    // Beats me, but a temp solves the problem.
11069    int temp = other.type_;
11070    if ( type_ != temp )
11071       return false;
11072    switch ( type_ ) {
11073    case nullValue:
11074       return true;
11075    case intValue:
11076       return value_.int_ == other.value_.int_;
11077    case uintValue:
11078       return value_.uint_ == other.value_.uint_;
11079    case realValue:
11080       return value_.real_ == other.value_.real_;
11081    case booleanValue:
11082       return value_.bool_ == other.value_.bool_;
11083    case stringValue:
11084       return ( value_.string_ == other.value_.string_ )
11085              || ( other.value_.string_  
11086                   &&  value_.string_  
11087                   && strcmp( value_.string_, other.value_.string_ ) == 0 );
11088 #ifndef JSON_VALUE_USE_INTERNAL_MAP
11089    case arrayValue:
11090    case objectValue:
11091       return value_.map_->size() == other.value_.map_->size()
11092              && (*value_.map_) == (*other.value_.map_);
11093 #else
11094    case arrayValue:
11095       return value_.array_->compare( *(other.value_.array_) ) == 0;
11096    case objectValue:
11097       return value_.map_->compare( *(other.value_.map_) ) == 0;
11098 #endif
11099    default:
11100       JSON_ASSERT_UNREACHABLE;
11101    }
11102    return false;  // unreachable
11103 }
11104 
11105 bool 
11106 Value::operator !=( const Value &other ) const
11107 {
11108    return !( *this == other );
11109 }
11110 
11111 const char *
11112 Value::asCString() const {
11113    JSON_ASSERT( type_ == stringValue );
11114    return value_.string_;
11115 }
11116 
11117 
11118 std::string 
11119 Value::asString() const {
11120    switch ( type_ ) {
11121    case nullValue:
11122       return "";
11123    case stringValue:
11124       return value_.string_ ? value_.string_ : "";
11125    case booleanValue:
11126       return value_.bool_ ? "true" : "false";
11127    case intValue:
11128    case uintValue:
11129    case realValue:
11130    case arrayValue:
11131    case objectValue:
11132       JSON_FAIL_MESSAGE( "Type is not convertible to string" );
11133    default:
11134       JSON_ASSERT_UNREACHABLE;
11135    }
11136    return ""; // unreachable
11137 }
11138 
11139 # ifdef JSON_USE_CPPTL
11140 CppTL::ConstString 
11141 Value::asConstString() const
11142 {
11143    return CppTL::ConstString( asString().c_str() );
11144 }
11145 # endif
11146 
11147 
11148 Value::Int 
11149 Value::asInt() const {
11150    switch ( type_ )
11151    {
11152    case nullValue:
11153       return 0;
11154    case intValue:
11155       JSON_ASSERT_MESSAGE( value_.int_ >= minInt  &&  value_.int_ <= maxInt, "unsigned integer out of signed int range" );
11156       return Int(value_.int_);
11157    case uintValue:
11158       JSON_ASSERT_MESSAGE( value_.uint_ <= UInt(maxInt), "unsigned integer out of signed int range" );
11159       return Int(value_.uint_);
11160    case realValue:
11161       JSON_ASSERT_MESSAGE( value_.real_ >= minInt  &&  value_.real_ <= maxInt, "Real out of signed integer range" );
11162       return Int( value_.real_ );
11163    case booleanValue:
11164       return value_.bool_ ? 1 : 0;
11165    case stringValue:
11166    case arrayValue:
11167    case objectValue:
11168       JSON_FAIL_MESSAGE( "Type is not convertible to int" );
11169    default:
11170       JSON_ASSERT_UNREACHABLE;
11171    }
11172    return 0; // unreachable;
11173 }
11174 
11175 
11176 Value::UInt 
11177 Value::asUInt() const {
11178    switch ( type_ ) {
11179    case nullValue:
11180       return 0;
11181    case intValue:
11182       JSON_ASSERT_MESSAGE( value_.int_ >= 0, "Negative integer can not be converted to unsigned integer" );
11183       JSON_ASSERT_MESSAGE( value_.int_ <= maxUInt, "signed integer out of UInt range" );
11184       return UInt(value_.int_);
11185    case uintValue:
11186       JSON_ASSERT_MESSAGE( value_.uint_ <= maxUInt, "unsigned integer out of UInt range" );
11187       return UInt(value_.uint_);
11188    case realValue:
11189       JSON_ASSERT_MESSAGE( value_.real_ >= 0  &&  value_.real_ <= maxUInt,  "Real out of unsigned integer range" );
11190       return UInt( value_.real_ );
11191    case booleanValue:
11192       return value_.bool_ ? 1 : 0;
11193    case stringValue:
11194    case arrayValue:
11195    case objectValue:
11196       JSON_FAIL_MESSAGE( "Type is not convertible to uint" );
11197    default:
11198       JSON_ASSERT_UNREACHABLE;
11199    }
11200    return 0; // unreachable;
11201 }

11204 # if defined(JSON_HAS_INT64)
11205 
11206 Value::Int64
11207 Value::asInt64() const {
11208    switch ( type_ ) {
11209    case nullValue:
11210       return 0;
11211    case intValue:
11212       return value_.int_;
11213    case uintValue:
11214       JSON_ASSERT_MESSAGE( value_.uint_ <= UInt64(maxInt64), "unsigned integer out of Int64 range" );
11215       return value_.uint_;
11216    case realValue:
11217       JSON_ASSERT_MESSAGE( value_.real_ >= minInt64  &&  value_.real_ <= maxInt64, "Real out of Int64 range" );
11218       return Int( value_.real_ );
11219    case booleanValue:
11220       return value_.bool_ ? 1 : 0;
11221    case stringValue:
11222    case arrayValue:
11223    case objectValue:
11224       JSON_FAIL_MESSAGE( "Type is not convertible to Int64" );
11225    default:
11226       JSON_ASSERT_UNREACHABLE;
11227    }
11228    return 0; // unreachable;
11229 }

11231 
11232 Value::UInt64
11233 Value::asUInt64() const {
11234    switch ( type_ ) {
11235    case nullValue:
11236       return 0;
11237    case intValue:
11238       JSON_ASSERT_MESSAGE( value_.int_ >= 0, "Negative integer can not be converted to UInt64" );
11239       return value_.int_;
11240    case uintValue:
11241       return value_.uint_;
11242    case realValue:
11243       JSON_ASSERT_MESSAGE( value_.real_ >= 0  &&  value_.real_ <= maxUInt64,  "Real out of UInt64 range" );
11244       return UInt( value_.real_ );
11245    case booleanValue:
11246       return value_.bool_ ? 1 : 0;
11247    case stringValue:
11248    case arrayValue:
11249    case objectValue:
11250       JSON_FAIL_MESSAGE( "Type is not convertible to UInt64" );
11251    default:
11252       JSON_ASSERT_UNREACHABLE;
11253    }
11254    return 0; // unreachable;
11255 }

11278 
11279 double 
11280 Value::asDouble() const {
11281    switch ( type_ ) {
11282    case nullValue:
11283       return 0.0;
11284    case intValue:
11285       return static_cast<double>( value_.int_ );
11286    case uintValue:
11287 #if !defined(JSON_USE_INT64_DOUBLE_CONVERSION)
11288       return static_cast<double>( value_.uint_ );
11289 #else // if !defined(JSON_USE_INT64_DOUBLE_CONVERSION)
11290       return static_cast<double>( Int(value_.uint_/2) ) * 2 + Int(value_.uint_ & 1);
11291 #endif // if !defined(JSON_USE_INT64_DOUBLE_CONVERSION)
11292    case realValue:
11293       return value_.real_;
11294    case booleanValue:
11295       return value_.bool_ ? 1.0 : 0.0;
11296    case stringValue:
11297    case arrayValue:
11298    case objectValue:
11299       JSON_FAIL_MESSAGE( "Type is not convertible to double" );
11300    default:
11301       JSON_ASSERT_UNREACHABLE;
11302    }
11303    return 0; // unreachable;
11304 }
11305 
11306 float
11307 Value::asFloat() const {
11308    switch ( type_ ) {
11309    case nullValue:
11310       return 0.0f;
11311    case intValue:
11312       return static_cast<float>( value_.int_ );
11313    case uintValue:
11314 #if !defined(JSON_USE_INT64_DOUBLE_CONVERSION)
11315       return static_cast<float>( value_.uint_ );
11316 #else // if !defined(JSON_USE_INT64_DOUBLE_CONVERSION)
11317       return static_cast<float>( Int(value_.uint_/2) ) * 2 + Int(value_.uint_ & 1);
11318 #endif // if !defined(JSON_USE_INT64_DOUBLE_CONVERSION)
11319    case realValue:
11320       return static_cast<float>( value_.real_ );
11321    case booleanValue:
11322       return value_.bool_ ? 1.0f : 0.0f;
11323    case stringValue:
11324    case arrayValue:
11325    case objectValue:
11326       JSON_FAIL_MESSAGE( "Type is not convertible to float" );
11327    default:
11328       JSON_ASSERT_UNREACHABLE;
11329    }
11330    return 0.0f; // unreachable;
11331 }
11332 
11333 bool 
11334 Value::asBool() const {
11335    switch ( type_ ) {
11336    case nullValue:
11337       return false;
11338    case intValue:
11339    case uintValue:
11340       return value_.int_ != 0;
11341    case realValue:
11342       return value_.real_ != 0.0;
11343    case booleanValue:
11344       return value_.bool_;
11345    case stringValue:
11346       return value_.string_  &&  value_.string_[0] != 0;
11347    case arrayValue:
11348    case objectValue:
11349       return value_.map_->size() != 0;
11350    default:
11351       JSON_ASSERT_UNREACHABLE;
11352    }
11353    return false; // unreachable;
11354 }
11355 
11356 
11357 bool 
11358 Value::isConvertibleTo( ValueType other ) const {
11359    switch ( type_ ) {
11360    case nullValue:
11361       return true;
11362    case intValue:
11363       return ( other == nullValue  &&  value_.int_ == 0 )
11364              || other == intValue
11365              || ( other == uintValue  && value_.int_ >= 0 )
11366              || other == realValue
11367              || other == stringValue
11368              || other == booleanValue;
11369    case uintValue:
11370       return ( other == nullValue  &&  value_.uint_ == 0 )
11371              || ( other == intValue  && value_.uint_ <= (unsigned)maxInt )
11372              || other == uintValue
11373              || other == realValue
11374              || other == stringValue
11375              || other == booleanValue;
11376    case realValue:
11377       return ( other == nullValue  &&  value_.real_ == 0.0 )
11378              || ( other == intValue  &&  value_.real_ >= minInt  &&  value_.real_ <= maxInt )
11379              || ( other == uintValue  &&  value_.real_ >= 0  &&  value_.real_ <= maxUInt )
11380              || other == realValue
11381              || other == stringValue
11382              || other == booleanValue;
11383    case booleanValue:
11384       return ( other == nullValue  &&  value_.bool_ == false )
11385              || other == intValue
11386              || other == uintValue
11387              || other == realValue
11388              || other == stringValue
11389              || other == booleanValue;
11390    case stringValue:
11391       return other == stringValue
11392              || ( other == nullValue  &&  (!value_.string_  ||  value_.string_[0] == 0) );
11393    case arrayValue:
11394       return other == arrayValue
11395              ||  ( other == nullValue  &&  value_.map_->size() == 0 );
11396    case objectValue:
11397       return other == objectValue
11398              ||  ( other == nullValue  &&  value_.map_->size() == 0 );
11399    default:
11400       JSON_ASSERT_UNREACHABLE;
11401    }
11402    return false; // unreachable;
11403 }
11404 
11405 
11406 /// Number of values in array or object
11407 ArrayIndex 
11408 Value::size() const {
11409    switch ( type_ ) {
11410    case nullValue:
11411    case intValue:
11412    case uintValue:
11413    case realValue:
11414    case booleanValue:
11415    case stringValue:
11416       return 0;
11417 #ifndef JSON_VALUE_USE_INTERNAL_MAP
11418    case arrayValue:  // size of the array is highest index + 1
11419       if ( !value_.map_->empty() ) {
11420          ObjectValues::const_iterator itLast = value_.map_->end();
11421          --itLast;
11422          return (*itLast).first.index()+1;
11423       }
11424       return 0;
11425    case objectValue:
11426       return ArrayIndex( value_.map_->size() );
11427 #else
11428    case arrayValue:
11429       return Int( value_.array_->size() );
11430    case objectValue:
11431       return Int( value_.map_->size() );
11432 #endif
11433    default:
11434       JSON_ASSERT_UNREACHABLE;
11435    }
11436    return 0; // unreachable;
11437 }
11438 
11439 
11440 bool 
11441 Value::empty() const {
11442    if ( isNull() || isArray() || isObject() )
11443       return size() == 0u;
11444    else
11445       return false;
11446 }

11454 
11455 void 
11456 Value::clear() {
11457    JSON_ASSERT( type_ == nullValue  ||  type_ == arrayValue  || type_ == objectValue );
11458 
11459    switch ( type_ )
11460    {
11461 #ifndef JSON_VALUE_USE_INTERNAL_MAP
11462    case arrayValue:
11463    case objectValue:
11464       value_.map_->clear();
11465       break;
11466 #else
11467    case arrayValue:
11468       value_.array_->clear();
11469       break;
11470    case objectValue:
11471       value_.map_->clear();
11472       break;
11473 #endif
11474    default:
11475       break;
11476    }
11477 }
11478 
11479 void 
11480 Value::resize( ArrayIndex newSize ) {
11481    JSON_ASSERT( type_ == nullValue  ||  type_ == arrayValue );
11482    if ( type_ == nullValue )
11483       *this = Value( arrayValue );
11484 #ifndef JSON_VALUE_USE_INTERNAL_MAP
11485    ArrayIndex oldSize = size();
11486    if ( newSize == 0 )
11487       clear();
11488    else if ( newSize > oldSize )
11489       (*this)[ newSize - 1 ];
11490    else {
11491       for ( ArrayIndex index = newSize; index < oldSize; ++index )
11492       {
11493          value_.map_->erase( index );
11494       }
11495       assert( size() == newSize );
11496    }
11497 #else
11498    value_.array_->resize( newSize );
11499 #endif
11500 }
11501 
11502 
11503 Value &
11504 Value::operator[]( ArrayIndex index ) {
11505    JSON_ASSERT( type_ == nullValue  ||  type_ == arrayValue );
11506    if ( type_ == nullValue )
11507       *this = Value( arrayValue );
11508 #ifndef JSON_VALUE_USE_INTERNAL_MAP
11509    CZString key( index );
11510    ObjectValues::iterator it = value_.map_->lower_bound( key );
11511    if ( it != value_.map_->end()  &&  (*it).first == key )
11512       return (*it).second;
11513 
11514    ObjectValues::value_type defaultValue( key, null );
11515    it = value_.map_->insert( it, defaultValue );
11516    return (*it).second;
11517 #else
11518    return value_.array_->resolveReference( index );
11519 #endif
11520 }

11525    JSON_ASSERT( index >= 0 );
11526    return (*this)[ ArrayIndex(index) ];
11527 }

11529 
11530 const Value &
11531 Value::operator[]( ArrayIndex index ) const {
11532    JSON_ASSERT( type_ == nullValue  ||  type_ == arrayValue );
11533    if ( type_ == nullValue )
11534       return null;
11535 #ifndef JSON_VALUE_USE_INTERNAL_MAP
11536    CZString key( index );
11537    ObjectValues::const_iterator it = value_.map_->find( key );
11538    if ( it == value_.map_->end() )
11539       return null;
11540    return (*it).second;
11541 #else
11542    Value *value = value_.array_->find( index );
11543    return value ? *value : null;
11544 #endif
11545 }

11551    return (*this)[ ArrayIndex(index) ];

11560 
11561 Value &
11562 Value::resolveReference( const char *key, 
11563                          bool isStatic ) {
11564    JSON_ASSERT( type_ == nullValue  ||  type_ == objectValue );
11565    if ( type_ == nullValue )
11566       *this = Value( objectValue );
11567 #ifndef JSON_VALUE_USE_INTERNAL_MAP
11568    CZString actualKey( key, isStatic ? CZString::noDuplication 
11569                                      : CZString::duplicateOnCopy );
11570    ObjectValues::iterator it = value_.map_->lower_bound( actualKey );
11571    if ( it != value_.map_->end()  &&  (*it).first == actualKey )
11572       return (*it).second;
11573 
11574    ObjectValues::value_type defaultValue( actualKey, null );
11575    it = value_.map_->insert( it, defaultValue );
11576    Value &value = (*it).second;
11577    return value;
11578 #else
11579    return value_.map_->resolveReference( key, isStatic );
11580 #endif
11581 }

11668 Value
11669 Value::removeMember( const char* key ) {
11670    JSON_ASSERT( type_ == nullValue  ||  type_ == objectValue );
11671    if ( type_ == nullValue )
11672       return null;
11673 #ifndef JSON_VALUE_USE_INTERNAL_MAP
11674    CZString actualKey( key, CZString::noDuplication );
11675    ObjectValues::iterator it = value_.map_->find( actualKey );
11676    if ( it == value_.map_->end() )
11677       return null;
11678    Value old(it->second);
11679    value_.map_->erase(it);
11680    return old;
11681 #else
11682    Value *value = value_.map_->find( key );
11683    if (value){
11684       Value old(*value);
11685       value_.map_.remove( key );
11686       return old;
11687    } else {
11688       return null;
11689    }
11690 #endif
11691 }

11725 
11726 Value::Members 
11727 Value::getMemberNames() const {
11728    JSON_ASSERT( type_ == nullValue  ||  type_ == objectValue );
11729    if ( type_ == nullValue )
11730        return Value::Members();
11731    Members members;
11732    members.reserve( value_.map_->size() );
11733 #ifndef JSON_VALUE_USE_INTERNAL_MAP
11734    ObjectValues::const_iterator it = value_.map_->begin();
11735    ObjectValues::const_iterator itEnd = value_.map_->end();
11736    for ( ; it != itEnd; ++it )
11737       members.push_back( std::string( (*it).first.c_str() ) );
11738 #else
11739    ValueInternalMap::IteratorState it;
11740    ValueInternalMap::IteratorState itEnd;
11741    value_.map_->makeBeginIterator( it );
11742    value_.map_->makeEndIterator( itEnd );
11743    for ( ; !ValueInternalMap::equals( it, itEnd ); ValueInternalMap::increment(it) )
11744       members.push_back( std::string( ValueInternalMap::key( it ) ) );
11745 #endif
11746    return members;
11747 }

11749 //# ifdef JSON_USE_CPPTL
11750 //EnumMemberNames
11751 //Value::enumMemberNames() const
11752 //{
11753 //   if ( type_ == objectValue )
11754 //   {
11755 //      return CppTL::Enum::any(  CppTL::Enum::transform(
11756 //         CppTL::Enum::keys( *(value_.map_), CppTL::Type<const CZString &>() ),
11757 //         MemberNamesTransform() ) );
11758 //   }
11759 //   return EnumMemberNames();
11760 //}
11761 //
11762 //
11763 //EnumValues 
11764 //Value::enumValues() const
11765 //{
11766 //   if ( type_ == objectValue  ||  type_ == arrayValue )
11767 //      return CppTL::Enum::anyValues( *(value_.map_), 
11768 //                                     CppTL::Type<const Value &>() );
11769 //   return EnumValues();
11770 //}
11771 //
11772 //# endif

11871 
11872 
11873 Value::const_iterator 
11874 Value::begin() const {
11875    switch ( type_ ) {
11876 #ifdef JSON_VALUE_USE_INTERNAL_MAP
11877    case arrayValue:
11878       if ( value_.array_ ) {
11879          ValueInternalArray::IteratorState it;
11880          value_.array_->makeBeginIterator( it );
11881          return const_iterator( it );
11882       }
11883       break;
11884    case objectValue:
11885       if ( value_.map_ ) {
11886          ValueInternalMap::IteratorState it;
11887          value_.map_->makeBeginIterator( it );
11888          return const_iterator( it );
11889       }
11890       break;
11891 #else
11892    case arrayValue:
11893    case objectValue:
11894       if ( value_.map_ )
11895          return const_iterator( value_.map_->begin() );
11896       break;
11897 #endif
11898    default:
11899       break;
11900    }
11901    return const_iterator();
11902 }
11903 
11904 Value::const_iterator 
11905 Value::end() const {
11906    switch ( type_ ) {
11907 #ifdef JSON_VALUE_USE_INTERNAL_MAP
11908    case arrayValue:
11909       if ( value_.array_ ) {
11910          ValueInternalArray::IteratorState it;
11911          value_.array_->makeEndIterator( it );
11912          return const_iterator( it );
11913       }
11914       break;
11915    case objectValue:
11916       if ( value_.map_ ) {
11917          ValueInternalMap::IteratorState it;
11918          value_.map_->makeEndIterator( it );
11919          return const_iterator( it );
11920       }
11921       break;
11922 #else
11923    case arrayValue:
11924    case objectValue:
11925       if ( value_.map_ )
11926          return const_iterator( value_.map_->end() );
11927       break;
11928 #endif
11929    default:
11930       break;
11931    }
11932    return const_iterator();
11933 }
11934 
11935 
11936 Value::iterator 
11937 Value::begin() {
11938    switch ( type_ ) {
11939 #ifdef JSON_VALUE_USE_INTERNAL_MAP
11940    case arrayValue:
11941       if ( value_.array_ ) {
11942          ValueInternalArray::IteratorState it;
11943          value_.array_->makeBeginIterator( it );
11944          return iterator( it );
11945       }
11946       break;
11947    case objectValue:
11948       if ( value_.map_ ) {
11949          ValueInternalMap::IteratorState it;
11950          value_.map_->makeBeginIterator( it );
11951          return iterator( it );
11952       }
11953       break;
11954 #else
11955    case arrayValue:
11956    case objectValue:
11957       if ( value_.map_ )
11958          return iterator( value_.map_->begin() );
11959       break;
11960 #endif
11961    default:
11962       break;
11963    }
11964    return iterator();
11965 }
11966 
11967 Value::iterator 
11968 Value::end() {
11969    switch ( type_ ) {
11970 #ifdef JSON_VALUE_USE_INTERNAL_MAP
11971    case arrayValue:
11972       if ( value_.array_ ) {
11973          ValueInternalArray::IteratorState it;
11974          value_.array_->makeEndIterator( it );
11975          return iterator( it );
11976       }
11977       break;
11978    case objectValue:
11979       if ( value_.map_ ) {
11980          ValueInternalMap::IteratorState it;
11981          value_.map_->makeEndIterator( it );
11982          return iterator( it );
11983       }
11984       break;
11985 #else
11986    case arrayValue:
11987    case objectValue:
11988       if ( value_.map_ )
11989          return iterator( value_.map_->end() );
11990       break;
11991 #endif
11992    default:
11993       break;
11994    }
11995    return iterator();
11996 }

12024 // class Path
12025 // //////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
12026 
12027 Path::Path( const std::string &path,
12028             const PathArgument &a1,
12029             const PathArgument &a2,
12030             const PathArgument &a3,
12031             const PathArgument &a4,
12032             const PathArgument &a5 ) {
12033    InArgs in;
12034    in.push_back( &a1 );
12035    in.push_back( &a2 );
12036    in.push_back( &a3 );
12037    in.push_back( &a4 );
12038    in.push_back( &a5 );
12039    makePath( path, in );
12040 }
12041 
12042 
12043 void 
12044 Path::makePath( const std::string &path,
12045                 const InArgs &in ) {
12046    const char *current = path.c_str();
12047    const char *end = current + path.length();
12048    InArgs::const_iterator itInArg = in.begin();
12049    while ( current != end ) {
12050       if ( *current == '[' ) {
12051          ++current;
12052          if ( *current == '%' )
12053             addPathInArg( path, in, itInArg, PathArgument::kindIndex );
12054          else {
12055             ArrayIndex index = 0;
12056             for ( ; current != end && *current >= '0'  &&  *current <= '9'; ++current )
12057                index = index * 10 + ArrayIndex(*current - '0');
12058             args_.push_back( index );
12059          }
12060          if ( current == end  ||  *current++ != ']' )
12061             invalidPath( path, int(current - path.c_str()) );
12062       }
12063       else if ( *current == '%' ) {
12064          addPathInArg( path, in, itInArg, PathArgument::kindKey );
12065          ++current;
12066       }
12067       else if ( *current == '.' ) {
12068          ++current;
12069       } else {
12070          const char *beginName = current;
12071          while ( current != end  &&  !strchr( "[.", *current ) )
12072             ++current;
12073          args_.push_back( std::string( beginName, current ) );
12074       }
12075    }
12076 }
12077 
12078 
12079 void 
12080 Path::addPathInArg( const std::string &path, 
12081                     const InArgs &in, 
12082                     InArgs::const_iterator &itInArg, 
12083                     PathArgument::Kind kind ) {
12084    if ( itInArg == in.end() ) {
12085       // Error: missing argument %d
12086    } else if ( (*itInArg)->kind_ != kind ) {
12087       // Error: bad argument type
12088    } else {
12089       args_.push_back( **itInArg );
12090    }
12091 }
12092 
12093 
12094 void 
12095 Path::invalidPath( const std::string &path, 
12096                    int location ) {
12097    // Error: invalid path.
12098 }
12099 
12100 
12101 const Value &
12102 Path::resolve( const Value &root ) const {
12103    const Value *node = &root;
12104    for ( Args::const_iterator it = args_.begin(); it != args_.end(); ++it ) {
12105       const PathArgument &arg = *it;
12106       if ( arg.kind_ == PathArgument::kindIndex ) {
12107          if ( !node->isArray()  ||  node->isValidIndex( arg.index_ ) ) {
12108             // Error: unable to resolve path (array value expected at position...
12109          }
12110          node = &((*node)[arg.index_]);
12111       } else if ( arg.kind_ == PathArgument::kindKey ) {
12112          if ( !node->isObject() ) {
12113             // Error: unable to resolve path (object value expected at position...)
12114          }
12115          node = &((*node)[arg.key_]);
12116          if ( node == &Value::null ) {
12117             // Error: unable to resolve path (object has no member named '' at position...)
12118          }
12119       }
12120    }
12121    return *node;
12122 }
12123 
12124 
12125 Value 
12126 Path::resolve( const Value &root, 
12127                const Value &defaultValue ) const {
12128    const Value *node = &root;
12129    for ( Args::const_iterator it = args_.begin(); it != args_.end(); ++it ) {
12130       const PathArgument &arg = *it;
12131       if ( arg.kind_ == PathArgument::kindIndex ) {
12132          if ( !node->isArray()  ||  node->isValidIndex( arg.index_ ) )
12133             return defaultValue;
12134          node = &((*node)[arg.index_]);
12135       } else if ( arg.kind_ == PathArgument::kindKey ) {
12136          if ( !node->isObject() )
12137             return defaultValue;
12138          node = &((*node)[arg.key_]);
12139          if ( node == &Value::null )
12140             return defaultValue;
12141       }
12142    }
12143    return *node;
12144 }
12145 
12146 
12147 Value &
12148 Path::make( Value &root ) const {
12149    Value *node = &root;
12150    for ( Args::const_iterator it = args_.begin(); it != args_.end(); ++it ) {
12151       const PathArgument &arg = *it;
12152       if ( arg.kind_ == PathArgument::kindIndex ) {
12153          if ( !node->isArray() ) {
12154             // Error: node is not an array at position ...
12155          }
12156          node = &((*node)[arg.index_]);
12157       } else if ( arg.kind_ == PathArgument::kindKey ) {
12158          if ( !node->isObject() ) {
12159             // Error: node is not an object at position...
12160          }
12161          node = &((*node)[arg.key_]);
12162       }
12163    }
12164    return *node;
12165 }

12206 static bool containsControlCharacter( const char* str ) {
12207    while ( *str ) {
12208       if ( isControlCharacter( *(str++) ) )
12209          return true;
12210    }
12211    return false;
12212 }
12213 
12214 
12215 std::string valueToString( LargestInt value ) {
12216    UIntToStringBuffer buffer;
12217    char *current = buffer + sizeof(buffer);
12218    bool isNegative = value < 0;
12219    if ( isNegative )
12220       value = -value;
12221    uintToString( LargestUInt(value), current );
12222    if ( isNegative )
12223       *--current = '-';
12224    assert( current >= buffer );
12225    return current;
12226 }
12227 
12228 
12229 std::string valueToString( LargestUInt value ) {
12230    UIntToStringBuffer buffer;
12231    char *current = buffer + sizeof(buffer);
12232    uintToString( value, current );
12233    assert( current >= buffer );
12234    return current;
12235 }

12239 std::string valueToString( Int value )
12240 {
12241    return valueToString( LargestInt(value) );
12242 }
12243 
12244 
12245 std::string valueToString( UInt value ) {
12246    return valueToString( LargestUInt(value) );
12247 }
12248 
12249 #endif // # if defined(JSON_HAS_INT64)
12250 
12251 
12252 std::string valueToString( double value ) {
12253    char buffer[32];
12254 #if defined(_MSC_VER) && defined(__STDC_SECURE_LIB__) // Use secure version with visual studio 2005 to avoid warning. 
12255    sprintf_s(buffer, sizeof(buffer), "%#.16g", value); 
12256 #else   
12257    sprintf(buffer, "%#.16g", value); 
12258 #endif
12259    char* ch = buffer + strlen(buffer) - 1;
12260    if (*ch != '0') return buffer; // nothing to truncate, so save time
12261    while(ch > buffer && *ch == '0'){
12262      --ch;
12263    }
12264    char* last_nonzero = ch;
12265    while(ch >= buffer){
12266      switch(*ch){
12267      case '0':
12268      case '1':
12269      case '2':
12270      case '3':
12271      case '4':
12272      case '5':
12273      case '6':
12274      case '7':
12275      case '8':
12276      case '9':
12277        --ch;
12278        continue;
12279      case '.':
12280        // Truncate zeroes to save bytes in output, but keep one.
12281        *(last_nonzero+2) = '\0';
12282        return buffer;
12283      default:
12284        return buffer;
12285      }
12286    }
12287    return buffer;
12288 }
12289 
12290 
12291 std::string valueToString( bool value ) {
12292    return value ? "true" : "false";
12293 }
12294 
12295 std::string valueToQuotedString( const char *value ) {
12296    // Not sure how to handle unicode...
12297    if (strpbrk(value, "\"\\\b\f\n\r\t") == NULL && !containsControlCharacter( value ))
12298       return std::string("\"") + value + "\"";
12299    // We have to walk value and escape any special characters.
12300    // Appending to std::string is not efficient, but this should be rare.
12301    // (Note: forward slashes are *not* rare, but I am not escaping them.)
12302    std::string::size_type maxsize = strlen(value)*2 + 3; // allescaped+quotes+NULL
12303    std::string result;
12304    result.reserve(maxsize); // to avoid lots of mallocs
12305    result += "\"";
12306    for (const char* c=value; *c != 0; ++c) {
12307       switch(*c) {
12308          case '\"':
12309             result += "\\\"";
12310             break;
12311          case '\\':
12312             result += "\\\\";
12313             break;
12314          case '\b':
12315             result += "\\b";
12316             break;
12317          case '\f':
12318             result += "\\f";
12319             break;
12320          case '\n':
12321             result += "\\n";
12322             break;
12323          case '\r':
12324             result += "\\r";
12325             break;
12326          case '\t':
12327             result += "\\t";
12328             break;
12329          //case '/':
12330             // Even though \/ is considered a legal escape in JSON, a bare
12331             // slash is also legal, so I see no reason to escape it.
12332             // (I hope I am not misunderstanding something.
12333             // blep notes: actually escaping \/ may be useful in javascript to avoid </ 
12334             // sequence.
12335             // Should add a flag to allow this compatibility mode and prevent this 
12336             // sequence from occurring.
12337          default:
12338             if ( isControlCharacter( *c ) ) {
12339                std::ostringstream oss;
12340                oss << "\\u" << std::hex << std::uppercase << std::setfill('0') << std::setw(4) << static_cast<int>(*c);
12341                result += oss.str();
12342             } else {
12343                result += *c;
12344             }
12345             break;
12346       }
12347    }
12348    result += "\"";
12349    return result;
12350 }

12379 
12380 
12381 void 
12382 FastWriter::writeValue( const Value &value ) {
12383    switch ( value.type() ) {
12384    case nullValue:
12385       document_ += "null";
12386       break;
12387    case intValue:
12388       document_ += valueToString( value.asLargestInt() );
12389       break;
12390    case uintValue:
12391       document_ += valueToString( value.asLargestUInt() );
12392       break;
12393    case realValue:
12394       document_ += valueToString( value.asDouble() );
12395       break;
12396    case stringValue:
12397       document_ += valueToQuotedString( value.asCString() );
12398       break;
12399    case booleanValue:
12400       document_ += valueToString( value.asBool() );
12401       break;
12402    case arrayValue: {
12403          document_ += "[";
12404          int size = value.size();
12405          for ( int index =0; index < size; ++index ) {
12406             if ( index > 0 )
12407                document_ += ",";
12408             writeValue( value[index] );
12409          }
12410          document_ += "]";
12411       }
12412       break;
12413    case objectValue: {
12414          Value::Members members( value.getMemberNames() );
12415          document_ += "{";
12416          for ( Value::Members::iterator it = members.begin(); 
12417                it != members.end(); 
12418                ++it ) {
12419             const std::string &name = *it;
12420             if ( it != members.begin() )
12421                document_ += ",";
12422             document_ += valueToQuotedString( name.c_str() );
12423             document_ += yamlCompatiblityEnabled_ ? ": " 
12424                                                   : ":";
12425             writeValue( value[name] );
12426          }
12427          document_ += "}";
12428       }
12429       break;
12430    }
12431 }

12435 // //////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
12436 
12437 StyledWriter::StyledWriter()
12438    : rightMargin_( 74 )
12439    , indentSize_( 3 ) {
12440 }
12441 
12442 
12443 std::string 
12444 StyledWriter::write( const Value &root ) {
12445    document_ = "";
12446    addChildValues_ = false;
12447    indentString_ = "";
12448    writeCommentBeforeValue( root );
12449    writeValue( root );
12450    writeCommentAfterValueOnSameLine( root );
12451    document_ += "\n";
12452    return document_;
12453 }
12454 
12455 
12456 void 
12457 StyledWriter::writeValue( const Value &value ) {
12458    switch ( value.type() ) {
12459    case nullValue:
12460       pushValue( "null" );
12461       break;
12462    case intValue:
12463       pushValue( valueToString( value.asLargestInt() ) );
12464       break;
12465    case uintValue:
12466       pushValue( valueToString( value.asLargestUInt() ) );
12467       break;
12468    case realValue:
12469       pushValue( valueToString( value.asDouble() ) );
12470       break;
12471    case stringValue:
12472       pushValue( valueToQuotedString( value.asCString() ) );
12473       break;
12474    case booleanValue:
12475       pushValue( valueToString( value.asBool() ) );
12476       break;
12477    case arrayValue:
12478       writeArrayValue( value);
12479       break;
12480    case objectValue:
12481       {
12482          Value::Members members( value.getMemberNames() );
12483          if ( members.empty() )
12484             pushValue( "{}" );
12485          else {
12486             writeWithIndent( "{" );
12487             indent();
12488             Value::Members::iterator it = members.begin();
12489             for (;;) {
12490                const std::string &name = *it;
12491                const Value &childValue = value[name];
12492                writeCommentBeforeValue( childValue );
12493                writeWithIndent( valueToQuotedString( name.c_str() ) );
12494                document_ += " : ";
12495                writeValue( childValue );
12496                if ( ++it == members.end() ) {
12497                   writeCommentAfterValueOnSameLine( childValue );
12498                   break;
12499                }
12500                document_ += ",";
12501                writeCommentAfterValueOnSameLine( childValue );
12502             }
12503             unindent();
12504             writeWithIndent( "}" );
12505          }
12506       }
12507       break;
12508    }
12509 }
12510 
12511 
12512 void 
12513 StyledWriter::writeArrayValue( const Value &value ) {
12514    unsigned size = value.size();
12515    if ( size == 0 )
12516       pushValue( "[]" );
12517    else {
12518       bool isArrayMultiLine = isMultineArray( value );
12519       if ( isArrayMultiLine ) {
12520          writeWithIndent( "[" );
12521          indent();
12522          bool hasChildValue = !childValues_.empty();
12523          unsigned index =0;
12524          for (;;) {
12525             const Value &childValue = value[index];
12526             writeCommentBeforeValue( childValue );
12527             if ( hasChildValue )
12528                writeWithIndent( childValues_[index] );
12529             else {
12530                writeIndent();
12531                writeValue( childValue );
12532             }
12533             if ( ++index == size ) {
12534                writeCommentAfterValueOnSameLine( childValue );
12535                break;
12536             }
12537             document_ += ",";
12538             writeCommentAfterValueOnSameLine( childValue );
12539          }
12540          unindent();
12541          writeWithIndent( "]" );
12542       } else { // output on a single line
12543          assert( childValues_.size() == size );
12544          document_ += "[ ";
12545          for ( unsigned index =0; index < size; ++index ) {
12546             if ( index > 0 )
12547                document_ += ", ";
12548             document_ += childValues_[index];
12549          }
12550          document_ += " ]";
12551       }
12552    }
12553 }
12554 
12555 
12556 bool 
12557 StyledWriter::isMultineArray( const Value &value ) {
12558    int size = value.size();
12559    bool isMultiLine = size*3 >= rightMargin_ ;
12560    childValues_.clear();
12561    for ( int index =0; index < size  &&  !isMultiLine; ++index ) {
12562       const Value &childValue = value[index];
12563       isMultiLine = isMultiLine  ||
12564                      ( (childValue.isArray()  ||  childValue.isObject())  &&  
12565                         childValue.size() > 0 );
12566    }
12567    if ( !isMultiLine ) { // check if line length > max line length
12568       childValues_.reserve( size );
12569       addChildValues_ = true;
12570       int lineLength = 4 + (size-1)*2; // '[ ' + ', '*n + ' ]'
12571       for ( int index =0; index < size  &&  !isMultiLine; ++index ) {
12572          writeValue( value[index] );
12573          lineLength += int( childValues_[index].length() );
12574          isMultiLine = isMultiLine  &&  hasCommentForValue( value[index] );
12575       }
12576       addChildValues_ = false;
12577       isMultiLine = isMultiLine  ||  lineLength >= rightMargin_;
12578    }
12579    return isMultiLine;
12580 }
12581 
12582 
12583 void 
12584 StyledWriter::pushValue( const std::string &value ) {
12585    if ( addChildValues_ )
12586       childValues_.push_back( value );
12587    else
12588       document_ += value;
12589 }
12590 
12591 
12592 void 
12593 StyledWriter::writeIndent() {
12594    if ( !document_.empty() )
12595    {
12596       char last = document_[document_.length()-1];
12597       if ( last == ' ' )     // already indented
12598          return;
12599       if ( last != '\n' )    // Comments may add new-line
12600          document_ += '\n';
12601    }
12602    document_ += indentString_;
12603 }
12604 
12605 
12606 void 
12607 StyledWriter::writeWithIndent( const std::string &value ) {
12608    writeIndent();
12609    document_ += value;
12610 }
12611 
12612 
12613 void 
12614 StyledWriter::indent() {
12615    indentString_ += std::string( indentSize_, ' ' );
12616 }
12617 
12618 
12619 void 
12620 StyledWriter::unindent() {
12621    assert( int(indentString_.size()) >= indentSize_ );
12622    indentString_.resize( indentString_.size() - indentSize_ );
12623 }
12624 
12625 
12626 void 
12627 StyledWriter::writeCommentBeforeValue( const Value &root ) {
12628    if ( !root.hasComment( commentBefore ) )
12629       return;
12630    document_ += normalizeEOL( root.getComment( commentBefore ) );
12631    document_ += "\n";
12632 }
12633 
12634 
12635 void 
12636 StyledWriter::writeCommentAfterValueOnSameLine( const Value &root ) {
12637    if ( root.hasComment( commentAfterOnSameLine ) )
12638       document_ += " " + normalizeEOL( root.getComment( commentAfterOnSameLine ) );
12639 
12640    if ( root.hasComment( commentAfter ) ) {
12641       document_ += "\n";
12642       document_ += normalizeEOL( root.getComment( commentAfter ) );
12643       document_ += "\n";
12644    }
12645 }
12646 
12647 
12648 bool 
12649 StyledWriter::hasCommentForValue( const Value &value ) {
12650    return value.hasComment( commentBefore )
12651           ||  value.hasComment( commentAfterOnSameLine )
12652           ||  value.hasComment( commentAfter );
12653 }
12654 
12655 
12656 std::string 
12657 StyledWriter::normalizeEOL( const std::string &text ) {
12658    std::string normalized;
12659    normalized.reserve( text.length() );
12660    const char *begin = text.c_str();
12661    const char *end = begin + text.length();
12662    const char *current = begin;
12663    while ( current != end ) {
12664       char c = *current++;
12665       if ( c == '\r' ) { // mac or dos EOL
12666          if ( *current == '\n' ) // convert dos EOL
12667             ++current;
12668          normalized += '\n';
12669       } else // handle unix EOL & other char
12670          normalized += c;
12671    }
12672    return normalized;
12673 }
12674 
12675 
12676 // Class StyledStreamWriter
12677 // //////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
12678 
12679 StyledStreamWriter::StyledStreamWriter( std::string indentation )
12680    : document_(NULL)
12681    , rightMargin_( 74 )
12682    , indentation_( indentation ) {
12683 }
12684 
12685 
12686 void
12687 StyledStreamWriter::write( std::ostream &out, const Value &root ) {
12688    document_ = &out;
12689    addChildValues_ = false;
12690    indentString_ = "";
12691    writeCommentBeforeValue( root );
12692    writeValue( root );
12693    writeCommentAfterValueOnSameLine( root );
12694    *document_ << "\n";
12695    document_ = NULL; // Forget the stream, for safety.
12696 }
12697 
12698 
12699 void 
12700 StyledStreamWriter::writeValue( const Value &value ) {
12701    switch ( value.type() ) {
12702    case nullValue:
12703       pushValue( "null" );
12704       break;
12705    case intValue:
12706       pushValue( valueToString( value.asLargestInt() ) );
12707       break;
12708    case uintValue:
12709       pushValue( valueToString( value.asLargestUInt() ) );
12710       break;
12711    case realValue:
12712       pushValue( valueToString( value.asDouble() ) );
12713       break;
12714    case stringValue:
12715       pushValue( valueToQuotedString( value.asCString() ) );
12716       break;
12717    case booleanValue:
12718       pushValue( valueToString( value.asBool() ) );
12719       break;
12720    case arrayValue:
12721       writeArrayValue( value);
12722       break;
12723    case objectValue: {
12724          Value::Members members( value.getMemberNames() );
12725          if ( members.empty() )
12726             pushValue( "{}" );
12727          else {
12728             writeWithIndent( "{" );
12729             indent();
12730             Value::Members::iterator it = members.begin();
12731             for (;;) {
12732                const std::string &name = *it;
12733                const Value &childValue = value[name];
12734                writeCommentBeforeValue( childValue );
12735                writeWithIndent( valueToQuotedString( name.c_str() ) );
12736                *document_ << " : ";
12737                writeValue( childValue );
12738                if ( ++it == members.end() ) {
12739                   writeCommentAfterValueOnSameLine( childValue );
12740                   break;
12741                }
12742                *document_ << ",";
12743                writeCommentAfterValueOnSameLine( childValue );
12744             }
12745             unindent();
12746             writeWithIndent( "}" );
12747          }
12748       }
12749       break;
12750    }
12751 }
12752 
12753 
12754 void 
12755 StyledStreamWriter::writeArrayValue( const Value &value ) {
12756    unsigned size = value.size();
12757    if ( size == 0 )
12758       pushValue( "[]" );
12759    else {
12760       bool isArrayMultiLine = isMultineArray( value );
12761       if ( isArrayMultiLine ) {
12762          writeWithIndent( "[" );
12763          indent();
12764          bool hasChildValue = !childValues_.empty();
12765          unsigned index =0;
12766          for (;;) {
12767             const Value &childValue = value[index];
12768             writeCommentBeforeValue( childValue );
12769             if ( hasChildValue )
12770                writeWithIndent( childValues_[index] );
12771             else {
12772                writeIndent();
12773                writeValue( childValue );
12774             }
12775             if ( ++index == size ) {
12776                writeCommentAfterValueOnSameLine( childValue );
12777                break;
12778             }
12779             *document_ << ",";
12780             writeCommentAfterValueOnSameLine( childValue );
12781          }
12782          unindent();
12783          writeWithIndent( "]" );
12784       }
12785       else { // output on a single line
12786          assert( childValues_.size() == size );
12787          *document_ << "[ ";
12788          for ( unsigned index =0; index < size; ++index ) {
12789             if ( index > 0 )
12790                *document_ << ", ";
12791             *document_ << childValues_[index];
12792          }
12793          *document_ << " ]";
12794       }
12795    }
12796 }
12797 
12798 
12799 bool 
12800 StyledStreamWriter::isMultineArray( const Value &value ) {
12801    int size = value.size();
12802    bool isMultiLine = size*3 >= rightMargin_ ;
12803    childValues_.clear();
12804    for ( int index =0; index < size  &&  !isMultiLine; ++index ) {
12805       const Value &childValue = value[index];
12806       isMultiLine = isMultiLine  ||
12807                      ( (childValue.isArray()  ||  childValue.isObject())  &&  
12808                         childValue.size() > 0 );
12809    }
12810    if ( !isMultiLine ) { // check if line length > max line length
12811       childValues_.reserve( size );
12812       addChildValues_ = true;
12813       int lineLength = 4 + (size-1)*2; // '[ ' + ', '*n + ' ]'
12814       for ( int index =0; index < size  &&  !isMultiLine; ++index ) {
12815          writeValue( value[index] );
12816          lineLength += int( childValues_[index].length() );
12817          isMultiLine = isMultiLine  &&  hasCommentForValue( value[index] );
12818       }
12819       addChildValues_ = false;
12820       isMultiLine = isMultiLine  ||  lineLength >= rightMargin_;
12821    }
12822    return isMultiLine;
12823 }
12824 
12825 
12826 void 
12827 StyledStreamWriter::pushValue( const std::string &value ) {
12828    if ( addChildValues_ )
12829       childValues_.push_back( value );
12830    else
12831       *document_ << value;
12832 }
12833 
12834 
12835 void 
12836 StyledStreamWriter::writeIndent() {
12837   /*
12838     Some comments in this method would have been nice. ;-)
12839 
12840    if ( !document_.empty() )
12841    {
12842       char last = document_[document_.length()-1];
12843       if ( last == ' ' )     // already indented
12844          return;
12845       if ( last != '\n' )    // Comments may add new-line
12846          *document_ << '\n';
12847    }
12848   */
12849    *document_ << '\n' << indentString_;
12850 }
12851 
12852 
12853 void 
12854 StyledStreamWriter::writeWithIndent( const std::string &value ) {
12855    writeIndent();
12856    *document_ << value;
12857 }
12858 
12859 
12860 void 
12861 StyledStreamWriter::indent() {
12862    indentString_ += indentation_;
12863 }
12864 
12865 
12866 void 
12867 StyledStreamWriter::unindent() {
12868    assert( indentString_.size() >= indentation_.size() );
12869    indentString_.resize( indentString_.size() - indentation_.size() );
12870 }
12871 
12872 
12873 void 
12874 StyledStreamWriter::writeCommentBeforeValue( const Value &root ) {
12875    if ( !root.hasComment( commentBefore ) )
12876       return;
12877    *document_ << normalizeEOL( root.getComment( commentBefore ) );
12878    *document_ << "\n";
12879 }
12880 
12881 
12882 void 
12883 StyledStreamWriter::writeCommentAfterValueOnSameLine( const Value &root ) {
12884    if ( root.hasComment( commentAfterOnSameLine ) )
12885       *document_ << " " + normalizeEOL( root.getComment( commentAfterOnSameLine ) );
12886 
12887    if ( root.hasComment( commentAfter ) ) {
12888       *document_ << "\n";
12889       *document_ << normalizeEOL( root.getComment( commentAfter ) );
12890       *document_ << "\n";
12891    }
12892 }
12893 
12894 
12895 bool 
12896 StyledStreamWriter::hasCommentForValue( const Value &value ) {
12897    return value.hasComment( commentBefore )
12898           ||  value.hasComment( commentAfterOnSameLine )
12899           ||  value.hasComment( commentAfter );
12900 }
12901 
12902 
12903 std::string 
12904 StyledStreamWriter::normalizeEOL( const std::string &text ) {
12905    std::string normalized;
12906    normalized.reserve( text.length() );
12907    const char *begin = text.c_str();
12908    const char *end = begin + text.length();
12909    const char *current = begin;
12910    while ( current != end ) {
12911       char c = *current++;
12912       if ( c == '\r' ) { // mac or dos EOL
12913          if ( *current == '\n' ) // convert dos EOL
12914             ++current;
12915          normalized += '\n';
12916       } else // handle unix EOL & other char
12917          normalized += c;
12918    }
12919    return normalized;
12920 }
12921 
12922 
12923 std::ostream& operator<<( std::ostream &sout, const Value &root ) {
12924    Json::StyledStreamWriter writer;
12925    writer.write(sout, root);
12926    return sout;
12927 }

12968 /*** Protected Functions ***/

12970 
12971 double pyne::Material::get_comp_sum() {
12972   // Sums the weights in the composition dictionary
12973   double sum = 0.0;
12974   for (pyne::comp_iter i = comp.begin(); i != comp.end(); i++) {
12975     sum = sum + i->second;
12976   }
12977   return sum;
12978 };
12979 
12980 
12981 
12982 void pyne::Material::norm_comp() {
12983   double sum = get_comp_sum();
12984   if (sum != 1.0 && sum != 0.0) {
12985     for (comp_iter i = comp.begin(); i != comp.end(); i++)
12986       i->second = i->second / sum;
12987   }
12988 
12989   if (mass < 0.0)
12990     mass = sum;
12991 }

12997 
12998 void pyne::Material::_load_comp_protocol0(hid_t db, std::string datapath, int row) {
12999   hid_t matgroup = H5Gopen2(db, datapath.c_str(), H5P_DEFAULT);
13000   hid_t nucset;
13001   double nucvalue;
13002   ssize_t nuckeylen;
13003   std::string nuckey;
13004 
13005   // get the number of members in the material group
13006   H5G_info_t group_info;
13007   H5Gget_info(matgroup, &group_info);
13008   hsize_t matG = group_info.nlinks;
13009 
13010   // Iterate over datasets in the group.
13011   for (int matg = 0; matg < matG; matg++) {
13012     nuckeylen = 1 + H5Lget_name_by_idx(matgroup, ".", H5_INDEX_NAME, H5_ITER_INC, matg,
13013                                         NULL, 0, H5P_DEFAULT);
13014     char * nkey = new char[nuckeylen];
13015     nuckeylen = H5Lget_name_by_idx(matgroup, ".", H5_INDEX_NAME, H5_ITER_INC, matg,
13016                                     nkey, nuckeylen, H5P_DEFAULT);
13017     nuckey = nkey;
13018     nucset = H5Dopen2(matgroup, nkey, H5P_DEFAULT);
13019     nucvalue = h5wrap::get_array_index<double>(nucset, row);
13020 
13021     if (nuckey == "Mass" || nuckey == "MASS" || nuckey == "mass")
13022       mass = nucvalue;
13023     else
13024       comp[pyne::nucname::id(nuckey)] = nucvalue;
13025 
13026     H5Dclose(nucset);
13027     delete[] nkey;
13028   };
13029 
13030   // Set meta data
13031   atoms_per_molecule = -1.0;
13032 };
13033 
13034 
13035 
13036 void pyne::Material::_load_comp_protocol1(hid_t db, std::string datapath, int row) {
13037   std::string nucpath;
13038   hid_t data_set = H5Dopen2(db, datapath.c_str(), H5P_DEFAULT);
13039 
13040   hsize_t data_offset[1] = {row};
13041   if (row < 0) {
13042     // Handle negative row indices
13043     hid_t data_space = H5Dget_space(data_set);
13044     hsize_t data_dims[1];
13045     H5Sget_simple_extent_dims(data_space, data_dims, NULL);
13046     data_offset[0] += data_dims[0];
13047   };
13048 
13049   // Grab the nucpath
13050   hid_t nuc_attr = H5Aopen(data_set, "nucpath", H5P_DEFAULT);
13051   H5A_info_t nuc_info;
13052   H5Aget_info(nuc_attr, &nuc_info);
13053   hsize_t nuc_attr_len = nuc_info.data_size;
13054   hid_t str_attr = H5Tcopy(H5T_C_S1);
13055   H5Tset_size(str_attr, nuc_attr_len);
13056   char * nucpathbuf = new char [nuc_attr_len];
13057   H5Aread(nuc_attr, str_attr, nucpathbuf);
13058   nucpath = std::string(nucpathbuf, nuc_attr_len);
13059   delete[] nucpathbuf;
13060 
13061   // Grab the nuclides
13062   std::vector<int> nuclides = h5wrap::h5_array_to_cpp_vector_1d<int>(db, nucpath, H5T_NATIVE_INT);
13063   int nuc_size = nuclides.size();
13064   hsize_t nuc_dims[1] = {nuc_size};
13065 
13066   // Get the data hyperslab
13067   hid_t data_hyperslab = H5Dget_space(data_set);
13068   hsize_t data_count[1] = {1};
13069   H5Sselect_hyperslab(data_hyperslab, H5S_SELECT_SET, data_offset, NULL, data_count, NULL);
13070 
13071   // Get memory space for writing
13072   hid_t mem_space = H5Screate_simple(1, data_count, NULL);
13073 
13074   // Get material type
13075   size_t material_data_size = sizeof(pyne::material_data) + sizeof(double)*nuc_size;
13076   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, material_data_size);
13077   hid_t comp_values_array_type = H5Tarray_create2(H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE, 1, nuc_dims);
13078 
13079   // make the data table type
13080   H5Tinsert(desc, "mass", HOFFSET(pyne::material_data, mass), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
13081   H5Tinsert(desc, "density", HOFFSET(pyne::material_data, density),
13082             H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
13083   H5Tinsert(desc, "atoms_per_molecule", HOFFSET(pyne::material_data, atoms_per_mol),
13084             H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
13085   H5Tinsert(desc, "comp", HOFFSET(pyne::material_data, comp), comp_values_array_type);
13086 
13087   // make the data array, have to over-allocate
13088   material_data * mat_data = new material_data [material_data_size];
13089 
13090   // Finally, get data and put in on this instance
13091   H5Dread(data_set, desc, mem_space, data_hyperslab, H5P_DEFAULT, mat_data);
13092 
13093   mass = (*mat_data).mass;
13094   density = (*mat_data).density;
13095   atoms_per_molecule = (*mat_data).atoms_per_mol;
13096   for (int i = 0; i < nuc_size; i++)
13097     comp[nuclides[i]] = (double) (*mat_data).comp[i];
13098 
13099   delete[] mat_data;
13100   H5Tclose(str_attr);
13101 
13102   //
13103   // Get metadata from associated dataset, if available
13104   //
13105   std::string attrpath = datapath + "_metadata";
13106   bool attrpath_exists = h5wrap::path_exists(db, attrpath);
13107   if (!attrpath_exists)
13108     return;
13109 
13110   hid_t metadatapace, attrtype, metadataet, metadatalab, attrmemspace;
13111   int attrrank;
13112   hvl_t attrdata [1];
13113 
13114   attrtype = H5Tvlen_create(H5T_NATIVE_CHAR);
13115 
13116   // Get the metadata from the file
13117   metadataet = H5Dopen2(db, attrpath.c_str(), H5P_DEFAULT);
13118   metadatalab = H5Dget_space(metadataet);
13119   H5Sselect_hyperslab(metadatalab, H5S_SELECT_SET, data_offset, NULL, data_count, NULL);
13120   attrmemspace = H5Screate_simple(1, data_count, NULL);
13121   H5Dread(metadataet, attrtype, attrmemspace, metadatalab, H5P_DEFAULT, attrdata);
13122 
13123   // convert to in-memory JSON
13124   Json::Reader reader;
13125   reader.parse((char *) attrdata[0].p, (char *) attrdata[0].p+attrdata[0].len, metadata, false);
13126 
13127   // close attr data objects
13128   H5Fflush(db, H5F_SCOPE_GLOBAL);
13129   H5Dclose(metadataet);
13130   H5Sclose(metadatapace);
13131   H5Tclose(attrtype);
13132 
13133   // Close out the HDF5 file
13134   H5Fclose(db);
13135 };

13141 void pyne::Material::from_hdf5(char * filename, char * datapath, int row, int protocol) {
13142   std::string fname (filename);
13143   std::string dpath (datapath);
13144   from_hdf5(fname, dpath, row, protocol);

13146 
13147 
13148 
13149 void pyne::Material::from_hdf5(std::string filename, std::string datapath, int row, int protocol) {
13150   // Turn off annoying HDF5 errors
13151   herr_t status;
13152   H5Eset_auto2(H5E_DEFAULT, NULL, NULL);
13153 
13154   // Check that the file is there
13155   if (!pyne::file_exists(filename))
13156     throw pyne::FileNotFound(filename);
13157 
13158   // Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
13159   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(filename.c_str());
13160   if (!ish5)
13161     throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(filename);
13162 
13163   //Set file access properties so it closes cleanly
13164   hid_t fapl;
13165   fapl = H5Pcreate(H5P_FILE_ACCESS);
13166   H5Pset_fclose_degree(fapl,H5F_CLOSE_STRONG);
13167   // Open the database
13168   hid_t db = H5Fopen(filename.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDONLY, fapl);
13169 
13170   bool datapath_exists = h5wrap::path_exists(db, datapath);
13171   if (!datapath_exists)
13172     throw h5wrap::PathNotFound(filename, datapath);
13173 
13174   // Clear current content
13175   comp.clear();
13176 
13177   // Load via various protocols
13178   if (protocol == 0)
13179     _load_comp_protocol0(db, datapath, row);
13180   else if (protocol == 1)
13181     _load_comp_protocol1(db, datapath, row);
13182   else
13183     throw pyne::MaterialProtocolError();
13184 
13185   // Close the database
13186   status = H5Fclose(db);
13187 
13188   // Renormalize the composition, just to be safe.
13189   norm_comp();
13190 };
