13196 void pyne::Material::write_hdf5(char * filename, char * datapath, char * nucpath, float row, int chunksize) {
13197   std::string fname (filename);
13198   std::string groupname (datapath);
13199   std::string nuclist (nucpath);
13200   write_hdf5(fname, groupname, nuclist, row, chunksize);
13201 };
13202 
13203 
13204 
13205 void pyne::Material::write_hdf5(std::string filename, std::string datapath,
13206                                 std::string nucpath, float row, int chunksize) {
13207   int row_num = (int) row;
13208 
13209   // Turn off annoying HDF5 errors
13210   H5Eset_auto2(H5E_DEFAULT, NULL, NULL);
13211 
13212   //Set file access properties so it closes cleanly
13213   hid_t fapl;
13214   fapl = H5Pcreate(H5P_FILE_ACCESS);
13215   H5Pset_fclose_degree(fapl,H5F_CLOSE_STRONG);
13216   // Create new/open datafile.
13217   hid_t db;
13218   if (pyne::file_exists(filename)) {
13219     bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(filename.c_str());
13220     if (!ish5)
13221       throw h5wrap::FileNotHDF5(filename);
13222     db = H5Fopen(filename.c_str(), H5F_ACC_RDWR, fapl);
13223   }
13224   else
13225     db = H5Fcreate(filename.c_str(), H5F_ACC_TRUNC, H5P_DEFAULT, fapl);
13226 
13227   //
13228   // Read in nuclist if available, write it out if not
13229   //
13230   bool nucpath_exists = h5wrap::path_exists(db, nucpath);
13231   std::vector<int> nuclides;
13232   int nuc_size;
13233   hsize_t nuc_dims[1];
13234 
13235   if (nucpath_exists) {
13236     nuclides = h5wrap::h5_array_to_cpp_vector_1d<int>(db, nucpath, H5T_NATIVE_INT);
13237     nuc_size = nuclides.size();
13238     nuc_dims[0] = nuc_size;
13239   } else {
13240     nuclides = std::vector<int>();
13241     for (pyne::comp_iter i = comp.begin(); i != comp.end(); i++)
13242       nuclides.push_back(i->first);
13243     nuc_size = nuclides.size();
13244 
13245     // Create the data if it doesn't exist
13246     int nuc_data [nuc_size];
13247     for (int n = 0; n != nuc_size; n++)
13248       nuc_data[n] = nuclides[n];
13249     nuc_dims[0] = nuc_size;
13250     hid_t nuc_space = H5Screate_simple(1, nuc_dims, NULL);
13251     hid_t nuc_set = H5Dcreate2(db, nucpath.c_str(), H5T_NATIVE_INT, nuc_space,
13252                                H5P_DEFAULT, H5P_DEFAULT, H5P_DEFAULT);
13253     H5Dwrite(nuc_set, H5T_NATIVE_INT, H5S_ALL, H5S_ALL, H5P_DEFAULT, nuc_data);
13254     H5Fflush(db, H5F_SCOPE_GLOBAL);
13255   };
13256 
13257 
13258   //
13259   // Write out the data itself to the file
13260   //
13261   hid_t data_set, data_space, data_hyperslab;
13262   int data_rank = 1;
13263   hsize_t data_dims[1] = {1};
13264   hsize_t data_max_dims[1] = {H5S_UNLIMITED};
13265   hsize_t data_offset[1] = {0};
13266 
13267   size_t material_data_size = sizeof(pyne::material_data) + sizeof(double)*nuc_size;
13268   hid_t desc = H5Tcreate(H5T_COMPOUND, material_data_size);
13269   hid_t comp_values_array_type = H5Tarray_create2(H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE, 1, nuc_dims);
13270 
13271   // make the data table type
13272   H5Tinsert(desc, "mass", HOFFSET(pyne::material_data, mass), H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
13273   H5Tinsert(desc, "density", HOFFSET(pyne::material_data, density),
13274             H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
13275   H5Tinsert(desc, "atoms_per_molecule", HOFFSET(pyne::material_data, atoms_per_mol),
13276             H5T_NATIVE_DOUBLE);
13277   H5Tinsert(desc, "comp", HOFFSET(pyne::material_data, comp),
13278             comp_values_array_type);
13279 
13280   material_data * mat_data  = new material_data[material_data_size];
13281   (*mat_data).mass = mass;
13282   (*mat_data).density = density;
13283   (*mat_data).atoms_per_mol = atoms_per_molecule;
13284   for (int n = 0; n != nuc_size; n++) {
13285     if (0 < comp.count(nuclides[n]))
13286       (*mat_data).comp[n] = comp[nuclides[n]];
13287     else
13288       (*mat_data).comp[n] = 0.0;
13289   };
13290 
13291   // get / make the data set
13292   bool datapath_exists = h5wrap::path_exists(db, datapath);
13293   if (datapath_exists) {
13294     data_set = H5Dopen2(db, datapath.c_str(), H5P_DEFAULT);
13295     data_space = H5Dget_space(data_set);
13296     data_rank = H5Sget_simple_extent_dims(data_space, data_dims, data_max_dims);
13297 
13298     // Determine the row size.
13299     if (std::signbit(row))
13300       row_num = data_dims[0] + row;  // careful, row is negative
13301 
13302     if (data_dims[0] <= row_num) {
13303       // row == -0, extend to data set so that we can append, or
13304       // row_num is larger than current dimension, resize to accomodate.
13305       data_dims[0] = row_num + 1;
13306       H5Dset_extent(data_set, data_dims);
13307     }
13308 
13309     data_offset[0] = row_num;
13310   } else {
13311     // Get full space
13312     data_space = H5Screate_simple(1, data_dims, data_max_dims);
13313 
13314     // Make data set properties to enable chunking
13315     hid_t data_set_params = H5Pcreate(H5P_DATASET_CREATE);
13316     hsize_t chunk_dims[1] ={chunksize};
13317     H5Pset_chunk(data_set_params, 1, chunk_dims);
13318     H5Pset_deflate(data_set_params, 1);
13319 
13320     material_data * data_fill_value  = new material_data[material_data_size];
13321     (*data_fill_value).mass = -1.0;
13322     (*data_fill_value).density= -1.0;
13323     (*data_fill_value).atoms_per_mol = -1.0;
13324     for (int n = 0; n != nuc_size; n++)
13325       (*data_fill_value).comp[n] = 0.0;
13326     H5Pset_fill_value(data_set_params, desc, &data_fill_value);
13327 
13328     // Create the data set
13329     data_set = H5Dcreate2(db, datapath.c_str(), desc, data_space, H5P_DEFAULT,
13330                             data_set_params, H5P_DEFAULT);
13331     H5Dset_extent(data_set, data_dims);
13332 
13333     // Add attribute pointing to nuc path
13334     hid_t nuc_attr_type = H5Tcopy(H5T_C_S1);
13335     H5Tset_size(nuc_attr_type, nucpath.length());
13336     hid_t nuc_attr_space = H5Screate(H5S_SCALAR);
13337     hid_t nuc_attr = H5Acreate2(data_set, "nucpath", nuc_attr_type, nuc_attr_space,
13338                                 H5P_DEFAULT, H5P_DEFAULT);
13339     H5Awrite(nuc_attr, nuc_attr_type, nucpath.c_str());
13340     H5Fflush(db, H5F_SCOPE_GLOBAL);
13341 
13342     // Remember to de-allocate
13343     delete[] data_fill_value;
13344   };
13345 
13346   // Get the data hyperslab
13347   data_hyperslab = H5Dget_space(data_set);
13348   hsize_t data_count[1] = {1};
13349   H5Sselect_hyperslab(data_hyperslab, H5S_SELECT_SET, data_offset, NULL, data_count, NULL);
13350 
13351   // Get a memory space for writing
13352   hid_t mem_space = H5Screate_simple(1, data_count, data_max_dims);
13353 
13354   // Write the row...
13355   H5Dwrite(data_set, desc, mem_space, data_hyperslab, H5P_DEFAULT, mat_data);
13356 
13357   // Close out the Dataset
13358   H5Fflush(db, H5F_SCOPE_GLOBAL);
13359   H5Dclose(data_set);
13360   H5Sclose(data_space);
13361   H5Tclose(desc);
13362 
13363   //
13364   // Write out the metadata to the file
13365   //
13366   std::string attrpath = datapath + "_metadata";
13367   hid_t metadatapace, attrtype, metadataet, metadatalab, attrmemspace;
13368   int attrrank;
13369 
13370   attrtype = H5Tvlen_create(H5T_NATIVE_CHAR);
13371 
13372   // get / make the data set
13373   bool attrpath_exists = h5wrap::path_exists(db, attrpath);
13374   if (attrpath_exists) {
13375     metadataet = H5Dopen2(db, attrpath.c_str(), H5P_DEFAULT);
13376     metadatapace = H5Dget_space(metadataet);
13377     attrrank = H5Sget_simple_extent_dims(metadatapace, data_dims, data_max_dims);
13378 
13379     if (data_dims[0] <= row_num) {
13380       // row == -0, extend to data set so that we can append, or
13381       // row_num is larger than current dimension, resize to accomodate.
13382       data_dims[0] = row_num + 1;
13383       H5Dset_extent(metadataet, data_dims);
13384     }
13385 
13386     data_offset[0] = row_num;
13387   } else {
13388     hid_t metadataetparams;
13389     hsize_t attrchunkdims [1];
13390 
13391     // Make data set properties to enable chunking
13392     metadataetparams = H5Pcreate(H5P_DATASET_CREATE);
13393     attrchunkdims[0] = chunksize;
13394     H5Pset_chunk(metadataetparams, 1, attrchunkdims);
13395     H5Pset_deflate(metadataetparams, 1);
13396 
13397     hvl_t attrfillvalue [1];
13398     attrfillvalue[0].len = 3;
13399     attrfillvalue[0].p = (char *) "{}\n";
13400     H5Pset_fill_value(metadataetparams, attrtype, &attrfillvalue);
13401 
13402     // make dataset
13403     metadatapace = H5Screate_simple(1, data_dims, data_max_dims);
13404     metadataet = H5Dcreate2(db, attrpath.c_str(), attrtype, metadatapace,
13405                          H5P_DEFAULT, metadataetparams, H5P_DEFAULT);
13406     H5Dset_extent(metadataet, data_dims);
13407     H5Pclose(metadataetparams);
13408   };
13409 
13410   // set the attr string
13411   hvl_t attrdata [1];
13412   Json::FastWriter writer;
13413   std::string metadatatr = writer.write(metadata);
13414   attrdata[0].p = (char *) metadatatr.c_str();
13415   attrdata[0].len = metadatatr.length();
13416 
13417   // write the attr
13418   metadatalab = H5Dget_space(metadataet);
13419   H5Sselect_hyperslab(metadatalab, H5S_SELECT_SET, data_offset, NULL, data_count, NULL);
13420   attrmemspace = H5Screate_simple(1, data_count, data_max_dims);
13421   H5Dwrite(metadataet, attrtype, attrmemspace, metadatalab, H5P_DEFAULT, attrdata);
13422 
13423   // close attr data objects
13424   H5Fflush(db, H5F_SCOPE_GLOBAL);
13425   H5Dclose(metadataet);
13426   H5Sclose(metadatapace);
13427   H5Tclose(attrtype);
13428 
13429   // Close out the HDF5 file
13430   H5Fclose(db);
13431   // Remember the milk!
13432   // ...by which I mean to deallocate
13433   delete[] mat_data;
13434 };
13435 
13436 std::string pyne::Material::mcnp(std::string frac_type) {
13437   //////////////////// Begin card creation ///////////////////////
13438   std::ostringstream oss;
13439   // 'name'
13440   if (metadata.isMember("name")) {
13441     oss << "C name: " << metadata["name"].asString() << std::endl;
13442   }
13443   // 'density'
13444   if (density != -1.0) {
13445      std::stringstream ds;
13446      ds << std::setprecision(1) << std::fixed << "C density = " << density << std::endl;
13447      oss << ds.str();
13448   }
13449   // 'source'
13450   if (metadata.isMember("source")) {
13451      oss << "C source: " << metadata["source"].asString() << std::endl;
13452   }
13453   // Metadata comments
13454   if (metadata.isMember("comments")) {
13455     std::string comment_string = "comments: " + metadata["comments"].asString();
13456     // Include as is if short enough
13457     if (comment_string.length() <= 77) {
13458       oss << "C " << comment_string << std::endl;
13459     }
13460     else { // otherwise create a remainder string and iterate/update it
13461       oss << "C " << comment_string.substr(0,77) << std::endl;
13462       std::string remainder_string = comment_string.substr(77);
13463       while (remainder_string.length() > 77) {
13464         oss << "C " << remainder_string.substr(0,77) << std::endl;
13465         remainder_string.erase(0,77);
13466       }
13467       if (remainder_string.length() > 0) {
13468         oss << "C " << remainder_string << std::endl;
13469       }
13470     }
13471   }
13472 
13473   // Metadata mat_num
13474   oss << "m";
13475   if (metadata.isMember("mat_number")) {
13476     int mat_num = metadata["mat_number"].asInt();
13477     oss << mat_num << std::endl;
13478   } else {
13479     oss << "?" << std::endl;
13480   }
13481 
13482   // Set up atom or mass frac map
13483   std::map<int, double> fracs;
13484   std::string frac_sign;
13485 
13486   if ("atom" == frac_type) {
13487     fracs = to_atom_frac();
13488     frac_sign = "";
13489   } else {
13490     fracs = comp;
13491     frac_sign = "-";
13492   }
13493 
13494   // iterate through frac map
13495   // This is an awkward pre-C++11 way to put an int to a string
13496   std::stringstream ss;
13497   std::string nucmcnp;
13498   std::string table_item;
13499   for(pyne::comp_iter i = fracs.begin(); i != fracs.end(); ++i) {
13500     // Clear first
13501     ss.str(std::string() );
13502     ss.str("");
13503     ss << pyne::nucname::mcnp(i->first );
13504     nucmcnp = ss.str();
13505 
13506     int mcnp_id;
13507     mcnp_id = pyne::nucname::mcnp(i->first );
13508     // Spaces are important for tests
13509     table_item = metadata["table_ids"][nucmcnp].asString();
13510     if ( !table_item.empty() ) {
13511       oss << "     " << mcnp_id << "." << table_item << " ";
13512     } else {
13513       oss << "     " << mcnp_id << " ";
13514     }
13515     // The int needs a little formatting
13516     std::stringstream fs;
13517     fs << std::setprecision(4) << std::scientific << frac_sign << i->second \
13518        << std::endl;
13519     oss << fs.str();
13520   }
13521 
13522   return oss.str();
13523 }
13524 
13525 ///---------------------------------------------------------------------------//
13526 /// Create a set out of the static string array. 
13527 std::set<std::string> fluka_builtin(pyne::fluka_mat_strings, 
13528                                     pyne::fluka_mat_strings+pyne::FLUKA_MAT_NUM);
13529 
13530 ///---------------------------------------------------------------------------//
13531 /// not_fluka_builtin
13532 ///---------------------------------------------------------------------------//
13533 /// Convenience function
13534 /// This is written as a negative because that is what we care about
13535 bool pyne::Material::not_fluka_builtin(std::string fluka_name) {
13536   return (fluka_builtin.find(fluka_name) == fluka_builtin.end());
13537 }
13538 
13539 ///---------------------------------------------------------------------------//
13540 /// fluka
13541 ///---------------------------------------------------------------------------//
13542 /// Main external call
13543 std::string pyne::Material::fluka(int id, std::string frac_type) {
13544   std::stringstream rs;
13545 
13546   // Element, one nucid
13547   if (comp.size() == 1) {
13548     rs << fluka_material_str(id);
13549   } else if (comp.size() > 1) {
13550   // Compound
13551     rs << fluka_compound_str(id, frac_type);
13552   } else {
13553     rs << "There is no nuclide information in the Material Object" << std::endl;
13554   }
13555   return rs.str();
13556 }
13557 
13558 ///---------------------------------------------------------------------------//
13559 /// fluka_material_str
13560 ///---------------------------------------------------------------------------//
13561 ///
13562 /// Requirement:  the material upon which this function is called has
13563 ///               exactly one nucid component, i.e. it is elemental
13564 /// Do not assume fluka_name is defined in the metadata.  This function
13565 /// may be called from a user-defined material, i.e. on that is not 
13566 /// read out of a UW^2-tagged geometry file, and thus does not have
13567 /// certain metadata.
13568 std::string pyne::Material::fluka_material_str(int id) {
13569   std::stringstream ms;
13570   std::string fluka_name; // needed to determine if built-in
13571 
13572   int nucid = comp.begin()->first;
13573    
13574   // NOTE:  first part of 'if' may never be called
13575   if (metadata.isMember("fluka_name")) {
13576     fluka_name = metadata["fluka_name"].asString();
13577   } else {  // Should be elemental
13578     if (comp.size() > 1 ) {
13579       std::cerr << "Error: this mix is a compound, there should be a fluka_name defined."
13580                 << std::endl;
13581       return ms.str();
13582     }
13583     fluka_name = nucname::fluka(nucid);
13584   }
13585 
13586   if (not_fluka_builtin(fluka_name)) {  
13587     ms << fluka_material_component(id, nucid, fluka_name);
13588   }
13589 
13590   // could be empty
13591   return ms.str();
13592 }
13593     
13594 ///---------------------------------------------------------------------------//
13595 /// fluka_material_component
13596 ///---------------------------------------------------------------------------//
13597 /// Material has only one component, 
13598 /// Density is either object density or it is ignored ==> use object density
13599 /// This function is not called for a compound, but it is called on the 
13600 /// material-ized components of compounds
13601 std::string pyne::Material::fluka_material_component(int fid, int nucid, 
13602                                                std::string fluka_name) {
13603   int znum = pyne::nucname::znum(nucid);
13604 
13605   double atomic_mass;
13606   if (0 != pyne::NUC_DATA_PATH.length()) { 
13607     // for compounds (i.e., unrecognized nucids), this will be 0
13608     atomic_mass = pyne::atomic_mass(nucid);
13609   } else {
13610     atomic_mass = -1; 
13611   }  
13612 
13613   return fluka_material_line(znum, atomic_mass, fid, fluka_name);
13614 }
13615 
13616 ///---------------------------------------------------------------------------//
13617 /// fluka_material_line
13618 ///---------------------------------------------------------------------------//
13619 /// Given all the info, return the Material string
13620 std::string pyne::Material::fluka_material_line(int znum, double atomic_mass, 
13621                                           int fid, std::string fluka_name) {
13622   std::stringstream ls;
13623 
13624   if (metadata.isMember("comments") ) {
13625      std::string comment = metadata["comments"].asString();
13626      ls << "* " << comment;
13627      ls << std::endl;
13628   }
13629   ls << std::setw(10) << std::left << "MATERIAL";
13630   ls << std::setprecision(0) << std::fixed << std::showpoint <<
13631         std::setw(10) << std::right << (float)znum; 
13632 
13633   ls << fluka_format_field(atomic_mass);
13634   // Note this is the current object density, and may or may not be meaningful
13635   ls << fluka_format_field(density);
13636 
13637   ls << std::setprecision(0) << std::fixed << std::showpoint <<
13638         std::setw(10) << std::right << (float)fid;
13639   ls << std::setw(10) << std::right << "";
13640   ls << std::setw(10) << std::right << "";
13641   ls << std::setw(10) << std::left << fluka_name << std::endl;
13642 
13643   return ls.str();
13644 }
13645 
13646 ///---------------------------------------------------------------------------//
13647 /// fluka_format_field
13648 ///---------------------------------------------------------------------------//
13649 /// Convenience function that returns a 10-character formatted string
13650 /// 999 -> 999.
13651 /// 999.12 -> 999.12
13652 /// 999.123 -> 999.123
13653 /// 999.1234 -> 999.123
13654 std::string pyne::Material::fluka_format_field(float field) {
13655   std::stringstream ls;
13656   double intpart;
13657   modf (field, &intpart);
13658   if (field == intpart) {
13659     ls << std::setprecision(0) << std::fixed << std::showpoint 
13660        << std::setw(10) << std::right << field;
13661   } else {
13662   // This will print however many digits after the decimal, up to a max of six
13663     ls.unsetf(std::ios::showpoint);
13664     ls.unsetf(std::ios::floatfield);
13665     ls.precision(6);
13666     ls << std::setw(10) << std::right << field;
13667   }  
13668 
13669   return ls.str();
13670 }
13671 
13672 ///---------------------------------------------------------------------------//
13673 /// fluka_compound_str
13674 ///---------------------------------------------------------------------------//
13675 /// Returns
13676 /// -- MATERIAL line for compound
13677 /// -- COMPOUND lines
13678 std::string pyne::Material::fluka_compound_str(int id, std::string frac_type) {
13679   std::stringstream ss;
13680   std::map<double, std::string> frac_name_map;
13681   std::string compound_string = "";
13682   std::vector<std::string> material_names;
13683 
13684   // The nucid doesn't make sense for a compound
13685   int znum = 999;
13686   double atomic_mass = 999.;
13687   // This better be true
13688   std::string compound_name;
13689   if (metadata.isMember("fluka_name")) {
13690     compound_name = metadata["fluka_name"].asString();
13691   } else {
13692     std::cerr << "Error:  metadata \"fluka_name\" expected." << std::endl;
13693     compound_name = "NotFound";
13694   }  
13695   ss << fluka_material_line(znum, atomic_mass, id, compound_name);
13696   
13697   std::string frac_sign;
13698   if ("atom" == frac_type) {
13699     frac_sign = "";
13700   } else {
13701     frac_sign = "-";
13702   }
13703 
13704   std::stringstream temp_s;
13705   int counter = comp.size();
13706   pyne::comp_iter nuc = comp.begin();
13707   // This will pick up multiples of 3 components
13708   while (counter >= 3) {
13709     ss << std::setw(10) << std::left  << "COMPOUND";
13710 
13711     temp_s << frac_sign << nuc->second;
13712     ss << std::setw(10) << std::right << temp_s.str();
13713     ss << std::setw(10) << std::right << nucname::fluka(nuc->first);
13714     nuc++;
13715     temp_s.str("");  // reset the stringstream for reuse
13716 
13717     temp_s << frac_sign << nuc->second;
13718     ss << std::setw(10) << std::right << temp_s.str();
13719     ss << std::setw(10) << std::right << nucname::fluka(nuc->first);
13720     nuc++;
13721     temp_s.str("");
13722 
13723     temp_s << frac_sign << nuc->second;
13724     ss << std::setw(10) << std::right << temp_s.str();
13725     ss << std::setw(10) << std::right << nucname::fluka(nuc->first);
13726     nuc++;
13727     temp_s.str("");
13728 
13729     ss << std::setw(10) << std::left << compound_name;
13730     ss << std::endl;
13731 
13732     counter -= 3;
13733   }
13734 
13735   // Get the last (or only, as the case may be) one or two fractions
13736   if (nuc != comp.end()) {
13737     std::stringstream temp_s;
13738     ss << std::setw(10) << std::left  << "COMPOUND";
13739     temp_s << frac_sign << nuc->second;
13740     ss << std::setw(10) << std::right << temp_s.str();
13741     ss << std::setw(10) << std::right << nucname::fluka(nuc->first);
13742     nuc++;
13743     temp_s.str("");
13744     
13745     if  (nuc != comp.end()) {
13746       temp_s << frac_sign << nuc->second;
13747       ss << std::setw(10) << std::right << temp_s.str();
13748       ss << std::setw(10) << std::right << nucname::fluka(nuc->first);
13749       nuc++;
13750       temp_s.str("");
13751     } else {
13752       ss << std::setw(10) << std::right << ""; 
13753       ss << std::setw(10) << std::right << ""; 
13754     }
13755 
13756     ss << std::setw(10) << std::right << ""; 
13757     ss << std::setw(10) << std::right << ""; 
13758     ss << std::setw(10) << std::left << compound_name;
13759     }
13760 
13761   ss<< std::endl;
13762   return ss.str();
13763 }

13765 void pyne::Material::from_text(char * filename) {
13766   std::string fname (filename);
13767   from_text(fname);
13768 };
13769 
13770 
13771 void pyne::Material::from_text(std::string filename) {
13772   // Check that the file is there
13773   if (!pyne::file_exists(filename))
13774     throw pyne::FileNotFound(filename);
13775 
13776   // New filestream
13777   std::ifstream f;
13778   f.open(filename.c_str());
13779 
13780   // Read in
13781   comp.clear();
13782   std::string keystr, valstr;
13783 
13784   while ( !f.eof() ) {
13785     f >> keystr;
13786 
13787     if (0 == keystr.length())
13788       continue;
13789 
13790     if (keystr == "Mass"){
13791       f >> valstr;
13792       mass = pyne::to_dbl(valstr);
13793     } else if (keystr == "Density") {
13794       f >> valstr;
13795       density = pyne::to_dbl(valstr);
13796     } else if (keystr == "APerM") {
13797       f >> valstr;
13798       atoms_per_molecule = pyne::to_dbl(valstr);
13799     } else if (pyne::nucname::isnuclide(keystr)) {
13800       f >> valstr;
13801        comp[pyne::nucname::id(keystr)] = pyne::to_dbl(valstr);
13802     } else {
13803       getline(f, valstr);
13804       valstr= valstr.substr(0, valstr.length()-1);
13805       metadata[keystr]= valstr;
13806       continue;
13807    }
13808    };
13809 
13810    f.close();
13811    norm_comp();
13812 };
13813 
13814 
13815 
13816 void pyne::Material::write_text(char * filename) {
13817   std::string fname (filename);
13818   write_text(fname);
13819 };
13820 
13821 
13822 void pyne::Material::write_text(std::string filename) {
13823   std::ofstream f;
13824   f.open(filename.c_str(), std::ios_base::trunc);
13825 
13826   Json::Reader reader;
13827   std::vector<std::string> obj = metadata.getMemberNames();
13828 
13829   if (0 <= mass)
13830     f << "Mass    " << mass << "\n";
13831 
13832   if (0 <= density)
13833     f << "Density "  << density << "\n";
13834 
13835   if (0 <= atoms_per_molecule)
13836     f << "APerM   " << atoms_per_molecule << "\n";
13837 
13838   for (int i=0; i < metadata.size(); i=i+2){
13839     f <<metadata.get(obj.at(i), "") << metadata.get(obj.at(i+1), "");
13840   }
13841 
13842   std::string nuc_name;
13843   for(pyne::comp_iter i = comp.begin(); i != comp.end(); i++) {
13844     nuc_name = pyne::nucname::name( i->first ) + "  ";
13845     while (nuc_name.length() < 8)
13846       nuc_name += " ";
13847     f << nuc_name << i->second << "\n";
13848   };
13849 
13850   f.close();
13851 };
13852 
13853 
13854 void pyne::Material::load_json(Json::Value json) {
13855   Json::Value::Members keys = json["comp"].getMemberNames();
13856   Json::Value::Members::const_iterator ikey = keys.begin();
13857   Json::Value::Members::const_iterator ikey_end = keys.end();
13858   comp.clear();
13859   for (; ikey != ikey_end; ++ikey)
13860     comp[nucname::id(*ikey)] = json["comp"][*ikey].asDouble();
13861   norm_comp();
13862   mass = json["mass"].asDouble();
13863   density = json["density"].asDouble();
13864   atoms_per_molecule = json["atoms_per_molecule"].asDouble();
13865   metadata = json["metadata"];
13866 };
13867 
13868 
13869 Json::Value pyne::Material::dump_json() {
13870   Json::Value json = Json::Value(Json::objectValue);
13871   Json::Value jcomp = Json::Value(Json::objectValue);
13872   json["mass"] = mass;
13873   json["density"] = density;
13874   json["atoms_per_molecule"] = atoms_per_molecule;
13875   json["metadata"] = metadata;
13876   for(comp_iter i = comp.begin(); i != comp.end(); i++)
13877     jcomp[nucname::name(i->first)] = (i->second);
13878   json["comp"] = jcomp;
13879   return json;
13880 };
13881 
13882 
13883 void pyne::Material::from_json(char * filename) {
13884   std::string fname (filename);
13885   from_json(fname);
13886 };
13887 
13888 void pyne::Material::from_json(std::string filename) {
13889   if (!pyne::file_exists(filename))
13890     throw pyne::FileNotFound(filename);
13891   std::string s;
13892   std::ifstream f (filename.c_str(), std::ios::in | std::ios::binary);
13893   f.seekg(0, std::ios::end);
13894   s.resize(f.tellg());
13895   f.seekg(0, std::ios::beg);
13896   f.read(&s[0], s.size());
13897   f.close();
13898   Json::Reader reader;
13899   Json::Value json;
13900   reader.parse(s, json);
13901   load_json(json);
13902 };
13903 
13904 
13905 void pyne::Material::write_json(char * filename) {
13906   std::string fname (filename);
13907   write_json(fname);
13908 };
13909 
13910 void pyne::Material::write_json(std::string filename) {
13911   Json::Value json = dump_json();
13912   Json::StyledWriter writer;
13913   std::string s = writer.write(json);
13914   std::ofstream f;
13915   f.open(filename.c_str(), std::ios_base::trunc);
13916   f << s << "\n";
13917   f.close();
13918 };

13936 pyne::Material::Material(pyne::comp_map cm, double m, double d, double apm,
13937                          Json::Value attributes) {
13938   // Initializes the mass stream based on an isotopic component dictionary.
13939   comp = cm;
13940   mass = m;
13941   density=d;
13942   atoms_per_molecule = apm;
13943   metadata = attributes;
13944   if (!comp.empty())
13945     norm_comp();

13949 
13950 pyne::Material::Material(char * filename, double m, double d, double apm,
13951                          Json::Value attributes) {
13952   mass = m;
13953   density=d;
13954   atoms_per_molecule = apm;
13955   metadata = attributes;
13956 
13957   // Check that the file is there
13958   std::string fname (filename);
13959   if (!pyne::file_exists(fname))
13960     throw pyne::FileNotFound(fname);
13961 
13962   // Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
13963   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(fname.c_str());
13964   if (ish5)
13965     from_hdf5(fname);
13966   else
13967     from_text(fname);
13968 };

13974   mass = m;
13975   density=d;
13976   atoms_per_molecule = apm;
13977   metadata = attributes;
13978 
13979   // Check that the file is there
13980   if (!pyne::file_exists(filename))
13981     throw pyne::FileNotFound(filename);
13982 
13983   // Check to see if the file is in HDF5 format.
13984   bool ish5 = H5Fis_hdf5(filename.c_str());
13985   if (ish5)
13986     from_hdf5(filename);
13987   else
13988     from_text(filename);
13989 };

14001   //print the Mass Stream to stdout
14002   os << "\tMass: " << mat.mass << "\n";
14003   os << "\t---------\n";
14004   for(pyne::comp_iter i = mat.comp.begin(); i != mat.comp.end(); i++)
14005   {
14006     os << "\t" << pyne::nucname::name( i->first ) << "\t" << i->second << "\n";
14007   };

14015 
14016 void pyne::Material::normalize () {
14017   // normalizes the mass
14018   mass = 1.0;
14019 };
14020 
14021 
14022 pyne::comp_map pyne::Material::mult_by_mass() {
14023   // bypass calculation if already normalized.
14024   if (mass == 1.0)
14025     return comp;
14026 
14027   pyne::comp_map cm;
14028   for (pyne::comp_iter i = comp.begin(); i != comp.end(); i++) {
14029     cm[i->first] = (i->second) * mass;
14030   };
14031   return cm;
14032 };
14033 
14034 
14035 
14036 double pyne::Material::molecular_mass(double apm) {
14037   // Calculate the atomic weight of the Material
14038   double inverseA = 0.0;
14039 
14040   for (pyne::comp_iter nuc = comp.begin(); nuc != comp.end(); nuc++)
14041     inverseA += (nuc->second) / pyne::atomic_mass(nuc->first);
14042 
14043   if (inverseA == 0.0)
14044     return inverseA;
14045 
14046   // select the atoms per mol
14047   double atsperm = 1.0; // default to 1.0
14048   if (0.0 <= apm) {
14049     atsperm = apm;            // take the function argument, if valid
14050     if (atoms_per_molecule < 0.0)
14051       atoms_per_molecule = apm;     // Store the function argument on class, if class has no value
14052   } else if (0.0 <= atoms_per_molecule)
14053     atsperm = atoms_per_molecule;  // select the class's value
14054 
14055   return atsperm / inverseA;
14056 };
14057 
14058 
14059 pyne::Material pyne::Material::expand_elements() {
14060   // Expands the natural elements of a material and returns a new material note
14061   // that this implementation relies on the fact that maps of ints are stored in
14062   // a sorted manner in C++.
14063   int n, nabund, znuc, zabund;
14064   comp_map newcomp;
14065   std::map<int, double>::iterator abund_itr, abund_end;
14066   if (pyne::natural_abund_map.empty())
14067     pyne::_load_atomic_mass_map();
14068   abund_itr = pyne::natural_abund_map.begin();
14069   abund_end = pyne::natural_abund_map.end();
14070   zabund = nucname::znum((*abund_itr).first);
14071   for (comp_iter nuc = comp.begin(); nuc != comp.end(); nuc++) {
14072     if(abund_itr == abund_end)
14073       newcomp.insert(*nuc);
14074     else if(0 == nucname::anum((*nuc).first)) {
14075       n = (*nuc).first;
14076       znuc = nucname::znum(n);
14077       if (znuc < zabund) {
14078         newcomp.insert(*nuc);
14079         continue;
14080       }
14081       while(zabund <= znuc) {
14082         nabund = (*abund_itr).first;
14083         if (zabund == znuc && 0 != nucname::anum(nabund) && 0.0 != (*abund_itr).second)
14084           newcomp[nabund] = (*abund_itr).second * (*nuc).second * \
14085                             atomic_mass_map[nabund] / atomic_mass_map[n];
14086         else if (n == nabund && 0.0 == (*abund_itr).second)
14087           newcomp.insert(*nuc);
14088         abund_itr++;
14089         if (abund_itr == abund_end) {
14090           zabund = INT_MAX;
14091           break;
14092         }
14093         zabund = nucname::znum(nabund);
14094       };
14095     } else
14096       newcomp.insert(*nuc);
14097   };
14098   return Material(newcomp, mass, density, atoms_per_molecule, metadata);
14099 };
14100 
14101 pyne::Material pyne::Material::collapse_elements(std::set<int> exception_ids) {
14102   ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
14103   // Assumptions
14104   //    - list passed in is of nucid's formed from the znum-anum of 
14105   //      Fluka-named isotopes, since we want to preserve the full 
14106   //      nucid of any such material in the problem
14107   // Algorithm
14108   // for each component listed in this material that has a nonzero frac or 
14109   //    weight amount, look at its 'stripped' nucid, that is, the last four 
14110   //    places replaced by zeros.
14111   //    if it's on the exception list, copy the component
14112   //    else it is to be collapsed 
14113   //       => add its frac to the component of the znum
14114   //  
14115   // * When from_hdf5 reads from a file the comp iterator will produce a 
14116   //   hit for EVERY nucid in EVERY material in the file.  Only the nucids
14117   //   belonging to the CURRENT material have a nonzero fraction/mass amount
14118   ///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////// 
14119   pyne::comp_map cm;
14120   
14121   for (pyne::comp_iter ptr = comp.begin(); ptr != comp.end(); ptr++) {
14122       if (0 < ptr->second) {
14123         // There is a nonzero amount of this nucid in the current material, 
14124         // check if znum and anum are in the exception list, 
14125         int cur_stripped_id = nucname::znum(ptr->first)*10000000 
14126                         + nucname::anum(ptr->first)*10000;
14127         if (0 < exception_ids.count(cur_stripped_id)) {
14128         // The znum/anum combination identify the current material as a 
14129         // fluka-named exception list => copy, don't collapse
14130           cm[ptr->first] = (ptr->second) * mass;
14131         } else {
14132           // Not on exception list => add frac to id-component
14133           int znum_id = nucname::id(nucname::znum(ptr->first));
14134           cm[znum_id] += (ptr->second) * mass;
14135         }
14136       }
14137   }
14138   // Copy 
14139   pyne::Material collapsed = pyne::Material(cm, mass, density, 
14140                                             atoms_per_molecule, metadata);
14141   return collapsed;
14142 }
14143 
14144 // Wrapped version for calling from python
14145 pyne::Material pyne::Material::collapse_elements(int** int_ptr_arry ) {
14146     std::set<int> nucvec;
14147     // Set first pointer to first int pointed to by arg
14148     int *int_ptr = *int_ptr_arry;
14149     while (int_ptr != NULL)
14150     {
14151       nucvec.insert(*int_ptr);
14152       int_ptr++;
14153     }
14154     return collapse_elements(nucvec);
14155 }
14156 
14157 double pyne::Material::mass_density(double num_dens, double apm) {
14158   if (0.0 <= num_dens) {
14159     double mw = molecular_mass(apm);
14160     density = num_dens * mw / pyne::N_A / atoms_per_molecule;
14161   };
14162   return density;
14163 };
14164 
14165 
14166 double pyne::Material::number_density(double mass_dens, double apm) {
14167   if (0 <= mass_dens)
14168     density = mass_dens;
14169   double mw = molecular_mass(apm);
14170   double num_dens = density * pyne::N_A * atoms_per_molecule / mw;
14171   return num_dens;
14172 };

14175 /*--- Stub-Stream Computation ---*/
14176 
14177 pyne::Material pyne::Material::sub_mat(std::set<int> nucset) {
14178   // Grabs a sub-material from this mat based on a set of integers.
14179   // Integers can either be of id form -OR- they can be a z-numer (is 8 for O, 93 for Np, etc).
14180 
14181   pyne::comp_map cm;
14182   for (pyne::comp_iter i = comp.begin(); i != comp.end(); i++) {
14183     if ( 0 < nucset.count(i->first) )
14184       cm[i->first] = (i->second) * mass;
14185   };
14186 
14187   return pyne::Material(cm, -1, -1);
14188 };
14189 
14190 
14191 
14192 pyne::Material pyne::Material::sub_mat(std::set<std::string> nucset) {
14193   // Grabs a substream from this stream based on a set of strings.
14194   // Strings can be of any form.
14195   std::set<int> iset;
14196   for (std::set<std::string>::iterator i = nucset.begin(); i != nucset.end(); i++) {
14197     iset.insert(pyne::nucname::id(*i));
14198   };
14199 
14200   return sub_mat(iset);
14201 };
14202 
14203 
14204 
14205 pyne::Material pyne::Material::set_mat (std::set<int> nucset, double value) {
14206   // Sets a sub-material from this mat based on a set of integers.
14207   // Integers can either be of id form -OR- they can be a z-numer (is 8 for O, 93 for Np, etc).
14208   // n is the name of the new material.
14209 
14210   pyne::comp_map cm;
14211 
14212   // Add non-set components
14213   for (pyne::comp_iter i = comp.begin(); i != comp.end(); i++) {
14214     if ( 0 == nucset.count(i->first) )
14215       cm[i->first] = (i->second) * mass;
14216   };
14217 
14218   // Add set component
14219   for (std::set<int>::iterator nuc = nucset.begin(); nuc != nucset.end(); nuc++)
14220     cm[*nuc] = value;
14221 
14222   return pyne::Material(cm, -1, -1);
14223 };

14226 
14227 pyne::Material pyne::Material::set_mat(std::set<std::string> nucset, double value) {
14228   // Sets a substream from this stream based on a set of strings.
14229   // Strings can be of any form.
14230   std::set<int> iset;
14231   for (std::set<std::string>::iterator i = nucset.begin(); i != nucset.end(); i++) {
14232     iset.insert(pyne::nucname::id(*i));
14233   };
14234 
14235   return set_mat(iset, value);
14236 };

14240 
14241 pyne::Material pyne::Material::del_mat(std::set<int> nucset) {
14242   // Removes a sub-material from this mat based on a set of integers.
14243   // Integers can either be of id form -OR- they can be a z-numer (is 8 for O, 93 for Np, etc).
14244   // n is the name of the new material.
14245 
14246   pyne::comp_map cm;
14247   for (pyne::comp_iter i = comp.begin(); i != comp.end(); i++) {
14248     // Only add to new comp if not in nucset
14249     if ( 0 == nucset.count(i->first) )
14250       cm[i->first] = (i->second) * mass;
14251   };
14252 
14253   return pyne::Material(cm, -1, -1);
14254 };

14258 pyne::Material pyne::Material::del_mat (std::set<std::string> nucset) {
14259   // Removes a substream from this stream based on a set of strings.
14260   // Strings can be of any form.
14261   std::set<int> iset;
14262   for (std::set<std::string>::iterator i = nucset.begin(); i != nucset.end(); i++) {
14263     iset.insert(pyne::nucname::id(*i));
14264   };
14265 
14266   return del_mat(iset);
14267 };

14273 
14274 pyne::Material pyne::Material::sub_range(int lower, int upper) {
14275   // Grabs a sub-material from this mat based on a range of integers.
14276   if (upper < lower)
14277   {
14278     int temp_upper = upper;
14279     upper = lower;
14280     lower = temp_upper;
14281   };
14282 
14283   pyne::comp_map cm;
14284   for (pyne::comp_iter i = comp.begin(); i != comp.end(); i++) {
14285     if ((lower <= (i->first)) && ((i->first) < upper))
14286       cm[i->first] = (i->second) * mass;
14287   };
14288 
14289   return pyne::Material(cm, -1,-1);
14290 };
14291 
14292 
14293 
14294 pyne::Material pyne::Material::set_range(int lower, int upper, double value) {
14295 // Sets a sub-material from this mat based on a range of integers.
14296 if (upper < lower) {
14297 int temp_upper = upper;
14298 upper = lower;
14299 lower = temp_upper;
14300 };
14301 
14302 pyne::comp_map cm;
14303 for (pyne::comp_iter i = comp.begin(); i != comp.end(); i++) {
14304   if ((lower <= (i->first)) && ((i->first) < upper))
14305     cm[i->first] = value;
14306   else
14307     cm[i->first] = (i->second) * mass;
14308 };
14309 
14310   return pyne::Material(cm, -1,-1);
14311 };
14312 
14313 
14314 
14315 pyne::Material pyne::Material::del_range(int lower, int upper) {
14316   // Removes a sub-material from this mat based on a range of integers.
14317   if (upper < lower) {
14318     int temp_upper = upper;
14319     upper = lower;
14320     lower = temp_upper;
14321   };
14322 
14323   pyne::comp_map cm;
14324   for (pyne::comp_iter i = comp.begin(); i != comp.end(); i++) {
14325     if ((upper <= (i->first)) || ((i->first) < lower))
14326       cm[i->first] = (i->second) * mass;
14327   };
14328 
14329   return pyne::Material(cm, -1, -1);
14330 };

14382 
14383 /*--- Atom Frac Functions ---*/
14384 
14385 std::map<int, double> pyne::Material::to_atom_frac() {
14386   // Returns an atom fraction map from this material's composition
14387   // the material's molecular mass
14388   double mat_mw = molecular_mass();
14389 
14390   std::map<int, double> atom_fracs = std::map<int, double>();
14391 
14392   for (comp_iter ci = comp.begin(); ci != comp.end(); ci++)
14393     atom_fracs[ci->first] = (ci->second) * mat_mw / pyne::atomic_mass(ci->first);
14394 
14395   return atom_fracs;
14396 };
14397 
14398 
14399 void pyne::Material::from_atom_frac(std::map<int, double> atom_fracs) {
14400   // atom frac must be of the form {nuc: af}, eg, water
14401   //  80160: 1.0
14402   //  10010: 2.0
14403 
14404   // clear existing components
14405   comp.clear();
14406   atoms_per_molecule = 0.0;
14407 
14408   for (std::map<int, double>::iterator afi = atom_fracs.begin(); afi != atom_fracs.end(); afi++) {
14409     comp[afi->first] = (afi->second) * pyne::atomic_mass(afi->first);
14410     atoms_per_molecule += (afi->second);
14411   };
14412 
14413   norm_comp();
14414 };
14415 
14416 
14417 
14418 std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > pyne::Material::gammas() {
14419   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > result;
14420   std::map<int, double> atom_fracs = this->to_atom_frac();
14421   int state_id;
14422   for (comp_iter ci = comp.begin(); ci != comp.end(); ci++) {
14423     if (ci->first % 10000 > 0)
14424         state_id = nucname::id_to_state_id(ci->first);
14425     else
14426         state_id = ci->first;
14427 
14428     std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > raw_gammas = pyne::gammas(state_id);
14429     for (int i = 0; i < raw_gammas.size(); ++i) {
14430       result.push_back(std::make_pair(raw_gammas[i].first,
14431         atom_fracs[ci->first]*raw_gammas[i].second));
14432     }
14433   }
14434   return result;
14435 }
14436 
14437 std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > pyne::Material::xrays() {
14438   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > result;
14439   std::map<int, double> atom_fracs = this->to_atom_frac();
14440   int state_id;
14441   for (comp_iter ci = comp.begin(); ci != comp.end(); ci++) {
14442     if (ci->first % 10000 > 0)
14443         state_id = nucname::id_to_state_id(ci->first);
14444     else
14445         state_id = ci->first;
14446 
14447     std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > raw_xrays = pyne::xrays(state_id);
14448     for (int i = 0; i < raw_xrays.size(); ++i) {
14449       result.push_back(std::make_pair(raw_xrays[i].first,
14450         atom_fracs[ci->first]*raw_xrays[i].second));
14451     }
14452   }
14453   return result;
14454 }
14455 
14456 std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > pyne::Material::photons(bool norm) {
14457   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> >  txray = this->xrays();
14458   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> >  tgammas = this->gammas();
14459   for (int i = 0; i < txray.size(); ++i)
14460     tgammas.push_back(txray[i]);
14461   if (norm)
14462     tgammas = normalize_radioactivity(tgammas);
14463   return tgammas;
14464 }
14465 
14466 std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > pyne::Material::normalize_radioactivity(
14467 std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > unnormed) {
14468   std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > normed;
14469   double sum = 0.0;
14470   for (int i = 0; i < unnormed.size(); ++i) {
14471     if (!isnan(unnormed[i].second))
14472       sum = sum + unnormed[i].second;
14473   }
14474   for (int i = 0; i < unnormed.size(); ++i) {
14475     if (!isnan(unnormed[i].second)) {
14476       normed.push_back(std::make_pair(unnormed[i].first,
14477         (unnormed[i].second)/sum));
14478     }
14479   }
14480   return normed;
14481 }
14482 
14483 
14484 pyne::Material pyne::Material::operator+ (double y) {
14485   // Overloads x + y
14486   return pyne::Material(comp, mass + y, density);
14487 };
14488 
14489 
14490 
14491 pyne::Material pyne::Material::operator+ (Material y) {
14492   // Overloads x + y
14493   pyne::comp_map cm;
14494   pyne::comp_map xwgt = mult_by_mass();
14495   pyne::comp_map ywgt = y.mult_by_mass();
14496 
14497   for (pyne::comp_iter i = xwgt.begin(); i != xwgt.end(); i++) {
14498     if ( 0 < ywgt.count(i->first) )
14499       cm[i->first] = xwgt[i->first] + ywgt[i->first];
14500     else
14501       cm[i->first] = xwgt[i->first];
14502   };
14503 
14504   for (pyne::comp_iter i = ywgt.begin(); i != ywgt.end(); i++) {
14505     if ( 0 == cm.count(i->first) )
14506       cm[i->first] = ywgt[i->first];
14507   };
14508 
14509   return pyne::Material(cm, -1, -1);
14510 };
14511

14515   // Overloads x * y
14516   return pyne::Material(comp, mass * y, density);
14517 };

14521 pyne::Material pyne::Material::operator/ (double y) {
14522   // Overloads x / y
14523   return pyne::Material(comp, mass / y, density );
14524 }

14593 pyne_enr::Cascade pyne_enr::_fill_default_uranium_cascade() {

14600   duc.j = 922350000;
14601   duc.k = 922380000;

14604   duc.M = 10.0;

14608   duc.x_tail_j = 0.0025;

14621 
14622 double pyne_enr::feed_per_prod(double x_feed, double x_prod, double x_tail) {
14623   return 1 / prod_per_feed(x_feed, x_prod, x_tail);
14624 }
14625 
14626 double pyne_enr::feed_per_tail(double x_feed, double x_prod, double x_tail) {
14627   return 1 / tail_per_feed(x_feed, x_prod, x_tail);
14628 }
14629 
14630 double pyne_enr::prod_per_tail(double x_feed, double x_prod, double x_tail) {
14631   return 1 / tail_per_prod(x_feed, x_prod, x_tail);
14632 }
14633 
14634 double pyne_enr::prod_per_feed(double x_feed, double x_prod, double x_tail) {
14635   return (x_feed - x_tail) / (x_prod - x_tail);
14636 }
14637 
14638 double pyne_enr::tail_per_feed(double x_feed, double x_prod, double x_tail) {
14639   return (x_feed - x_prod) / (x_tail - x_prod);
14640 }
14641 
14642 double pyne_enr::tail_per_prod(double x_feed, double x_prod, double x_tail) {
14643   return (x_feed - x_prod) / (x_tail - x_feed);
14644 }
14645 
14646 double pyne_enr::value_func(double x) {
14647   return (2 * x - 1) * log(x / (1 - x));
14648 }
14649 
14650 double pyne_enr::swu_per_feed(double x_feed, double x_prod, double x_tail) {
14651   return
14652       prod_per_feed(x_feed, x_prod, x_tail) * value_func(x_prod) + \
14653       tail_per_feed(x_feed, x_prod, x_tail) * value_func(x_tail) - \
14654       value_func(x_feed);
14655 }
14656 
14657 double pyne_enr::swu_per_prod(double x_feed, double x_prod, double x_tail) {
14658   return
14659       value_func(x_prod) + \
14660       tail_per_prod(x_feed, x_prod, x_tail) * value_func(x_tail) - \
14661       feed_per_prod(x_feed, x_prod, x_tail) * value_func(x_feed);
14662 }
14663 
14664 double pyne_enr::swu_per_tail(double x_feed, double x_prod, double x_tail) {
14665   return
14666       prod_per_tail(x_feed, x_prod, x_tail) * value_func(x_prod) + \
14667       value_func(x_tail) - \
14668       feed_per_tail(x_feed, x_prod, x_tail) * value_func(x_feed);
14669 }
14670 
14671 
14672 double pyne_enr::alphastar_i(double alpha, double Mstar, double M_i) {
14673   // M_i is the mass of the ith nuclide
14674   return pow(alpha, (Mstar - M_i));
14675 }
14676 
14677 
14678 void pyne_enr::_recompute_nm(pyne_enr::Cascade & casc, double tolerance) {
14679 
14680   double ppf = prod_per_feed(casc.mat_feed.comp[casc.j], casc.x_prod_j, casc.x_tail_j);
14681   double tpf = tail_per_feed(casc.mat_feed.comp[casc.j], casc.x_prod_j, casc.x_tail_j);
14682   double astar_j = alphastar_i(casc.alpha, casc.Mstar, pyne::atomic_mass(casc.j));
14683 
14684   // Save original state of N & M
14685   double N = casc.N;
14686   double M = casc.M;
14687   double origN = casc.N;
14688   double origM = casc.M;
14689 
14690   double lhs_prod = ppf * casc.x_prod_j / casc.mat_feed.comp[casc.j];
14691   double rhs_prod = (pow(astar_j, M+1.0) - 1.0) / (pow(astar_j, M+1.0) - pow(astar_j, -N));
14692   double lhs_tail = tpf * casc.x_tail_j / casc.mat_feed.comp[casc.j];
14693   double rhs_tail = (1.0 - pow(astar_j, -N)) / (pow(astar_j, M+1.0) - pow(astar_j, -N));
14694 
14695   double n = 1.0;
14696   double delta_prod = lhs_prod - rhs_prod;
14697   double delta_tail = lhs_tail - rhs_tail;
14698   while (tolerance < fabs(delta_prod) && tolerance < fabs(delta_tail)) {
14699     delta_prod = lhs_prod - rhs_prod;
14700     delta_tail = lhs_tail - rhs_tail;
14701 
14702     if (tolerance < fabs(delta_prod)) {
14703       N = N - (delta_prod * N);
14704       rhs_prod = (pow(astar_j, M+1.0) - 1.0) / (pow(astar_j, M+1.0) - pow(astar_j, -N));
14705     };
14706 
14707     if (tolerance < fabs(delta_tail)) {
14708       M = M - (delta_tail * M);
14709       rhs_tail = (1.0 - pow(astar_j, -N)) / (pow(astar_j, M+1.0) - pow(astar_j, -N));
14710     };
14711 
14712     if (N < tolerance) {
14713       N = origN + n;
14714       M = origM + n;
14715       n = n + 1.0;
14716     };
14717 
14718     if (M < tolerance) {
14719       N = origN + n;
14720       M = origM + n;
14721       n = n + 1.0;
14722     };
14723   };
14724 
14725   casc.N = N;
14726   casc.M = M;
14727   return; 
14728 };
14729 
14730 
14731 
14732 void pyne_enr::_recompute_prod_tail_mats(pyne_enr::Cascade & casc) {
14733   //This function takes a given initial guess number of enriching and stripping stages 
14734   //for a given composition of fuel with a given jth key component, knowing the values 
14735   //that are desired in both Product and Tails streams.  Having this it solves for what 
14736   //the actual N and M stage numbers are and also what the product and waste streams 
14737   //compositions are.  It returns precisely these.
14738   pyne::comp_map comp_prod;
14739   pyne::comp_map comp_tail;
14740 
14741   int nuc;
14742   double astar_i, numer_prod, numer_tail, denom_prod, denom_tail;
14743 
14744   double N = casc.N;
14745   double M = casc.M;
14746 
14747   double ppf = prod_per_feed(casc.mat_feed.comp[casc.j], casc.x_prod_j, casc.x_tail_j);
14748   double tpf = tail_per_feed(casc.mat_feed.comp[casc.j], casc.x_prod_j, casc.x_tail_j);
14749 
14750   for (pyne::comp_iter i = casc.mat_feed.comp.begin(); i != casc.mat_feed.comp.end(); i++) {
14751     nuc = (i->first);
14752     astar_i = alphastar_i(casc.alpha, casc.Mstar, pyne::atomic_mass(nuc));
14753 
14754     // calc prod comp
14755     numer_prod = casc.mat_feed.comp[nuc] * (pow(astar_i, M+1.0) - 1.0);
14756     denom_prod = (pow(astar_i, M+1.0) - pow(astar_i, -N)) / ppf;
14757     comp_prod[nuc] = numer_prod / denom_prod;
14758 
14759     // calc tail comp
14760     numer_tail = casc.mat_feed.comp[nuc] * (1.0 - pow(astar_i, -N));
14761     denom_tail = (pow(astar_i, M+1.0) - pow(astar_i, -N)) / tpf;
14762     comp_tail[nuc] = numer_tail / denom_tail;
14763   };
14764 
14765   casc.mat_prod = pyne::Material(comp_prod);
14766   casc.mat_tail = pyne::Material(comp_tail);
14767   return;
14768 };
14769 
14770 
14771 
14772 pyne_enr::Cascade pyne_enr::_norm_comp_secant(pyne_enr::Cascade & casc, \
14773                                               double tolerance, int max_iter) {
14774   // This function actually solves the whole system of equations.  It uses _recompute_prod_tail_mats 
14775   // to find the roots for the enriching and stripping stage numbers.  It then 
14776   // checks to see if the product and waste streams meet their target enrichments
14777   // for the jth component like they should.  If they don't then it trys other values 
14778   // of N and M varied by the Secant ethod.  Rinse and repeat as needed.
14779   int j = casc.j;
14780   pyne_enr::Cascade prev_casc = casc;
14781   pyne_enr::Cascade curr_casc = casc;
14782 
14783   // Is the history of N and M that has been input
14784   unsigned int h;
14785   int niter = 0;
14786   int max_hist = max_iter / 10;
14787   std::vector<double> historyN;
14788   std::vector<double> historyM;
14789 
14790   // Initialize prev point
14791   prev_casc.N += 1.0;
14792   prev_casc.M += 1.0;
14793   _recompute_nm(prev_casc, tolerance);
14794   _recompute_prod_tail_mats(prev_casc);
14795   historyN.push_back(prev_casc.N);
14796   historyM.push_back(prev_casc.M);
14797 
14798 
14799   // Initialize current point
14800   _recompute_nm(curr_casc, tolerance);
14801   _recompute_prod_tail_mats(curr_casc);
14802   historyN.push_back(curr_casc.N);
14803   historyM.push_back(curr_casc.M);
14804 
14805   // My guess is that what we are checkin here is that the isotopic compositions
14806   // make sense with abs(1.0 - masscurr_P) rather than calculatign the 
14807   // relative product to watse mass streams.
14808   double prev_N = prev_casc.N;
14809   double prev_M = prev_casc.M;
14810   double curr_N = curr_casc.N;
14811   double curr_M = curr_casc.M;
14812   double temp_prev_N = 0.0;
14813   double temp_prev_M = 0.0;
14814   double temp_curr_N = 0.0;
14815   double temp_curr_M = 0.0;
14816 
14817   double delta_x_prod_j = casc.x_prod_j - curr_casc.mat_prod.comp[j];
14818   double delta_x_tail_j = casc.x_tail_j - curr_casc.mat_tail.comp[j];
14819 
14820   while ((tolerance < fabs(delta_x_prod_j) / curr_casc.mat_prod.comp[j]  || \
14821           tolerance < fabs(delta_x_tail_j) / curr_casc.mat_tail.comp[j]) && \
14822           niter < max_iter) {
14823     delta_x_prod_j = casc.x_prod_j - curr_casc.mat_prod.comp[j];
14824     delta_x_tail_j = casc.x_tail_j - curr_casc.mat_tail.comp[j];
14825 
14826     if (tolerance <= fabs(delta_x_prod_j)/curr_casc.mat_prod.comp[j]) {
14827       // Make a new guess for N
14828       temp_curr_N = curr_N;
14829       temp_prev_N = prev_N;
14830       curr_N = curr_N + delta_x_prod_j*\
14831               ((curr_N - prev_N)/(curr_casc.mat_prod.comp[j] - prev_casc.mat_prod.comp[j]));
14832       prev_N = temp_curr_N;
14833 
14834       // If the new value of N is less than zero, reset.
14835       if (curr_N < 0.0)
14836         curr_N = (temp_curr_N + temp_prev_N)/2.0;
14837     };
14838 
14839     if (tolerance <= fabs(delta_x_tail_j)/curr_casc.mat_tail.comp[j]) {
14840       // Make a new guess for M
14841       temp_curr_M = curr_M;
14842       temp_prev_M = prev_M;
14843       curr_M = curr_M + delta_x_tail_j*\
14844                ((curr_M - prev_M)/(curr_casc.mat_tail.comp[j] - prev_casc.mat_tail.comp[j]));
14845       prev_M = temp_curr_M;
14846 
14847       // If the new value of M is less than zero, reset.
14848       if (curr_M < 0.0)
14849         curr_M = (temp_curr_M + temp_prev_M)/2.0;
14850     };
14851 
14852     // Check for infinite loops
14853     for (h = 0; h < historyN.size(); h++) {
14854       if (historyN[h] == curr_N && historyM[h] == curr_M) {
14855         curr_N = curr_N + delta_x_prod_j * \
14856               ((curr_N - prev_N)/(curr_casc.mat_prod.comp[j] - prev_casc.mat_prod.comp[j]));
14857         curr_M = curr_M + delta_x_tail_j * \
14858                ((curr_M - prev_M)/(curr_casc.mat_tail.comp[j] - prev_casc.mat_tail.comp[j]));;
14859         break;
14860       };
14861     };
14862 
14863     if (max_hist <= historyN.size()) {
14864       historyN.erase(historyN.begin());
14865       historyM.erase(historyM.begin());
14866     };
14867     historyN.push_back(curr_N);
14868     historyM.push_back(curr_M);
14869 
14870     niter += 1;
14871 
14872     // Calculate new isotopics for valid (N, M)        
14873     prev_casc = curr_casc;
14874     curr_casc.N = curr_N;
14875     curr_casc.M = curr_M;
14876     _recompute_nm(curr_casc, tolerance);
14877     _recompute_prod_tail_mats(curr_casc);
14878   };
14879   return curr_casc;
14880 };
14881 
14882 
14883 
14884 double pyne_enr::_deltaU_i_OverG(pyne_enr::Cascade & casc, int i) {
14885   // Solves for a stage separative power relevant to the ith component
14886   // per unit of flow G.  This is taken from Equation 31 divided by G 
14887   // from the paper "Wood, Houston G., Borisevich, V. D. and Sulaberidze, G. A.,
14888   // 'On a Criterion Efficiency for Multi-Isotope Mixtures Separation', 
14889   // Separation Science and Technology, 34:3, 343 - 357"
14890   // To link to this article: DOI: 10.1081/SS-100100654
14891   // URL: http://dx.doi.org/10.1081/SS-100100654
14892 
14893   double astar_i = alphastar_i(casc.alpha, casc.Mstar, pyne::atomic_mass(i));
14894   return log(pow(casc.alpha, (casc.Mstar - pyne::atomic_mass(casc.j)) )) * \
14895                              ((astar_i - 1.0)/(astar_i + 1.0));
14896 };
14897 
14898 
14899 pyne_enr::Cascade pyne_enr::solve_numeric(pyne_enr::Cascade & orig_casc, \
14900                                           double tolerance, int max_iter) {
14901   // This function finds the total flow rate (L) over the feed flow rate (F)
14902   pyne_enr::Cascade casc = orig_casc;
14903 
14904   casc = _norm_comp_secant(casc, tolerance, max_iter);
14905 
14906   int nuc;
14907   int j = casc.j;
14908   int k = casc.k;
14909   double ppf = prod_per_feed(casc.mat_feed.comp[j], casc.x_prod_j, casc.x_tail_j);
14910   double tpf = tail_per_feed(casc.mat_feed.comp[j], casc.x_prod_j, casc.x_tail_j);
14911 
14912   // Matched Flow Ratios
14913   double rfeed = casc.mat_feed.comp[j] / casc.mat_feed.comp[k];
14914   double rprod = casc.mat_prod.comp[j] / casc.mat_prod.comp[k];
14915   double rtail = casc.mat_tail.comp[j] / casc.mat_tail.comp[k];
14916 
14917   double ltotpf = 0.0;
14918   double swupf = 0.0;
14919   double temp_numer = 0.0; 
14920 
14921   for (pyne::comp_iter i = casc.mat_feed.comp.begin(); i != casc.mat_feed.comp.end(); i++) {
14922     nuc = (i->first);
14923     temp_numer = (ppf*casc.mat_prod.comp[nuc]*log(rprod) + \
14924                   tpf*casc.mat_tail.comp[nuc]*log(rtail) - \
14925                       casc.mat_feed.comp[nuc]*log(rfeed));
14926     ltotpf = ltotpf + (temp_numer / _deltaU_i_OverG(casc, nuc));
14927     swupf = swupf + temp_numer;
14928   };
14929 
14930   // Assign flow rates
14931   casc.l_t_per_feed = ltotpf;
14932 
14933   // The -1 term is put in the SWU calculation because otherwise swupf   
14934   // represents the SWU that would be undone if you were to deenrich the 
14935   // whole process.  Thus the SWU to enrich is -1x this number.  This is 
14936   // a by-product of the value function used as a constraint.
14937   casc.swu_per_feed = -1 * swupf;       // This is the SWU for 1 kg of Feed material.
14938   casc.swu_per_prod = -1 * swupf / ppf; // This is the SWU for 1 kg of Product material.
14939 
14940   // Assign isotopic streams the proper masses.
14941   casc.mat_prod.mass = casc.mat_feed.mass * ppf;
14942   casc.mat_tail.mass = casc.mat_feed.mass * tpf;
14943   return casc;
14944 };
14945 
14946 pyne_enr::Cascade pyne_enr::multicomponent(pyne_enr::Cascade & orig_casc, \
14947                                     char * solver, double tolerance, int max_iter) {
14948   std::string strsolver(solver);
14949   return multicomponent(orig_casc, strsolver, tolerance, max_iter);
14950 };
14951 
14952 pyne_enr::Cascade pyne_enr::multicomponent(pyne_enr::Cascade & orig_casc, \
14953                                     std::string solver, double tolerance, int max_iter) {
14954   // The multicomponent() function finds a value of Mstar by minimzing the seperative power.  
14955   // Note that Mstar0 represents an intial guess at what Mstar might be.
14956   // This is the final function that actually solves for an optimized M* that makes the cascade!
14957   pyne_enr::Cascade temp_casc;
14958   pyne_enr::Cascade prev_casc = orig_casc;
14959   pyne_enr::Cascade curr_casc = orig_casc;
14960 
14961   // define the solver to use
14962   int solver_code;
14963   if (solver == "symbolic")
14964     solver_code = 0;
14965   else if (solver == "numeric")
14966     solver_code = 1;
14967   else 
14968     throw "solver not known: " + solver;
14969 
14970   // validate Mstar or pick new value
14971   if ((orig_casc.Mstar < pyne::atomic_mass(orig_casc.j) &&  \
14972        orig_casc.Mstar < pyne::atomic_mass(orig_casc.k)) || \
14973       (orig_casc.Mstar > pyne::atomic_mass(orig_casc.j) &&  \
14974        orig_casc.Mstar > pyne::atomic_mass(orig_casc.k))) {
14975     double ms = (pyne::atomic_mass(orig_casc.j) + pyne::atomic_mass(orig_casc.k)) / 2.0;
14976     prev_casc.Mstar = ms;
14977     curr_casc.Mstar = ms;
14978   };
14979 
14980   // xpn is the exponential index 
14981   double ooe = -log10(tolerance);
14982   double xpn = 1.0;
14983 
14984   // Initialize previous point
14985   switch (solver_code) {
14986     case 0:
14987       prev_casc = solve_symbolic(prev_casc);
14988       break;
14989     case 1:
14990       prev_casc = solve_numeric(prev_casc, tolerance, max_iter);
14991       break;
14992   };
14993 
14994   // Initialize curr_ent point
14995   curr_casc.Mstar = (pyne::atomic_mass(curr_casc.j) + curr_casc.Mstar) / 2.0;
14996   switch (solver_code) {
14997     case 0:
14998       curr_casc = solve_symbolic(curr_casc);
14999       break;
15000     case 1:
15001       curr_casc = solve_numeric(curr_casc, tolerance, max_iter);
15002       break;
15003   };
15004 
15005   double m = pyne::slope(curr_casc.Mstar, curr_casc.l_t_per_feed, \
15006                          prev_casc.Mstar, prev_casc.l_t_per_feed);
15007   double m_sign = m / fabs(m);
15008 
15009   double temp_m;
15010   double temp_m_sign;
15011 
15012   while (tolerance < fabs(curr_casc.l_t_per_feed - prev_casc.l_t_per_feed) / curr_casc.l_t_per_feed) {
15013     // Check that parameters are still well-formed
15014     if (isnan(curr_casc.Mstar) || isnan(curr_casc.l_t_per_feed) || \
15015         isnan(prev_casc.Mstar) || isnan(prev_casc.l_t_per_feed))
15016       throw EnrichmentIterationNaN();
15017 
15018     prev_casc = curr_casc;
15019 
15020     curr_casc.Mstar = curr_casc.Mstar - (m_sign * pow(10.0, -xpn));
15021     switch (solver_code) {
15022       case 0:
15023         curr_casc = solve_symbolic(curr_casc);
15024         break;
15025       case 1:
15026         curr_casc = solve_numeric(curr_casc, tolerance, max_iter);
15027         break;
15028     };
15029 
15030     if (prev_casc.l_t_per_feed < curr_casc.l_t_per_feed) {
15031       temp_casc = curr_casc;
15032       temp_casc.Mstar = temp_casc.Mstar - (m_sign * pow(10.0, -xpn));
15033       switch (solver_code) {
15034         case 0:
15035           temp_casc = solve_symbolic(temp_casc);
15036           break;
15037         case 1:
15038           temp_casc = solve_numeric(temp_casc, tolerance, max_iter);
15039           break;
15040       };
15041 
15042       temp_m = pyne::slope(curr_casc.Mstar, curr_casc.l_t_per_feed, \
15043                            temp_casc.Mstar, temp_casc.l_t_per_feed);
15044       if (temp_m == 0.0) {
15045         prev_casc = curr_casc;
15046         curr_casc = temp_casc;
15047         break;
15048       };
15049 
15050       temp_m_sign = temp_m / fabs(temp_m);
15051       if (m_sign != temp_m_sign) {
15052         xpn = xpn + 1;
15053 
15054         temp_casc = prev_casc;
15055         temp_casc.Mstar = temp_casc.Mstar + (m_sign * pow(10.0, -xpn));
15056         switch (solver_code) {
15057           case 0:
15058             temp_casc = solve_symbolic(temp_casc);
15059             break;
15060           case 1:
15061             temp_casc = solve_numeric(temp_casc, tolerance, max_iter);
15062             break;
15063         };
15064         temp_m = pyne::slope(prev_casc.Mstar, prev_casc.l_t_per_feed, \
15065                              temp_casc.Mstar, temp_casc.l_t_per_feed);
15066 
15067         if (temp_m == 0.0) {
15068           prev_casc = curr_casc;
15069           curr_casc = temp_casc;
15070           break;
15071         };
15072 
15073         m_sign = temp_m / fabs(temp_m);
15074         m = temp_m;
15075         prev_casc = curr_casc;
15076         curr_casc = temp_casc;
15077       };
15078     };
15079   };
15080 
15081   return curr_casc;
15082 };

16128   xF[1] = casc.mat_feed.comp[k];
16129   for(pyne::comp_iter ci = casc.mat_feed.comp.begin(); ci != casc.mat_feed.comp.end(); ci++)
16130   {
16131     nuc = (*ci).first;
16132     if (nuc == j || nuc == k)
16133         continue;

16135     xF[i] = (*ci).second;
16136     i++;
